<div class="pointer-events-none h-px w-px absolute bottom-0" aria-hidden="true" data-edge="true"> </div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"212\"><strong data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"126\">MAN:</strong> Sandra – I seem to remember you had some family visitors staying with you recently.</p>\n<p data-start=\"214\" data-end=\"306\"><strong data-start=\"214\" data-end=\"225\">SANDRA:</strong> Yeah that’s right. My brother and his family were here a couple of months ago.</p>\n<p data-start=\"308\" data-end=\"474\"><strong data-start=\"308\" data-end=\"316\">MAN:</strong> Oh good. Well I wanted to ask your advice – I’ve got my cousin and her family visiting next month and as I don’t have kids I’ve no idea where to take them.</p>\n<p data-start=\"476\" data-end=\"568\"><strong data-start=\"476\" data-end=\"487\">SANDRA:</strong> Right. What about accommodation? Are they going to stay with you in your flat?</p>\n<p data-start=\"570\" data-end=\"685\"><strong data-start=\"570\" data-end=\"578\">MAN:</strong> No, thankfully – there wouldn’t be room – my cousin wants me to recommend a hotel. Do you know anywhere?</p>\n<p data-start=\"687\" data-end=\"771\"><strong data-start=\"687\" data-end=\"698\">SANDRA:</strong> Yes, I do actually. I always recommend people stay at the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(1) Kings</strong></span> Hotel.</p>\n<p data-start=\"773\" data-end=\"802\"><strong data-start=\"773\" data-end=\"781\">MAN:</strong> Where’s that near?</p>\n<p data-start=\"804\" data-end=\"922\"><strong data-start=\"804\" data-end=\"815\">SANDRA:</strong> It’s about five minutes’ walk from Murray Station – so nice and central. It’s actually on George Street.</p>\n<p data-start=\"924\" data-end=\"1032\"><strong data-start=\"924\" data-end=\"932\">MAN:</strong> Oh yes I know. I think they’re on quite a tight budget – so how much roughly is it to stay there?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1034\" data-end=\"1195\"><strong data-start=\"1034\" data-end=\"1045\">SANDRA:</strong> If you book a family room it’s about <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) £125</strong></span> per night. My brother paid for two double rooms in the end and I think that was around £95 for each room.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1197\" data-end=\"1230\"><strong data-start=\"1197\" data-end=\"1205\">MAN:</strong> Oh that’s not too bad.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1232\" data-end=\"1280\"><strong data-start=\"1232\" data-end=\"1243\">SANDRA:</strong> So how old are your cousin’s kids?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1282\" data-end=\"1457\"><strong data-start=\"1282\" data-end=\"1290\">MAN:</strong> Twelve and nine. So I want to organise some trips while they’re here. I was thinking of doing a bus tour of the city centre – as none of them have been here before.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1459\" data-end=\"1698\"><strong data-start=\"1459\" data-end=\"1470\">SANDRA:</strong> Those bus tours are quite expensive. I think it’s better to do a <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(3) walking</span></strong> tour – it gives you a much better feel for the city. There’s one that starts from Carlton Square. It takes a couple of hours and doesn’t cost that much.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1700\" data-end=\"1751\"><strong data-start=\"1700\" data-end=\"1708\">MAN:</strong> Sounds good. I’ll look that up – thanks.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1753\" data-end=\"1895\"><strong data-start=\"1753\" data-end=\"1764\">SANDRA:</strong> If the weather’s nice, one thing you could do is visit the old fort. You can get there by <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(4) boat</span></strong>. The whole trip takes half a day.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1897\" data-end=\"2086\"><strong data-start=\"1897\" data-end=\"1905\">MAN:</strong> That’s a really good idea. I’d like to do that myself. And if the weather’s bad I was thinking they could go to the Science Museum. But maybe they could do that when I’m at work.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2088\" data-end=\"2145\"><strong data-start=\"2088\" data-end=\"2099\">SANDRA:</strong> Yeah – don’t forget it’s closed on Mondays.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2147\" data-end=\"2235\"><strong data-start=\"2147\" data-end=\"2155\">MAN:</strong> They’re here from Saturday for four nights so <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(5) Tuesday</span></strong> would be best, I think.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2237\" data-end=\"2439\"><strong data-start=\"2237\" data-end=\"2248\">SANDRA:</strong> Mmm, and it won’t be so crowded then. Saturdays are terrible. I took my kids to the exhibition on old computers there and it was far too crowded. I wanted to go back but it’s finished now.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2441\" data-end=\"2509\"><strong data-start=\"2441\" data-end=\"2449\">MAN:</strong> That’s a shame. My cousin’s kids would have enjoyed that.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2511\" data-end=\"2596\"><strong data-start=\"2511\" data-end=\"2522\">SANDRA:</strong> There’s another one starting soon on <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(6) space</strong></span> which looks really good too.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2598\" data-end=\"2649\"><strong data-start=\"2598\" data-end=\"2606\">MAN:</strong> OK, well I’ll mention that to my cousin.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2656\" data-end=\"2719\"><strong data-start=\"2656\" data-end=\"2667\">SANDRA:</strong> Have you thought about where to take them to eat?</p>\n<p data-start=\"2721\" data-end=\"2872\"><strong data-start=\"2721\" data-end=\"2729\">MAN:</strong> Well I really like all the food stalls at Clacton Market. My cousin’s <br><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) vegetarian</strong></span> – I know it’s one of the best places for that kind of food.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2874\" data-end=\"3055\"><strong data-start=\"2874\" data-end=\"2885\">SANDRA:</strong> Definitely, and there’ll be loads of choice for the kids, too. You need to get there quite early though – at the weekend most of the stalls stop serving lunch at <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(8) 2.30</span></strong>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3057\" data-end=\"3220\"><strong data-start=\"3057\" data-end=\"3065\">MAN:</strong> Good point. It’s all going to need careful planning! My cousin said she’d love to take the kids to a show at the theatre – but tickets are so expensive!</p>\n<hr data-start=\"3222\" data-end=\"3225\">\n<p data-start=\"3227\" data-end=\"3381\"><strong data-start=\"3227\" data-end=\"3238\">SANDRA:</strong> I know. But you can get some good deals if you book online with bargaintickets.com the following day – on some seats there’s a<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (9) 75%</strong></span> discount.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3383\" data-end=\"3426\"><strong data-start=\"3383\" data-end=\"3391\">MAN:</strong> Really? I must try and get some.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3428\" data-end=\"3530\"><strong data-start=\"3428\" data-end=\"3439\">SANDRA:</strong> Yeah. There are lots of things you can do for free as well – no need to spend a fortune.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3532\" data-end=\"3553\"><strong data-start=\"3532\" data-end=\"3540\">MAN:</strong> Like what?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3555\" data-end=\"3697\"><strong data-start=\"3555\" data-end=\"3566\">SANDRA:</strong> They’re coming next month, right? Well, check and see if it’s the same weekend as the Roots Music Festival in Blackwell Gardens.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3699\" data-end=\"3725\"><strong data-start=\"3699\" data-end=\"3707\">MAN:</strong> R-double-O-T-S?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3727\" data-end=\"3832\"><strong data-start=\"3727\" data-end=\"3738\">SANDRA:</strong> Yeah. Check it out online. It’s always a family-friendly event and there’s no entry charge.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3834\" data-end=\"3865\"><strong data-start=\"3834\" data-end=\"3842\">MAN:</strong> That sounds perfect.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3867\" data-end=\"4044\"><strong data-start=\"3867\" data-end=\"3878\">SANDRA:</strong> And if you’re in Blackwell Gardens – climb Telegraph Hill – you’ll be able to look right down on the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) port</strong></span>. Everyone’s always really impressed because it’s so huge.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4046\" data-end=\"4136\"><strong data-start=\"4046\" data-end=\"4054\">MAN:</strong> Oh yeah – I’ve been meaning to do that for ages. I’ve heard the view’s amazing.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4138\" data-end=\"4187\"><strong data-start=\"4138\" data-end=\"4149\">SANDRA:</strong> Yeah. It’s really worth the effort.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4189\" data-end=\"4269\"><strong data-start=\"4189\" data-end=\"4197\">MAN:</strong> Well that’s given me loads of ideas. Thanks so much for all the info.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4568cd00-3619-4bdd-b43c-fbed009da948', '07a30f62-a036-432a-97f0-abd50118d6cb', 'checkbox', 'Questions 11–12', '', '<p data-start="126" data-end="154">Choose <strong data-start="133" data-end="140">TWO</strong> letters, A–E.</p>
<p data-start="156" data-end="248">Which <strong data-start="162" data-end="169">TWO</strong> things does the speaker say about visiting the football stadium with children?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A Children can get their photo taken with a football player"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B There is a competition for children today"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C Parents must stay with their children at all times"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D Children will need sunhats and drinks"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E The café has a special offer on meals for children"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"134\" data-end=\"353\">Good morning, and welcome to City Football Club. I’d like to give you some useful information about your visit to the stadium today, and then we’ll start the tour of the areas of the stadium that are open to visitors.</p>\n<p data-start=\"355\" data-end=\"1278\">I can see lots of children here today, so just to let mums and dads know a few things before we start. The stadium has lots of stairs, and the players’ tunnel is very dark. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(11) Please don’t let your children wander off on their own, even for a minute</strong></span>. We don’t want any accidents or anyone getting frightened. Cameras are permitted everywhere, and you can take pictures of your child shooting a penalty. Assistants are helping to organise this, and hopefully the queue won’t be too long – it’s very hot and sunny out on the pitch today. You can get food and drink at the café, and I really recommend the healthy lunch boxes for children. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(12) Also in the café, children are invited to do a football-themed drawing. We’ll pick the best one at the end of the afternoon</span></strong>, so don’t forget to put your name and contact details on the back. That way, if you’ve left the stadium, we’ll send your prize, but sadly we can’t return drawings.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1280\" data-end=\"2073\">I’d like to mention some features of the tour. We’ll start with the three-sixty cinema experience, which has been very popular over the years, and then I’ll take you to the players’ dressing rooms before going outside to the seating area and the pitch. I should say, <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(13) if you’d prefer your visit to be self-guided, please collect headphones from the reception, and then you can listen to the pre-recorded information at your own speed. We’ve only just introduced this feature</span></strong>, and would appreciate your feedback. We’re thinking of offering just tours in other languages in future so if you have any thoughts on that, we’d welcome those too. If you plan to return another time, you might like to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(14) book one of our VIP tours – we’ve only just started offering these</strong></span>, and they can be booked online.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2075\" data-end=\"2454\">Now, the stadium you see today was built in 1989, as part of a three-year redevelopment project – while that project was going on, the team had to play its matches at the ground of another club – apart from that, the club has been here on this site since 1870. As some of you may know, that was the start of a really important decade in the history of football in this country.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2506\" data-end=\"2727\">For example, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(15) 1870 was also the year that football teams started to include a player whose role it was to guard the goal</strong></span>. It’s hard to imagine what the game must have been like without someone in that position, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-start=\"2729\" data-end=\"2985\">In 1872 and 73, many other clubs were established, both here and abroad, and the following year, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(16) in 1874, referees were allowed to send players off if they committed certain offences. And also in that year, teams started having to swap ends at half-time.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2987\" data-end=\"3280\">One fact I was interested to discover was that in early football games, the aim was for the scorer to get the ball between two flag posts, and later between sticks joined at the top with a piece of tape. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(17) In 1875, that tape was replaced with the solid crossbar that we’re familiar with today.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"3282\" data-end=\"3683\">1877 saw the founding of further new clubs, and the history books tell us that <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(18) in the same year, all the clubs decided to set a limit of ninety minutes for each match.</span></strong> Before that, it was a more casual arrangement, and this sometimes caused huge arguments – and sometimes fights – during matches, when one team called the end of the game and the other team wanted to play on to score a winning goal.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3685\" data-end=\"3948\">By 1878, the number of teams in the football league increased again. In addition, referees started using whistles, and <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(19) electric lamps were installed on certain pitches</span></strong>. This was a significant change, as games could then be played in the evenings all year round.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3950\" data-end=\"4229\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(20) In 1880, clubs began to charge fans for admission to games</span></strong>, even though players were still amateurs and had other ‘proper’ jobs. That’s hard to imagine in the modern professional game where top players earn significant sums of money from both playing and commercial activities.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('834870a4-548e-4ca9-b796-464982642e43', '07a30f62-a036-432a-97f0-abd50118d6cb', 'checkbox', 'Questions 13–14', '', '<p data-start="544" data-end="572">Choose <strong data-start="551" data-end="558">TWO</strong> letters, A–E.</p>
<p data-start="574" data-end="635">Which <strong data-start="580" data-end="587">TWO</strong> features of the stadium tour are new this year?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A VIP tour"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B 360 cinema experience"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C audio guide"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D dressing room tour"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E tours in other languages"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7b2da1d2-e578-43c5-99e5-4798b87216ab', 'e6213f11-b604-4534-b0c3-0b55b8775c40', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23–24', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>problems do Dean and Hannah identify in their lesson?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A the materials", "correct": false}, {"option": "B the student grouping", "correct": true}, {"option": "C the lesson structure", "correct": false}, {"option": "D the teacher coordination", "correct": false}, {"option": "E the timing", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5815652e-0eb3-4bec-948d-4b32cb1ca974', '07a30f62-a036-432a-97f0-abd50118d6cb', 'matching', 'Questions 15–20', '', '<p data-start="107" data-end="198">Which event in the history of football in the UK took place in each of the following years?</p>
<p data-start="200" data-end="303">Choose <strong data-start="207" data-end="214">SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong data-start="266" data-end="273">A–H</strong>, next to Questions <strong data-start="293" data-end="302">15–20</strong>.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Year</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1870 {the introduction of goalkeepers}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1874 {two changes to the rules of the game}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1875 {a change to the design of the goal}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1877 {an agreement on the length of a game}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1878 {the first use of lights for matches}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1880 {the introduction of a fee for spectators}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "the introduction of pay for the players"}, {"optionText": "a change to the design of the goal"}, {"optionText": "the first use of lights for matches"}, {"optionText": "the introduction of goalkeepers"}, {"optionText": "the first international match"}, {"optionText": "two changes to the rules of the game"}, {"optionText": "the introduction of a fee for spectators"}, {"optionText": "an agreement on the length of a game"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ab208bc9-da50-4029-a695-6b314f2ea7ae', '21a8c315-7f0a-47b9-8c0a-c69c49e7bd08', 'radio', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">Choose </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">TRUE</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;"> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">FALSE</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;"> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;"> if there is no information on this.</span></span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Mayan ruling class forbade the use of cocoa and chocolate in rituals."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Spanish explorer Hernán Cortés had made an investment in chocolate and chocolate beverages."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Wild cocoa trees are more susceptible to infectious diseases than cultivated ones."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "During chocolate production, some of the seeds are discarded."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Chocolate enjoys more prestige in Europe and the United States than in any other country."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32. The Mayan ruling class forbade the use of cocoa and chocolate in rituals.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “<strong>While the aristocracy, particularly the royal families, consumed chocolate during elaborate ceremonies</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giới quý tộc Maya (<strong>ruling class</strong>) tiêu thụ sô cô la trong các nghi lễ trang trọng, mâu thuẫn với việc họ cấm đoán (forbade).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>33. The Spanish explorer Hernán Cortés had made an investment in chocolate and chocolate beverages.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “…later Spanish explorer Hernán Cortés quickly <strong>recognised the potential economic value of chocolate</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cortés nhận ra giá trị kinh tế của sô cô la, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> xác nhận ông đã đầu tư (made an investment) vào lĩnh vực này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. Wild cocoa trees are more susceptible to infectious diseases than cultivated ones.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Unexpectedly, <strong>cocoa trees grown on farms are more vulnerable to disease and pests than their wild counterparts</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cây trồng (cultivated) dễ bị bệnh hơn cây dại (wild), mâu thuẫn với nhận định cây dại dễ bị bệnh hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. During chocolate production, some of the seeds are discarded.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Workers first sort, clean, and roast the <strong>beans</strong> before extracting the outer shells, leaving only the inner <strong>nibs</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các hạt ca cao (beans) được tách vỏ để lấy lõi (nibs), nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về việc loại bỏ (discarded) một phần hạt nào trong quá trình này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>36. Chocolate enjoys more prestige in Europe and the United States than in any other country.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “…and its reputation remains <strong>most prominent in Europe and the United States</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Danh tiếng (prestige) của sô cô la nổi bật nhất ở Châu Âu và Mỹ, ngụ ý hơn bất kỳ quốc gia nào khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0834ad0b-692d-4b6a-bfd3-e50675420e1c', '21a8c315-7f0a-47b9-8c0a-c69c49e7bd08', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–40', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">Complete the flow-chart below.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">Write </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> from the passage for each answer.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">From Cocoa Beans to Chocolate</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Seeds</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">classifying, cleaning, and roasting</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">stripping their {outer shells}</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">↓</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Nibs</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">↓</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Crushing</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">producing </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">{chocolate liquor}</span></span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">mixing with measured quantities of substances such as sweeteners, liquid dairy, and </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">{cocoa butter}</span></span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">↓</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Crumb blending</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">crushing finely to obtain a smooth texture manufacturing diverse shapes of chocolate in </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">{moulds}</span></span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">↓</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Chocolate</span></strong></span></p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong>37. Seeds classifying, cleaning, and roasting stripping their <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> outer shells</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>outer shells</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Workers first sort, clean, and roast the beans before extracting the <strong>outer shells</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong>38. Nibs Crushing producing <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> chocolate liquor</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>chocolate liquor</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “These nibs I are then ground into a dense paste known as <strong>chocolate liquor</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong>39. mixing with measured quantities of substances such as sweeteners, liquid dairy, and <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> cocoa butter</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>cocoa butter</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Chocolate manufacturers blend the chocolate liquor with precise ratios of sugar, milk, and <strong>cocoa butter</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong>40. Crumb blending crushing finely to obtain a smooth texture manufacturing diverse shapes of chocolate in <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> moulds</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>moulds</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “…before being placed into <strong>moulds</strong> to create various forms, such as bars or other chocolate products.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cb55f57d-8c57-48a7-a50a-40b23fffdb0c', 'a9c975b1-0bc6-46c8-80e5-8a6af07dbcc2', 'radio', 'Questions 21–25', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Climate change and allergies</strong></span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A.because people’s diets have improved since the 1950s"}, {"content": "B.because most people get enough vitamin D"}, {"content": "C.because the evidence only applies in Britain"}], "question": "Why is Beth unconvinced that allergies are linked to vitamin D deficiency?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A.will mean distribution of pollen over a wider area."}, {"content": "B.are having less impact on pollen than milder winters."}, {"content": "C.are responsible for higher quantities of pollen."}], "question": "Eliot explains that rising CO2 levels"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A.There is no clear short-term trend for the arrival of spring."}, {"content": "B.In general, spring is likely to continue arriving early."}, {"content": "C.Springs are becoming milder and longer."}], "question": "What does Beth say about seasonal changes?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A.it is spreading to more countries."}, {"content": "B.it is the most widespread cause of allergies globally."}, {"content": "C.it causes the most severe type of allergy."}], "question": "What point is made about the plant ragweed?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A.Trees produce more pollen there."}, {"content": "B.There is less to absorb the tree pollen."}, {"content": "C.There is not enough control over tree-planting."}], "question": "Why is tree pollen a more serious problem in cities?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2> (Section 3) Climate Change and Allergies</h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Have you had a chance to look at the information for our project yet Beth?</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> I’ve had a look at most of the stuff on the relationship between climate change and allergies and the role played by pollen from flowering plants and trees.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Yeah, me too. The main message is that seasonal allergies seem to be getting worse in just the last 20 years. The amount of pollen that’s produced by the flowers on birch trees has tripled, and one in four people suffers from either hay fever or asthma which is triggered by pollen.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> I read something about allergy sufferers being more likely to have a vitamin D deficiency because we no longer take cod liver oil as a vitamin supplement like many people used to do in the 1950s in Britain, and since then allergies have quadrupled in most European countries. <span class=\"citation-457\">But it was only in </span><strong><span class=\"citation-457\">(21) Britain (C)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-457 citation-end-457\"> that cod liver oil was so popular, so that argument doesn’t really make sense<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ4ww\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> No, it doesn’t seem that relevant. What seems to be happening now is that an increasing number of people are getting their first attack in their 40s and fifties.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Hmm, that must be because of the link with climate change causing rising temperatures.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> But CO2 levels are seriously affecting pollen counts too, as much as milder winters. Definitely. <span class=\"citation-456\">CO2 helps stimulate plant growth and several recent studies have shown that when plants are exposed to more CO2 they produce </span><strong><span class=\"citation-456\">(22) more pollen (C)</span></strong></p>\n<p><!----><!----><strong>Beth:</strong> Really? So people might experience more severe allergic symptoms in future.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5Aw\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> That’s right. Hmm, and another factor is that the pollen season is changing. Yes, scientists are predicting spring will come five weeks earlier by 2130, that’s in the long term. But that doesn’t mean that spring will come earlier every year. Look at last winter, that was really cold until March, and the pollen season was delayed. Whereas this year spring came earlier and lasted longer. <strong><span class=\"citation-455\">(23) Right (A)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-455 citation-end-455\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span>.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5Qw\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> And another thing we should mention is ragweed as an example of a plant species moving into new areas as a result of climate change.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Yes, in the US it’s already the major allergen affecting millions of people in August and September. But we’re starting to see it grow in Europe for the first time, which is really worrying because it’s so allergenic. <strong><span class=\"citation-454\">(24) (A)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-454 citation-end-454\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span>. The problem with tree pollen is also worse in cities because there are so many hard surfaces around and the pollen doesn’t get absorbed so much, just stays in the air. <strong><span class=\"citation-453\">(25) (B)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-453 citation-end-453\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span>.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5gw\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Yeah, wasn’t the pollen shown to be three times higher in one city? I think so. So because of this many cities have started to ban the planting of certain types of trees.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> So shall we look at the different data tables for seasonal changes for pollen in Europe?</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Okay, but I think we should just focus on the trees and plants which we have the most data for: so that’s oak trees and birch trees and grass.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Yes, that makes it more manageable. Shall we go through the data for each country in detail and pick out anything interesting? Alright, so uh, starting with Austria. <span class=\"citation-452\">Well, here we’ve </span><strong><span class=\"citation-452\">(26) only got data for birch pollen (G)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-452 citation-end-452\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"6\"><!----></sup></span>. I wonder why there’s no data for oak or grass. Hmm, it would be interesting to compare with neighbouring countries.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5ww\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> True. The picture in France is unusual.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Yes. The pollen season starts earlier for both oak and birch, but it doesn’t start any earlier for grass. <strong><span class=\"citation-451\">(27) (B)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-451 citation-end-451\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"7\"><!----></sup></span>. I wonder why that is.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6Aw\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> In the Netherlands we’ve got complete data for all three plants. So what does it show? Hmm, grass and birch pollen are only starting a few days earlier, but oak pollen is starting much earlier, 18 days in fact. <strong><span class=\"citation-450\">(28) (A)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-450 citation-end-450\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"8\"><!----></sup></span>. Hmm, that’s unusual. There’s not such a big difference in other countries.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6Qw\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> No. Switzerland’s an interesting case. <span class=\"citation-449\">The pollen season starts here </span><strong><span class=\"citation-449\">(29) earlier than in the past for oak, birch and grass (D)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-449 citation-end-449\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"9\"><!----></sup></span>. Yeah, from 21 days to 14 days earlier.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6gw\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Yeah, the UK shows a different picture again. <span class=\"citation-448\">Yeah, here the problem is that wet summers have </span><strong><span class=\"citation-448\">(30) extended the grass pollen season (C)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-448 citation-end-448\"> from 5 weeks to 8 weeks, which is bad news for allergy sufferers<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"10\"><!----></sup></span>.<!----><!----><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6ww\"><!----><!----></button><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></h2>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Right, well, I think we should have another look.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b3653ded-5bc2-45dd-9c6e-6740c00e8628', 'a9c975b1-0bc6-46c8-80e5-8a6af07dbcc2', 'matching', 'Questions 26–30', '', '<p>What comment is made about the seasonal changes in pollen in each of the following European countries?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FIVE </strong>correct answers, A – G</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p>Australia  {information only available for birch pollen}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>France {changes identified for two pollen types only}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Netherlands  {greatest change recorded for oak pollen}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Switzerland  {earlier start dates for all pollen types}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>UK  {a longer season for grass pollen}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "greatest change recorded for oak pollen"}, {"optionText": "changes identified for two pollen types only"}, {"optionText": "a longer season for grass pollen"}, {"optionText": "earlier start dates for all pollen types"}, {"optionText": "significant change in start date of birch pollen"}, {"optionText": "little difference in start dates"}, {"optionText": "information only available for birch pollen"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a26d5ad1-90c4-4040-ae71-f0a89e77db31', 'ac3cc1cc-d520-421b-b036-c53a4b51d58b', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Saffron</strong></span></p>
<p>Saffron: a spice which comes from the crocus flower</p>
<p><strong>Cultivation and production</strong></p>
<p>Harvested in October</p>
<p>Number of stigmas needed for 50 grams: {14,000 | 14000}</p>
<p>Method of preservation: {drying}</p>
<p>Taste and aroma: like honey</p>
<p>Forms in which sold: as whole stigmas and as a {powder}</p>
<p><strong>Uses of saffron today</strong></p>
<p>To colour and flavour food in many countries especially for making {rice} dishes</p>
<p>In medicine</p>
<p>• as a drug in treatment of problems affecting the {eye}</p>
<p>• experiments with rats as protection from exposure to some types of {lights}</p>
<p><strong>History of saffron use</strong></p>
<p>Ancient Crete as a dye for {clothes}</p>
<p>Roman Empire</p>
<p>• in oil used for the production of {cosmetics}</p>
<p>• as a {perfume} in public baths</p>
<p>Persia (Iran) as a dye used in the making of {carpets}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2>(Section 4) Saffron</h2>\n<p>For my investigation into the history and uses of plant products, I have focused on the cultivation and production of saffron, an expensive bright yellow spice made from crocus flowers. Unlike most other species of crocus, the saffron crocus doesn’t flower in February or March, but in October, when it produces fragrant lilac coloured flowers, which are harvested at that time. During the harvest, the flower petals are discarded and only the stigmas, the three dark orange or red colored reproductive parts of the flower, are commercially used. One person must pick for almost 400 hours to produce just one kilo of saffron, and amazingly to produce just 50 grams it takes about <strong>(31) 14,000</strong> individual stigmas. No wonder the spice is so expensive.</p>\n<p>After this painstaking harvesting, and to preserve the intensive taste, smell and color of the product, the stigmas are subject to a process of <strong>(32) drying</strong> by which some 98% of their moisture content is removed. This makes it possible to keep saffron on the shelf to be used for many years. The highly prized spice is famous for the flavor and aroma it imparts, which are often compared to that of honey. Saffron is also prized for its rich golden color, which makes food look so tempting and indulgent. If you want to buy some of this fabled spice, you will find that saffron is either sold as whole stigmas or ground up as a <strong>(33) powder</strong>.</p>\n<p>Today, saffron is used in both eastern and western cuisines to add both color and flavor to an enormous range of recipes, though cooks would agree that it is most commonly added to recipes for the cooking of <strong>(34) rice</strong> because somehow it seems to complement such dishes perfectly. It is found to varying degrees in Italian, Spanish, Indian and Iranian food. Although food preparation is its most common present day use, medical research indicates that saffron may have important applications as a drug in the clinical treatment of a number of problems affecting the <strong>(35) eye</strong>. Patients given saffron in their regular diet seem to show remarkable signs of recovery from serious conditions. And although scientists are still unsure of exactly why, recent experiments with laboratory rats have shown saffron to be effective in protecting the animals from damage caused when they are exposed to potentially harmful <strong>(36) lights</strong>.</p>\n<p>Now I’d like to give a few examples of how saffron has been used since ancient times. Some of the earliest evidence of saffron cultivation comes from archaeological excavations dating back 4,000 years on the island of Crete, where paintings and other artifacts have been found indicating that women wore beautiful saffron colored <strong>(37) clothes</strong>. This is the earliest evidence of saffron being used as a dye. During the Roman Empire saffron oil was produced, which because of both its color and aroma was used to create <strong>(38) cosmetics</strong>, but only the wealthiest citizens could afford these. Another use of saffron was to be found in the public baths—there saffron was used as a <strong>(39) perfume</strong> to keep the places smelling fresh and aromatic. It is even said that the streets of Rome were strewn with saffron threads to greet Emperor Nero as an extravagant and sweet smelling gesture when he made a triumphal entrance into the city.</p>\n<p>Other parts of the ancient world use saffron extensively. One of the most well known examples was in Persia, which is modern day Iran, where saffron was a vital part of the process of manufacturing <strong>(40) carpets</strong> being used as a traditional dye along with other natural products like berries and minerals. To end my presentation, I’d like to read out a recipe written by a…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('26b037cd-6e11-4ff8-98af-627da382b3c9', '68bffba5-c133-4282-b7f3-fb5abf66416f', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Write ONE WORD ONLY for each answer.<br>BIOMASS FUEL</p>
<p>– Biomass is waste plant material, e.g. sawdust, straw.</p>
<p>– Biomass briquettes can be used as domestic or industrial fuel.</p>
<p>Benefits of biomass briquettes</p>
<p>– Financial: no {cost} for materials</p>
<p>– Convenience: clean and easy to handle and {store}</p>
<p>Production by machine</p>
<p>– Biomass is first converted to a {powder}Then other substances are added.</p>
<p>– The machine expels the mixture through {holes} of different shapes.</p>
<p>– NB Only a relatively small amount of {electricity| energy} is needed to operate the machine.</p>
<p>Production by hand</p>
<p>– Biomass is mixed with water and sticky material, e.g. {starch}, and then pressed into shape.</p>
<p>Current use</p>
<p>– Europe and the USA</p>
<p>+ Briquettes have been in use for some time for {agriculture}.</p>
<p>+ The use of briquettes made from wood has increased rapidly.</p>
<p>– India and China</p>
<p>+ 1990s: briquette manufacture began.</p>
<p>+ 2002: China had about 600 {factories}.</p>
<p>– Uganda</p>
<p>+ Customers are mainly public institutions or {businesses}.</p>
<p>Prospects for biomass fuel</p>
<p>– The {demand} is likely to increase.</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-58\" data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> <span class=\"citation-1008 citation-1009 citation-end-1009\">Good afternoon, everyone. In this course, we’ve been discussing the principles of sustainable development, and now we’re going to look at some of the ways in which these principles are being put into practice.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-59\" data-path-to-node=\"4\"><span class=\"citation-1006 citation-1007\">Today I’m </span><span class=\"citation-1004 citation-1005 citation-1006 citation-1007 citation-end-1007\">going to talk about the use of biomass. And for those of you who don’t know what biomas</span><span class=\"citation-1004 citation-1005 citation-1006 citation-end-1006\">s is, it’s plant material, usually</span><span class=\"citation-1004 citation-1005 citation-end-1005\"> agricultural waste such as sawdust or straw. And briquettes made out of biomass are used as fuel, either in the ho</span><span class=\"citation-1004 citation-end-1004\">me or in industry.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-60\" data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"citation-1003 citation-end-1003\">I’ll start with the benefits. Using briquettes has a financial benefit because they make use of waste products as raw material</span>s,<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">(Q31) so there isn’t any cost involved for that.</strong></span> Another advantage is convenience. Handling briquettes is cleaner than handling materials like wood or charcoal. Also, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"296\">(Q32) briquettes are less trouble to store because they are of uniform size and shape.</strong></span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-61\" data-path-to-node=\"6\">Right, let’s look briefly now at how these briquettes are made. There are two basic methods of manufacture. The first method uses machinery. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">(Q33) <span class=\"citation-1001 citation-1002\">At the initial stage, all the loose plant material is ground into a powder and then mixed with other materials.</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1001 citation-1002 citation-end-1002\"> Next, a machine compresses the biomass mixture, and that process raises the temperature and cau</span><span class=\"citation-1001 citation-end-1001\">ses it to m</span>elt. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"370\">(Q34) <span class=\"citation-1000\">The machine forces the biomass mixture out through rectangular or circular holes.</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1000 citation-end-1000\"> Then, as the pressure decreases, the mixture cools and becomes solid again, and that’s how the briquettes are formed.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-62\" data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-999 citation-end-999\">It’s important to point out that with this method</span>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"51\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q35) electricity (hoặc energy) </span><span class=\"citation-997 citation-998\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">is essential to operate the machinery</span>.</span></strong><span class=\"citation-997 citation-998 citation-end-998\"> And the exact amount you need depends on the type of biomass you use, but generally, the amount required is only 3% to 9% of the energy that’s produced by the briquettes when they are burnt.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-63\" data-path-to-node=\"8\"><span class=\"citation-995 citation-996 citation-end-996\">The second method</span><span class=\"citation-995\"> involves making briquettes by hand. This method is suitable when the biomass is mainly composed of material that doesn’t melt, like paper. </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"157\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><span class=\"citation-995 citation-end-995\">(</span>Q36) </span><span class=\"citation-994\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">The biomass is made into a paste by adding water and, in addition, something sticky such as starch</span>.</span></strong><span class=\"citation-994 citation-end-994\"> This mixture is then shaped using either a simple metal press or bare hands.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><span class=\"citation-993 citation-end-993\">So, where is biomass fuel used and how extensively? Well, it’s difficult to obtain detailed figures, but</span> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"105\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q37) </span><span class=\"citation-991 citation-992\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">it’s been used for several years in Europe and the USA, mainly for agriculture</span>.</span></strong><span class=\"citation-991 citation-992\"> And since 2000, there’s been a rapid increase in the production and use of briquettes </span><span class=\"citation-990 citation-991 citation-992 citation-end-992\">made out of wood waste. I can give you a ballpark figure: in 2010, a</span><span class=\"citation-990 citation-991 citation-end-991\">bout 5 million ton</span><span class=\"citation-990 citation-end-990\">s were used in Europe. Some of these had to be imported from the USA.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-65\" data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-989 citation-end-989\">Moving further east, both India and China have bee</span>n producing biomass briquettes since the 1990s. Detailed figures are hard to come by, but <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">(Q38) <span class=\"citation-987 citation-988\">in China in 2002, the number of factories producing biomass briquettes had increased to approximately 600</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-987 citation-988 citation-end-988\">, and production is still growing.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-66\" data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"citation-985 citation-986 citation-end-986\">I don’t have information about Africa in general, but I can give you an example of one company in Uganda which is producing briquettes. Most of the compa</span><span class=\"citation-985\">ny’s customers are public institutions like schools and universities that provide hot meals for their students. </span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"265\"><span class=\"citation-985 citation-end-985\">(</span>Q39) <span class=\"citation-984\">The other main users are businesses that need a source of heat for producing their products.</span></strong></span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_c21eee174a61121a-67\" data-path-to-node=\"12\"><span class=\"citation-983 citation-end-983\">Okay, well, how viable are biomass fuels like these in economic terms, and what is likely to happen in the future? Well, the answer depends partly on the price of the fuels that they replace, and that varies from place to plac</span>e. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"229\">(Q40) But in general, the demand for biomass fuels is almost certain to grow</strong></span>, and that can only benefit the environment. Let’s turn now to another facet of society…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f06832d4-2167-4213-a55a-44829a8754bf', 'b586bd90-cc84-4edc-bc13-332547edda0b', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p>Complete the notes below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Rooms to hire for parties</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>The Exchange Hotel</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Number of seated guests possible: 45</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Room on the {fifth} floor large, bright room with a good {view}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Cost £32 with buffet per person [minimum number of people: {35}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Available any {Saturday} In April</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The {Limerick} Hotel</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Large room [seats 75]</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the {business} area of the city</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Room on ground floor with a small {garden} for guests to use</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>cost : £36 with buffet per person</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Available: 13th and 20th April</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Booking information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Bookings held for a {week}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Final payment of {65} %required 10 days before booking</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Need to confirm guests and menu 5 days in advance</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>To book, phone {044298611} On Monday</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: ROOMS TO HIRE FOR PARTIES</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Good morning, The Function Company. Can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong>Woman:</strong> Hi. A friend told me that you can arrange rooms for hire for parties and things like that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> That''s right. We have about ten hotels on our list and we hire out function rooms on their behalf. Are you having a party?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>Yes, it''s for my birthday—my 21st.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. First of all, can you tell me how many people you''re inviting?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> I''m not sure yet. It depends on the cost.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. Well, the Exchange Hotel might be a good choice for you. They have a room which will seat up to 45 and will take 65 people standing. Are you going to have a meal or just a buffet?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> Uh, I think a buffet. It doesn''t have to be a sit-down meal. I don''t know the Exchange Hotel. Can you tell me a bit more about it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Well, it was built about 150 years ago. We regularly arrange parties there. They have a room for hire on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">(Q1) fifth</strong></span> floor. It''s not the most central hotel, but it''s very easy for people to find. It''s very popular for wedding parties, so I''ll have to check if it''s available.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> Okay. Is the room nice? Have you seen it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> I have. It''s quite big and very light, but the best thing is that it has a wonderful <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">(Q2) view</strong></span>. On a fine evening, you can see for miles.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> Oh, sounds good. How much is it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> It''s £32 a head. That includes the hire of the room and the standard buffet, but not drinks. And you have to have at least <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">(Q3) 35</strong></span> guests.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>Well, that won''t be a problem. We''re likely to be more than that. Can you tell me when it''s available?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> I can check that for you. Which dates are you looking at?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>Uh, ideally the middle to end of April, weekends.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Let me see... um, they can do any <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">(Q4) Saturday</strong></span> in April, but not Fridays or Sundays.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> Okay. But if I want something bigger, what would you recommend?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> There''s the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">(Q5) Limerick</strong></span> Hotel.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>How do you spell that? Oh, I''m taking notes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> It''s L-I-M-E-R-I-C-K. There''s a large room there which seats up to 75 people, or there''s room for 125 standing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> Oh, I expect we''ll be standing. Where is it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> It''s in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">(Q6) business</strong></span> district, so public transport''s good. It''s got a large car park too. Though the room''s on the ground floor and it''s recently been refurbished.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman: </strong>Is there a garden we could use if we''re on the ground floor?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> There''s a small <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">(Q7) garden</strong></span> that would be available.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman: </strong>Oh, sounds nice, especially if it''s a warm evening. And the cost?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> The buffet is £36 per person. Shall I check availability in April for you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>Yes, please.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay, you said weekends, didn''t you? Yes... No Fridays again. And it''s not free on the first Saturday, that''s the 6th, but it''s free on the 13th and 20th.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">BOOKING INFORMATION (Questions 8–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>I think the first hotel looks best for me, but I need two or three days to think about it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. Well, if I take your booking today, I can hold it for a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">(Q8) week</strong></span>. So if you want to change your mind or have a look at other possible hotels, we can do that. To confirm the booking, I then need a deposit of 35%. You pay the other <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"246\">(Q9) 65%</strong></span> 10 days before the party.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>Okay. And when do I have to confirm numbers?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> The number of guests needs to be confirmed five days before the party, and you also have to decide which menu you want then.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong> That sounds okay. I''ll ring you on Monday. Is this your direct line? 368207.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> I''ll be out of the office on Monday, but you can call me on my <strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> mobile phone </span></strong>on <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(Q10) </strong><strong>04429 8611.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">Woman:</strong>Alright, I''ve got all that. I''ll ring you back later. Thanks</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager: </strong>bye then.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('89cbc0d1-562b-4fbd-bd14-fd83257cf40d', 'ee3f422e-fa1f-43d1-82bb-b39b5817fe7c', 'radio', 'Questions 36 - 40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A the extreme conditions that Polar explorers have to face."}, {"content": "B the unusual quality of the beauty of Polar regions."}, {"content": "C the vital importance of preserving the Arctic environment."}, {"content": "D the personal qualities required of an explorer in Arctic conditions."}], "question": "In paragraph E, the writer describes different types of ice in order to illustrate"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A He expresses a very limited range of ideas."}, {"content": "B He is only willing to discuss things he is familiar with."}, {"content": "C He uses words and phrases that he has previously memorised."}, {"content": "D He is only fluent when talking about naval matters."}], "question": "What is said about the way Franklin communicates?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A They no longer notice his slowness."}, {"content": "B They start to copy his approach to work."}, {"content": "C They begin to recognise his efforts to overcome his problems."}, {"content": "D They eventually appreciate his good qualities."}], "question": "How does the attitude of the other sailors change towards Franklin?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A text from a wide variety of sources."}, {"content": "B short, disconnected pieces of text."}, {"content": "C descriptions of the Arctic landscape."}, {"content": "D information about other explorers like Franklin."}], "question": "The chapters of The Discovery of Slowness which describe Franklin''s early years contain"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A it reflects many people''s concern about one aspect of modern life."}, {"content": "B it offers achievable solutions to many of the problems of today."}, {"content": "C it tells the story of someone''s triumph over personal problems."}, {"content": "D it shows how life in the past was less pressured than it is now."}], "question": "The Discovery of Slowness has achieved widespread popularity because"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36 In paragraph E, the writer describes different types of ice in order to illustrate</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D. the personal qualities required of an explorer in Arctic conditions.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn E,</span><span class=\"\"> câu cuối:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“Ice demands a corresponding patience from those who venture onto it. The explorers who have thrived… haven’t usually lacked unusual <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">self-possession</strong>, a considerable <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">capacity for boredom</strong>, and a talent for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"239\">uncomplaining endurance of suffering</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả mô tả sự hình thành chậm chạp của băng để nhấn mạnh rằng môi trường này đòi hỏi những phẩm chất cá nhân tương ứng (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">personal qualities</strong><span class=\"\">) như sự điềm tĩnh,</span><span class=\"\"> khả năng chịu đựng sự buồn chán và gian khổ.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37 What is said about the way Franklin communicates?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C. He uses words and phrases that he has previously memorised.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn F,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 2:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“He <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">learns by heart</strong> “entire fleets of words and batteries of responses,” and speaks a languid, bric-a-brac language.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Cụm từ “learns by heart” đồng nghĩa với “memorised” (học thuộc lòng).</span><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc cho biết vì Franklin không thể nói trôi chảy,</span><span class=\"\"> ông phải học thuộc lòng các tập hợp từ và câu trả lời sẵn có để giao tiếp.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38 How does the attitude of the other sailors change towards Franklin?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D. They eventually appreciate his good qualities.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn F,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 5-8:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“In the Navy, his method… initially <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">provokes mockery</strong> from his fellow sailors. But Franklin persists… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">gradually earns the respect</strong> of those around him.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> * Thái độ ban đầu:</span><span class=\"\"> Chế nhạo (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">mockery</strong><span class=\"\">).</span></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,0,0\"><span class=\"\">Thái độ sau đó:</span><span class=\"\"> Dần có được sự tôn trọng (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">earns the respect</strong><span class=\"\">).</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,1,0\"><span class=\"\">Sự tôn trọng chính là việc họ bắt đầu trân trọng (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">appreciate</strong><span class=\"\">) những phẩm chất của ông.</span><span class=\"\"> (Lưu ý:</span><span class=\"\"> Bài không nói họ “copy” – sao chép cách làm của ông,</span><span class=\"\"> nên không chọn B).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39 The chapters of The Discovery of Slowness which describe Franklin’s early years contain</strong></p>\n<ul class=\"animating\" data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li class=\"animating\">\n<p class=\"animating\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B. short, disconnected pieces of text.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"animating\">\n<p class=\"animating\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn G,</span> câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The chapters describing Franklin’s early years are a <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">medley of separate fragments</strong>, rhetorical questions, associative jumps…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “separate fragments” (những mảnh vụn tách biệt) tương ứng với “disconnected pieces of text” (những đoạn văn bản rời rạc).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40 The Discovery of Slowness has achieved widespread popularity because</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A. it reflects many people’s concern about one aspect of modern life.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn H, câu 4: <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The various groups that have taken the novel up have one thing in common: a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">dislike of the high-speed culture of Postmodernity</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cuốn sách nổi tiếng vì nó phản ánh sự không hài lòng của nhiều người đối với văn hóa tốc độ cao của đời sống hiện đại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">modern life</strong>), điều mà họ đang lo lắng hoặc phản đối.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('33e1550b-c490-4a08-ad97-247934ba27c4', 'b2554d64-629e-4aa2-8c14-2da421d2141b', 'matrix', 'Questions 14-19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven sections, A-G.</p>
<p>Which section contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A-G, to boxes 14-19.</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a contrast between the ways young players gain experience of playing different positions", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "examples outside sport of greater emphasis on individual safety", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a description of methods of selection for leadership on soccer teams", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "details of urban changes that discourage street soccer", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a mention of the lesson that failure teaches street soccer players", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "an explanation of why youth soccer emphasises the need for coaches", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>14. a contrast between the ways young players gain experience of playing different positions</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: E</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “One of the basic ideas of street soccer is that young players are assigned a particular role… Such an assignment runs counter to the idea of youth soccer that every child needs to learn every position…“<br />\nGiải thích: Đoạn E so sánh sự khác biệt trong việc phân công vai trò (vị trí) giữa hai loại hình bóng đá (cụ thể hóa cách thức nhận kinh nghiệm vị trí).<br />\n<strong>15. examples outside sport of greater emphasis on individual safety</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: C</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng: </strong>(Đoạn C) “Like the 1960s consumer movement which brought seat belts and airbags to cars, the (youth) soccer movement felt like it could create a set of … regulations that would protect both the child’s body and mind from damage.“<br />\nGiải thích: Tác giả dùng dây an toàn và túi khí ô tô làm ví dụ về sự chú trọng an toàn cá nhân ngoài lĩnh vực thể thao.<br />\n<strong>16. a description of methods of selection for leadership on soccer teams</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: F</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng: </strong>(Đoạn F) “Positions of responsibility are earned through competition within the team… In youth soccer, however, with its overly democratic values, youngsters are guaranteed their time in the spotlight.“<br />\nGiải thích: Đoạn F mô tả cách thức đạt được vị trí có trách nhiệm (leadership) trong cả hai loại hình bóng đá (bằng cạnh tranh trong street soccer và bằng luân phiên/dân chủ quá mức trong youth soccer).<br />\n<strong>17. details of urban changes that discourage street soccer</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: B</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng: </strong>(Đoạn B) “Congested traffic now dominates where games were once played. Parks and open fields are used as hangouts… Add to this the requirement in many localities for official permits…”<br />\nGiải thích: Đoạn B chi tiết hóa các yếu tố thay đổi môi trường đô thị (giao thông, thiếu không gian, yêu cầu giấy phép) khiến bóng đá đường phố khó thực hiện.<br />\n<strong>18. a mention of the lesson that failure teaches street soccer players</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: G</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng: </strong>(Đoạn G) “Losing a game is a common experience and players learn early on how to handle this. As a result… they acquire resilience.”<br />\nGiải thích: Thất bại (Losing a game) dạy cho người chơi street soccer bài học về sự kiên cường (resilience).<br />\n<strong>19. an explanation of why youth soccer emphasises the need for coaches</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: D</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng: </strong>(Đoạn D) “They argue that children need to be taught by experts… This need to get ahead brings with it a fear of falling behind that only expert instruction can prevent.”<br />\nGiải thích: Nhu cầu được dạy bởi chuyên gia (coaches/experts) xuất phát từ nỗi sợ bị tụt lại phía sau.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6f66807e-ff7f-4179-a305-92f682009509', '18318151-caed-4803-a0d4-9381160a306a', 'checkbox', 'Questions 27–28', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>decisions do the students reach about the subject matter of their assignment?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. They will keep the assessment criteria in mind.", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. They will limit the scale of their investigation.", "correct": true}, {"option": "C. They will select countries from all over the world.", "correct": false}, {"option": "D. They will collect data about two groups of countries.", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. They will find figures for wind and nuclear power.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b759cb48-9f30-4d37-b6c1-c78076e78aeb', 'b2554d64-629e-4aa2-8c14-2da421d2141b', 'checkbox', 'Questions 20-21', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct answers.</p>
<p>The list below gives some possible reasons for the popularity of street soccer.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> of these reasons are mentioned by the writer of the text?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "Many famous soccer players got their start in street soccer.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Young people can begin playing street soccer at a very early age.", "correct": false}, {"option": "You do not need elaborate facilities to play street soccer.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Inexperienced street soccer players are not criticised for mistakes.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Street soccer teams can have varying numbers of players.", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>20-21. Which TWO of these reasons are mentioned by the writer of the text? (Lý do Street Soccer phổ biến)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: C (You do not need elaborate facilities to play street soccer.) và E (Street soccer teams can have varying numbers of players.)</strong><br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng cho C:</strong> (Đoạn A) “…<strong>no large space is needed</strong>, and goal posts, corner markers, and marked lines… <strong>are typically absent</strong>…” (Không cần cơ sở vật chất phức tạp).<br />\n<strong>Dẫn chứng cho E:</strong> (Đoạn A) “…does not necessarily require standard 11-a-side teams or <strong>fixed playing positions</strong>.” (Số lượng đội có thể thay đổi, không cần đội cố định 11 người).</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('31df0848-2b06-4123-b089-25b33f36782e', 'b67a0d01-5a34-42ad-8682-c71648f11530', 'radio', 'Questions 18-20', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A the Science Centre."}, {"option_text": "B the Natural History Museum"}, {"option_text": "C the Maritime Museum."}], "question": "For families, the tour guide recommends"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A two adults and one child."}, {"option_text": "B one adult and two children."}, {"option_text": "C two adults and two children."}], "question": "You can buy a family ticket for a minimum of"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A two days."}, {"option_text": "B three days"}, {"option_text": "C one week."}], "question": "The Culture Pass is valid for"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b68dfa1d-5370-48c7-bee7-d8eac3a3261a', 'f6a0c121-1148-4d42-aa96-35ee338c7f47', 'radio', 'Questions 21-25', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. a history textbook"}, {"option_text": " B. an academic article"}, {"option_text": "C. a lecture handout"}], "question": "What source did Mike use for his definition?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the permanent preservation of recordings"}, {"option_text": "B. an increase in student interest"}, {"option_text": "C. wide access to the interviews by the public"}], "question": "According to Mike and his tutor, what is the most important contribution of the intern to oral history?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. he is football fan"}, {"option_text": "B. his father loves football."}, {"option_text": "C. his friends encouraged him"}], "question": "Mikes says he chose his particular topic because"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. doing research in the local newspaper archives"}, {"option_text": "B. speaking to the team manager"}, {"option_text": "C. looking at materials in the local library"}], "question": "What does Mike say was his best source of information about the team?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. on the internet"}, {"option_text": "B. in the team records"}, {"option_text": "C. in the phone book"}], "question": "How did Mike find the former players he has arranged to interview?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 3: ORAL HISTORY PROJECT</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Thanks Mike for dropping by. I''ve read the proposal for your project, which is an oral history of the local football team, particularly the time around 1983 when they won the league championship. But first, how do you define oral history?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Well, in fact, I use the definition you gave us last year in our research methodology class. <strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"99\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q21) I found the handout in my file</span>.</strong> The definition says that oral histories are planned interviews or conversations about some aspect of the past which is considered historically or socially important. The interviews are with people who took part in whatever it''s about, so there''ll be a record which historians can use later for all those academic articles they write. And although history textbooks are mostly about famous people and important events, oral history can be about ordinary people doing ordinary things.Oral history really seems to have started in the States.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong>  You''re right. In fact, the first modern oral history interviews were done by a historian in New York. By that time, audio technology had improved so much that it was fairly easy to record those interviews. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong>  I was also interested in how the internet has contributed to oral history studies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, it means that lots of people can access the material and that''s great. Also, the interactive nature of the better websites means that more students get interested in oral history.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> But from what I''ve read, the real contribution of the internet is that <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"77\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q22) the recording of the interviews will be preserved forever</span>.</strong> In the old days, the tapes would just wear out and after some years you couldn''t really use them, but not now.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> You''re right, of course. Anyhow, let''s move on to the subject of your project. Why did you decide to study a sports team?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Well actually, I don''t even like football very much and some of my friends think I''m crazy to go for that subject. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">(Q23) But my dad is a huge fan</strong> </span>and he might be able to help me.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Hmm, and how did you find out background about the team? You talked to the team manager, I assume?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Yes, I did manage to track him down. <strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"43\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q24) And I looked at all the old news stories about the team in the town newspaper office. That was where I got the most helpful information</span>.</strong> I had high hopes that the local library would have lots of stuff, but they don''t keep many records for more than 10 years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> I know that you managed to locate 10 of the original 18 members of the team using an old-fashioned method, didn''t you? Not a website or anything. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(Q25) Just the telephone directory. </strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong>Yes, I didn''t even need to use the local team''s records.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PROJECT IMPROVEMENTS (Questions 26–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> OK, now I''ve read your proposal carefully. Overall, your plans seem excellent, but I want to discuss how you might improve them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Great.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> I''ve read through the list of questions you''ve drafted. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">(Q26) I felt most of them are rather complex (G)</strong></span> to be processed as oral questions. You don''t have too many, which is good, but you should try to do something about that problem.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Right, I''ll work on them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And the time you''ve allotted for each interview... actually, I think you may have scheduled <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">(Q27) too much time (D - too long)</strong></span> for each. You want them to be tight, not going on and on. That makes for better results.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> I can change the schedule. One thing I''m nervous about is the recording equipment I use. I''ve got an old recorder. It runs without making too much noise and it isn''t complicated, but it <strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"192\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q28) sometimes just doesn''t seem to work (A - too unreliable)</span>.</strong> It stopped during an interview I tried out with my dad.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Well, the important thing is just be ready if anything happens. Uh, take some spare batteries or even an extra recorder.  Now, I''m a little concerned with the subjects you''ve chosen to cover. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">(Q29) The topics seem quite general, not very specific (H - too vague)</strong></span>. For example, \"Why did they like playing for this team?\". You need to talk about more exact things and feelings.That way your results will be more valuable.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> I''ll try to refine them. And the plan for my report seems to be just to report back more or less what the players say... <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">(Q30) what happened when, what they each did and so on (F - too factual).</strong></span>But I''m not sure about that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, although your outline seems long enough, change it to indicate that you plan to include your own evaluation of the data you get from your interviewees. Anyhow, best of luck on your project.I look forward to seeing the results.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong>Mike:</strong> Thanks for your help!</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('411c0b64-903b-461b-81f0-919ee497f1b0', '4660f8b6-d7b2-4449-b05f-9af0da34722f', 'radio', 'Questions 21-26', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. design development from 1800s"}, {"content": "B. design development and social advancement"}, {"content": "C. design development and art movement"}], "question": "Mona''s presentation topic is about"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. She is afraid of her tutor''s response"}, {"content": "B. She wants to give a complete talk."}, {"content": "C. She thinks it would be too simple."}], "question": "Mona doesn''t want to just talk about one topic because"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. Very detailed"}, {"content": "B. Too old"}, {"content": "C. Too broad"}], "question": "What does Ted say about Mona''s topic?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. They have improved work efficiency."}, {"content": "B. They have influenced traditional media."}, {"content": "C. They have changed people''s sense of style."}], "question": "What is Mona''s viewpoint on computers?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. It''s important for architecture"}, {"content": "B. It saves a lot of effort"}, {"content": "C. He admires it in arts"}], "question": "Why does Ted think of ''purism''?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. meet one of his friends"}, {"content": "B. read more books"}, {"content": "C. visit a museum"}], "question": "What does Ted suggest Mona"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">SECTION 3</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Ted, you’ve looked at my presentation haven’t you? What do you think of it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> Hey Mona, yes I have. Before giving you some advice, I have a question. Why didn’t you write about the development of design and its influence or connection with social advancement or even art movement? In my opinion, this direction would have more significance.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Actually I just want to focus on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">(21) history of design. I’m particularly interested in its history from the 1800s (A)</strong></span>, that’s why I wrote about it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> I see, it could save some effort.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Not really. I’ve covered different areas of design, such as building, clothing and products. It’s a lot of work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> Right. Is it because you want to give a comprehensive talk?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> To be honest, I was<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"26\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(22)</span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">w</span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">orried about my teacher’s reaction (A)</span></strong></span> if I only talk about one area. She might think I’ve been lazy.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> You know what, even though it’s okay to talk about different aspects, I think the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">(23) topic is too broad (C)</strong></span>. It would be hard for the listeners to focus on any specific area.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Um… you are right. I only have about 45 minutes for the talk. Maybe I should narrow the range.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> That would be much better. And you can use computer technology to assist you in your presentation, like using the CAD or other computer software.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> I’m not sure. Although computer technology can improve the visual effects of my presentation, I’d rather use the traditional way. Since I’m talking about the history of design, I guess <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"191\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(24) traditional media is more affected by computers (B)</span></strong> rather than designing industry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> That makes sense. You could do it your own way. As for the content, you mentioned purism and you said it can save people’s effort. I don’t really agree with that. I think it’s not really easy to achieve. On the other hand, I do think it’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"244\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(25) important to apply this concept in architecture (A)</span></strong>. I mean, the building should look simple and elegant.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> That’s a good point Ted. What do you think I should do to further improve my talk?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> Well, I think you have read enough books about it, so it’s not the theories that you lack. Why don’t you <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"110\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(26)</span> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">visit the Design Museum (C)</span></strong> in the north of the city? One of my friends went there last month and he said it was worth it. I’m sure it can give you some inspiration.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"17\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> How do you usually prepare for a presentation? You have done it many times, right?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> You can say that. When I prepare for a presentation, I would first try to come up with an <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"95\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(27) introduction (D)</span></strong>, telling the audience what my topic is. It’s very important to grasp people’s attention and let them know what you want to talk about.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Okay, I think so. A good beginning can mean everything.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> Exactly. Maybe you could use a story to start. Step 2, I would <strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"68\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(28) research (G)</span></strong> deeper into the topic and give the audience something new.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Yeah, that’s what I’ve been working on. I always try to look for more related information online. I want them to learn something from my presentation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> Since you work so hard, they will like it. I noticed that you use a lot of pictures in your slides. What I would do is put a <strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"130\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(29) statement (E)</span></strong> under each picture, so the audience would know what exactly the pictures are about.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> I just thought it would be more impressive to use only pictures. Alright, I will add that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> In the next step, you should try illustrating slide by slide. Each slide should only contain one thought or idea, so all of these thoughts will link together in your illustration. This step would need a lot of practice.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> Exactly, a lot of practice is needed before you stand in front of the real audience.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> There’s one final step you should not forget. I suggest you prepare some <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"78\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(30) </span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">text handouts (A)</span></strong> </span>with important details.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> What are they for?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> The audience can reflect on what you talk about in and after your presentation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mona:</strong> I’ve never thought about that. Thank you so much Ted. You’re a great help.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ted:</strong> No problem Mona.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a4b51dd4-8186-4303-939e-cc1e2a9d649e', '4660f8b6-d7b2-4449-b05f-9af0da34722f', 'matching', 'Questions 27-30', NULL, '<p>According to Ted, what is the right way to make a successful presentation?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>letters from the box and write the correct letter, A-F, next to questions 27-30.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p>Step 1. Write {D an introduction}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Step 2. {G research} further on the topic</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Step 3. Put a {E statement} for every picture and support it</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Step 4. every slide illustrates a thought, all the thoughts link together</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Step 5. Write {A text handouts}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A text handouts"}, {"optionText": "B questions"}, {"optionText": "C an outline"}, {"optionText": "D an introduction"}, {"optionText": "E statement"}, {"optionText": "F explain"}, {"optionText": "G research"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5107ddeb-c247-40f7-8fa8-7b96e73268d8', '26761b07-daf8-4acf-b2cd-ea49e50fb7f3', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p data-start="204" data-end="373">Choose<strong data-start="204" data-end="212"> TRUE</strong> – if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-start="262" data-end="271">FALSE</strong> – if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-start="321" data-end="334">NOT GIVEN</strong> – if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It was Hazel Platt who found people to join the first Rockdale Dramatic Class."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The actors adapted the hall in the Carlton School of Arts to make it suitable for their first production."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In 1953, plays were performed in a variety of venues."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The group wanted to use the Carlton School of Arts on a temporary basis."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Improvements to the Guild Theatre had been completed when the Mayor opened the building."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The performance of Australian plays is in response to public demand."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The company produces plays for a total of five weeks each year."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. It was Hazel Plant who found people to join the first Rockdale Dramatic Class. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A small group of young people got together and decided to form the Rockdale Dramatic Class…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói một nhóm người trẻ tự tập hợp lại để thành lập nhóm. Không có ai tên là Hazel Plant tìm người tham gia (trong bài chỉ nhắc đến đạo diễn Hal Pannell nhưng là do nhóm đi tìm và bổ nhiệm).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. The actors adapted the hall in the Carlton School of Arts to make it suitable for their first production. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The performers built their own scenery, made a stage out of tables, and draped material… to create a dressing space.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các diễn viên đã tự dựng cảnh trí, dùng bàn làm sân khấu và treo vải làm phòng thay đồ, tức là họ đã tự điều chỉnh (adapted) hội trường để biểu diễn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. In 1953, plays were performed in a variety of venues. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…productions were taken to local halls throughout Sydney as their popularity increased.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Local halls throughout Sydney” (các hội trường địa phương khắp Sydney) chính là “a variety of venues” (nhiều địa điểm khác nhau).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. The group wanted to use the Carlton School of Arts on a temporary basis. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…after the group’s failed attempt at making the Carlton School of Arts their permanent base.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhóm đã cố gắng biến nơi này thành trụ sở vĩnh viễn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">permanent base</strong>) nhưng thất bại, trái ngược với ý muốn sử dụng tạm thời (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">temporary</strong>) trong câu hỏi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Improvements to the Guild Theatre had been completed when the Mayor opened the building. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The Guild Theatre was officially opened… After this, further plays… continued… along with continued renovations and improvements…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau khi Thị trưởng khai trương, việc cải tạo và nâng cấp vẫn tiếp tục diễn ra (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">continued</strong>), nghĩa là lúc khai trương thì các công đoạn này chưa hoàn thành xong.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. The performance of Australian plays is in response to public demand. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In recent years, Australian plays have been included…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ xác nhận có diễn các vở kịch của Úc, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">không đề cập lý do</strong> có phải là do yêu cầu của công chúng (public demand) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. The company produces plays for a total of five weeks each year. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…four to five seasons each year, each season having sixteen performances over five weeks.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mỗi mùa kéo dài 5 tuần, mà một năm có tận 4-5 mùa. Như vậy tổng thời gian biểu diễn trong năm phải là 20-25 tuần, không phải chỉ có 5 tuần. Câu này đưa ra thông tin sai lệch về tổng thời gian nên là <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"211\">False</strong> hoặc bài đọc không nêu con số tổng nên là <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"259\">Not Given</strong> (Tùy logic đề, nhưng ở đây thông tin 5 tuần chỉ là thời gian của 1 mùa).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b628cb3b-e7e5-41b3-bddd-befec89c958d', '26761b07-daf8-4acf-b2cd-ea49e50fb7f3', 'matrix', 'Questions 8–14', '', '<p data-start="201" data-end="271">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="227" data-end="234">A–H</strong>, in boxes 8–14 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="273" data-end="318"><strong data-start="273" data-end="279">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It provides you with a lot of detail about accommodation.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "It has a feature enabling travellers to write their own opinions.", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "It is just as effective as the printed version.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "It shows an awareness of possible problems travellers might have.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It helps you to search for information elsewhere on the internet.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Wider access to booking on the website would be an improvement.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "There is a lack of information on how to get to places.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. It provides you with a lot of detail about accommodation. — {G} – visitbritain.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Visit Britain offers a huge choice of places to stay… all the information is <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">comprehensive enough</strong> to give a real taste of what to expect.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Places to stay” chính là accommodation (chỗ ở). Thông tin “comprehensive” (toàn diện/chi tiết) khớp với “a lot of detail”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. It has a feature enabling travellers to write their own opinions. — {H} – roughguides.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Share your own thoughts</strong> in the Community and Journals sections…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc “chia sẻ suy nghĩ cá nhân” (share your own thoughts) chính là tính năng cho phép khách du lịch viết ý kiến riêng (write their own opinions).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. It is just as effective as the printed version. — {E} – fodors.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Fodor’s ever-reliable series of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">guide books</strong> translates well to the internet and is <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">equally successful</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Guide books” là phiên bản in (printed version). Cụm “equally successful” (thành công tương đương) khớp với “just as effective”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. It shows an awareness of possible problems travellers might have. — {A} – artoftravel.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…doesn’t ignore the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">difficulties</strong> of independent travel.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc “không phớt lờ những khó khăn” (doesn’t ignore difficulties) cho thấy website có sự nhận thức (awareness) về các vấn đề mà du khách có thể gặp phải.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. It helps you to search for information elsewhere on the internet. — {F} – lonelyplanet.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…there are numerous <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">links to other websites</strong> if you want to find out more.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các đường link dẫn đến các trang web khác chính là công cụ giúp người dùng tìm kiếm thông tin ở những nơi khác trên internet (elsewhere on the internet).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Wider access to booking on the website would be an improvement. — {G} – visitbritain.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Online reservations are only available for a few… and a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">more extensive service</strong> would make the site <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">even better</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết cho rằng nếu dịch vụ đặt phòng (reservations) rộng rãi hơn (more extensive) thì trang web sẽ tốt hơn (even better/improvement).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. There is a lack of information on how to get to places. — {B} – https://www.google.com/search?q=beachwizard.com</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">No directions</strong> to these beaches are included, which could make things difficult…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “No directions” (không có chỉ đường) chính là sự thiếu hụt thông tin về cách đi đến các địa điểm (how to get to places).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1c880ae5-c25a-4d98-9525-2fe1d7776104', '10d8ae29-eb1c-4665-bf15-27b7fc67fc74', 'fillup', 'Questions 15–21', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15–21 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Dress Code in the U.K.</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Modern UK dress code legislation reflects the idea that it is unacceptable to demand that a female dresses in a {skirt}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In addition to clothing, {long hair} may be a problem where it could catch in work equipment.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Sometimes employers may insist that certain clothing is worn to fit with their {uniform}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>It is wise to make sure that {visible tattoos} are permitted by your employer if you intend to get one.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The Human Rights Act does not offer any {protection} for the wearing of certain items purely for religious purposes.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Where domestic employees live {on site}, they can argue that limits on what they wear are unfair.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In certain cases, {compensation} may be obtained if discrimination can be proved.</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Modern UK dress code legislation reflects the idea that it is unacceptable to demand that a female dresses in a {skirt}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is wrong to insist that a woman wears a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">skirt</strong>, or indeed a man wears trousers.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Luật pháp hiện đại coi trọng sự bình đẳng. Việc bắt buộc phụ nữ mặc váy (skirt) là không đúng (wrong/unacceptable).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. In addition to clothing, {long hair} may be a problem where it could catch in work equipment.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“There could be a case for keeping <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">long hair</strong> away from dangerous machinery out of prudence.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Work equipment” (thiết bị làm việc) tương ứng với “machinery” (máy móc). Mái tóc dài có thể gây nguy hiểm nếu bị cuốn vào máy.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Sometimes employers may insist that certain clothing is worn to fit with their {uniform}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Some employers will provide you with a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">uniform</strong> so that health and safety regulations are adhered to. Other employers will issue a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"142\">uniform</strong> as part of a corporate image.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Fit with” (phù hợp với) tương ứng với việc mặc để tuân thủ quy định hoặc xây dựng hình ảnh tập thể thông qua đồng phục (uniform).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. It is wise to make sure that {visible tattoos} are permitted by your employer if you intend to get one.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Visible tattoos</strong> could prove offensive to some clients… Therefore you should check with your boss before you have one done.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Check with your boss” (hỏi ý kiến sếp) đồng nghĩa với “make sure they are permitted”. Bạn nên làm việc này trước khi đi xăm (intend to get one).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. The Human Rights Act does not offer any {protection} for the wearing of certain items purely for religious purposes.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“However, employees should be aware that this gives no <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">protection</strong> for clothing for religious reasons.”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù Đạo luật Nhân quyền cho phép tự do tôn giáo, nhưng nó không trực tiếp bảo vệ (protection) việc mặc trang phục vì lý do tôn giáo thuần túy (trừ khi liên quan đến sắc tộc).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Where domestic employees live {on site}, they can argue that limits on what they wear are unfair.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“However, this can cause issues when an employee lives <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">on site</strong> (oil platforms, hospitals, domestic staff).”</em> (Đoạn 6)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những nhân viên giúp việc gia đình (domestic staff) sống tại nơi làm việc (on site) thường cảm thấy các hạn chế về trang phục làm ảnh hưởng đến đời sống riêng tư của họ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. In certain cases, {compensation} may be obtained if discrimination can be proved.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you feel that you are being discriminated against… then you may be eligible for <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">compensation</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 7)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Eligible for” (có đủ điều kiện nhận) tương ứng với “may be obtained”. Nếu chứng minh được bị phân biệt đối xử, người lao động có thể nhận được tiền bồi thường.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('568164df-4a78-4aa9-a291-299fd1d3e44f', '10d8ae29-eb1c-4665-bf15-27b7fc67fc74', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–27', '<p>Complete the flow-chart below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 22–27 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">What to do if you know of some wrongdoing at work</span></strong></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9989%; height: 22.832px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8607%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 22.832px;">
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>You have a {duty} to tell the relevant people if you know of any wrongdoing at work.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9989%; height: 22.832px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8607%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 22.832px;">
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>Notify the Company so that the high standards of the Company are maintained.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9989%; height: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8607%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>Have a confidential discussion with the Head of the HR Department if you have {doubts} about informing the Company.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9631%; height: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8569%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>If you can’t inform the Company for some reason, inform the relevant {external body}.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9631%; height: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8569%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>The Company conducts {preliminary enquiries} to decide what kind of investigation is appropriate.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9631%; height: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8569%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>The matter is investigated {internally} or referred to the police or lawyers.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9631%; height: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8569%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p>As long as there is no legal issue involved, the Company will ensure you know what’s happening and what the {outcome} is.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;">🔽</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9631%; height: 22.832px; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8569%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 22.832px;">
<td style="padding: 1px;">
<p data-start="1037" data-end="1154">If you purposely invent untrue statements, you could lose your job or disciplinary action might be taken against you.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: center;"> </p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. You have a {duty} to tell the relevant people if you know of any wrongdoing at work.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is your <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">duty</strong> to report any situation or matter which you reasonably believe might show that… wrongdoing… has occurred…”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu đầu tiên của bài khẳng định việc báo cáo sai phạm là nghĩa vụ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">duty</strong>) của nhân viên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Have a confidential discussion with the Head of the HR Department if you have {doubts} about informing the Company.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Where there are any <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">doubts</strong> in your mind as to whether to notify the Company, you are encouraged to discuss any matter with the Human Resources Manager…”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nếu bạn có những nghi ngờ hoặc thắc mắc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">doubts</strong>) về việc có nên báo cáo hay không, bạn nên thảo luận với Quản lý nhân sự (Head of HR).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. If you can’t inform the Company for some reason, inform the relevant {external body}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“You must notify an appropriate <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">external body</strong> in cases where notifying the Company is not possible…”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi không thể báo cáo nội bộ công ty, bước tiếp theo là thông báo cho một cơ quan bên ngoài (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">external body</strong>) phù hợp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. The Company conducts {preliminary enquiries} to decide what kind of investigation is appropriate.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the Company will normally make <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">preliminary enquiries</strong> to determine whether a full investigation is needed.”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trước khi điều tra chính thức, công ty sẽ tiến hành các bước tìm hiểu sơ bộ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">preliminary enquiries</strong>) để xem xét mức độ cần thiết của cuộc điều tra.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. The matter is investigated {internally} or referred to the police or lawyers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the matter will either be examined <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">internally</strong>, or referred to our lawyers or the police.”</em> (Đoạn 6)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Examined internally” đồng nghĩa với việc được điều tra nội bộ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">investigated internally</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. As long as there is no legal issue involved, the Company will ensure you know what’s happening and what the {outcome} is.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Subject to any legal constraints, we will keep you informed of the progress and <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">outcome</strong> of the investigation.”</em> (Đoạn 7)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Subject to any legal constraints” tương ứng với “no legal issue involved”. Công ty sẽ thông báo cho bạn về tiến độ và kết quả cuối cùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">outcome</strong>) của cuộc điều tra.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('44451839-0fa4-4829-bd35-4bf50a1046eb', '44b7ba78-0b92-454e-8d8c-3d1acf6fe500', 'fillup', 'Questions 21 - 30', '<p>Complete the notes below</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Archaeology Course</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Can be combined with any other subject except {classical history}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Has three {compulsory} modules in first semester?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Module 1</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Title: {object matters}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Lecturer: Dr. Morris</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Learning method: Lectures and practical sessions</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Content: Based on processes</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>recording</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>{classification}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>interpretation</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>display</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Assessment: By {coursework}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Module 2</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Title: {towns and cities}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Lecturer: Prof.Elliot</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Content: {the origins} and development of built environments</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Assessment: By {oral} examination</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Module 3</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Title: Method and Science</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Lecturer: Dr. Thompson</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Content: Standard techniques in fieldwork and analysis</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Learning method: 50% lab work, 50% {seminars}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Site survey at end of module (the {location} is to be announced later)</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 3: ARCHAEOLOGY COURSE DISCUSSION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Good morning, come in. You''re Paul, are you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> Yes, I spoke to you on the phone.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, have a seat. You wanted to talk to me about the archaeology course?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> Yes, I read the handbook, but I''d like to find out a few more details before I decide whether to do it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Right, yes. What would you like to know?</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-115\" data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> Well, first of all, can I combine the archaeology <span class=\"citation-1778 citation-end-1778\">course with one in anthropology?<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-116\" data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1777\">Tutor:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1777\"> Yes, you can combine it with any other subject apart from </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"65\"><span class=\"citation-1777\">(Q21) classical history</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1777 citation-end-1777\">. That''s simply because there''s some overlap in the lecture times for those two courses. We weren''t a<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span>ble to coordinate them.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-117\" data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1774 citation-1775 citation-1776\">Paul:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1774 citation-1775 citation-1776 citation-end-1776\"> Okay, fine. And could you tell me about the modules?<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1774 citation-1775 citation-end-1775\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1774 citation-end-1774\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-118\" data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1771 citation-1772 citation-1773\">Tutor:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1771 citation-1772 citation-1773\"> Well, in the first semester, there are three; all of them are </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"69\"><span class=\"citation-1771 citation-1772 citation-1773\">(Q22) compulsory</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1771 citation-1772 citation-1773 citation-end-1773\">. We don''t offer optional modules till next year.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"6\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1771 citation-1772 citation-end-1772\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"7\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1771 citation-end-1771\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"8\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-119\" data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1768 citation-1769 citation-1770\">Paul:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1768 citation-1769 citation-1770 citation-end-1770\"> Right.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"9\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1768 citation-1769 citation-end-1769\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"10\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1768 citation-end-1768\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"11\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-120\" data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1765 citation-1766 citation-1767\">Tutor:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1765 citation-1766 citation-1767 citation-end-1767\"> The first one focuses on what can be learned from specific artifacts, su<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"12\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1765 citation-1766\">ch as pottery and stone tools. It''s called </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"122\"><span class=\"citation-1765 citation-1766\">(Q23) Object Matters</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-1765 citation-1766 citation-end-1766\">, and it''s taug<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"13\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1765 citation-end-1765\">ht by Dr. Morris.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"14\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-121\" data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1764 citation-end-1764\">Paul:<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"15\"><!----></sup></span></strong> How is the module presented? I mean, is it lectures?</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> We refer to the means of presentation as the learning method, and in this case, it''s lectures integrated with practical sessions.So it''s a mixture. </p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-122\" data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> What about <span class=\"citation-1763 citation-end-1763\">the content? I suppose we''ll be looking at different kinds of archaeological remains and how to date them and so on?<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"16\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-123\" data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1762\">Tutor:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1762 citation-end-1762\"> To some extent, but the module is basically about processes. First of all, recording material, the<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"17\"><!----></sup></span>n <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(Q24) classification</strong></span>, then interpretation <span class=\"citation-1760 citation-1761 citation-end-1761\">of the data—that''s how archaeologists draw conclusions about their findings—and finally, display. Is that okay?<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"18\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1760 citation-end-1760\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"19\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-124\" data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1758 citation-1759\">Paul:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1758 citation-1759 citation-end-1759\"> I think so, yes thanks. Uh, one other thing, how is the module assessed? Is there an exam?<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"20\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1758 citation-end-1758\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"21\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-125\" data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1756 citation-1757\">Tutor:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1756 citation-1757 citation-end-1757\"> No, it''s all based o<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"22\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-1756\">n </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"29\"><span class=\"citation-1756 citation-end-1756\">(Q25) course<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"23\"><!----></sup></span>work</strong></span>.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MODULE 2 &amp; 3 (Questions 26–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> Okay</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And the second module, that''s the one called <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">(Q26) Towns and Cities</strong></span>, is taught by our department head, Professor Elliot. And as the name suggests, the module''s about the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">(Q27) origins</strong></span> of built environments and how they developed.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> That''s mainly factual then, I suppose?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> It is really, and for that reason, the assessment''s by examination. But you may be pleased to know it''s an <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">(Q28) oral</strong></span> rather than a written exam.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> It sounds a bit scary!</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_57a721f172e69c22-126\" data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Most of our students find they actually enjoy it, so don''t worry too much.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong>Paul: </strong>Okay</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><span class=\"citation-1755 citation-end-1755\"><strong>Tutor:</strong> And then the title of the third module is \"Method and Science\", and in that, Dr. Thompson will be introducing you to the standard techniques used in archaeological fieldwork and analysis, things like excavating and dati<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"24\"><!----></sup></span>ng.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> What about the learning method for this module? Are there any lectures or is it all laboratory work?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Oh, it''s half lab work and half <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">(Q29) seminars</strong></span>. There aren''t any lectures then. Right at the end of the module, you''ll take part in a site survey. The date for that is week beginning March 10th, but I can''t tell you the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"227\">(Q30) location</strong></span> yet—that''ll be announced later. But I think you''ll find it very useful.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Paul:</strong> Yes, I know someone who went on that last year...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('91553d4e-a58b-4263-a4f6-d1a70ca974f5', 'a73c6549-8c8e-4355-9425-19058dc8673b', 'matrix', 'Questions 15–18', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="26">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="29">B</strong>, or <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="35">C</strong> next to Questions 15–18.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Ceri", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "James", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Leo", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Mark", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "a lack of confidence", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "a dislike of running", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "a lack of time", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('50d1e563-d6b4-4403-8fa6-ce51f87024b4', '617564f3-b19f-48fd-b9d5-809f9363eda5', 'radio', 'Questions 27–32', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer. <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer. <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When DeJesus first used ABS, he shared decision-making about strikes with it."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "MLB considered it necessary to amend the size of the strike zone when criticisms were received from players."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "MLB is keen to justify the money spent on improving the accuracy of ABS’s calculations."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The hundred-mile-an-hour fastball led to a more exciting style of play."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The differing proposals for alterations to the baseball bat led to fierce debate on Sword’s team."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "ABS makes changes to the shape of the strike zone feasible."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>27. NO<br />(Đoạn 1: “Instead of making any judgments himself about a strike, DeJesus had decisions fed to him through an earpiece…”)<br />→ DeJesus không chia sẻ quyền quyết định mà hoàn toàn dựa vào ABS để gọi strike. → NO.</p>\n<p> <br />28. YES<br />(Đoạn 4: “During the first robo-umpire season, players complained about some strange calls. In response, MLB decided to tweak the dimensions of the zone.”)<br />→ MLB điều chỉnh kích thước vùng strike zone sau khi nhận phản hồi từ cầu thủ. → YES.</p>\n<p> <br />29. NOT GIVEN<br />→ Không có thông tin nói rằng MLB cần biện minh cho chi phí đã đầu tư để cải thiện độ chính xác của ABS. → NOT GIVEN.</p>\n<p> <br />30. NO<br />(Đoạn 6: “The hundred-mile-an-hour fastball… flattened the game into strikeouts, walks, and home runs—a type of play lacking much action.”)<br />→ Fastball 100 dặm/giờ khiến trận đấu ít sôi động hơn, không phải “exciting”. → NO.</p>\n<p> <br />31. NOT GIVEN<br />→ Không có chi tiết cho thấy đội của Sword tranh cãi gay gắt về việc thay đổi gậy bóng chày. → NOT GIVEN.</p>\n<p> <br />32. YES<br />(Đoạn 6: “Once you get the technology right, you can load any strike zone you want into the system… Over time, ABS can allow the zone to change with it.”)<br />→ Công nghệ ABS cho phép thay đổi hình dạng vùng strike zone. → YES.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('75e316b3-de2c-4df7-80f1-cb9b89604ab4', 'd401d71d-0210-415f-9ec6-0350623bbf6d', 'matrix', 'Questions 28 – 32', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="26">A-F</strong>, in boxes 28-32 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a personal motive for improving the design of a pen", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "extreme conditions in which existing pens did not work well", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "the reason why some writing tools are not classified as pens", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a type of pen which constantly needed reshaping", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "the suitability of a new pen to an older style of writing", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. A personal motive for improving the design of a pen — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…he was preparing to sign an important contract… but it failed to work and as a result he lost the contract. Waterman refused to be caught out again and… designed his own fountain pen.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Motive” (động cơ) cá nhân của Waterman là do ông đã đánh mất một hợp đồng quan trọng vì chiếc bút cũ bị hỏng, dẫn đến quyết định tự thiết kế một chiếc bút máy tốt hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Extreme conditions in which existing pens did not work well — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…they also functioned at high altitudes, whereas fountain pens flooded as a result of the reduced pressure.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Extreme conditions” (điều kiện khắc nghiệt) ở đây là ở độ cao lớn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">high altitudes</strong>). Trong điều kiện này, áp suất giảm khiến bút máy truyền thống bị chảy mực (flooded), trong khi bút bi của Biro vẫn hoạt động tốt.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"attachment-container search-images\">\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"image-container ng-star-inserted\" data-full-size-image-uri=\"https://encrypted-tbn2.gstatic.com/licensed-image?q=tbn:ANd9GcS_GVZqgumpp9H1xIXilAikPD_FdS5rpdvPsz5t_MU-rjhBUDWZre-d-W9sG3vGwG8AVvAi3K9tJx1WGM0NfsG2S813oP-70r0F3rZgxAt7KbhzT9U\"> </div>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The reason why some writing tools are not classified as pens — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“However, as the dictionary definition of a pen is ‘a tool for writing or drawing with a coloured fluid such as ink’, these are not true pens.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A nêu lý do các công cụ khắc lên đất sét hay sáp không được coi là bút “thực thụ” vì chúng không sử dụng chất lỏng có màu (mực) theo định nghĩa của từ điển.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. A type of pen which constantly needed reshaping — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The writing life of the quills was extremely short and they needed constant trimming with a knife after use…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bút lông ngỗng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">quills</strong>) có tuổi thọ rất ngắn và cần phải được gọt/tỉa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">trimming</strong>) liên tục bằng dao để tạo lại hình dáng đầu bút sau khi sử dụng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. The suitability of a new pen to an older style of writing — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The product was ideally suited to the strokes of Japanese calligraphy, which is traditionally produced with a pointed ink brush.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Older style of writing” chính là nghệ thuật thư pháp Nhật Bản (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">Japanese calligraphy</strong>). Chiếc bút dạ (fibre-tipped pen) mới của Yukio Horie rất phù hợp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">suited</strong>) với các nét vẽ vốn truyền thống được tạo ra bằng cọ.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2e601cca-a534-4294-97fd-0c45fba4c9d0', 'd401d71d-0210-415f-9ec6-0350623bbf6d', 'radio', 'Questions 33 – 36', '', '<p>Choose<strong data-path-to-node="11,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information ,<strong data-path-to-node="11,0" data-index-in-node="50">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information ,<strong data-path-to-node="11,0" data-index-in-node="101">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Quill pens were cheaper to produce than pens made from reeds."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Heat was used to make one type of pen last longer."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Pens with metal nibs first appeared in the 1800s."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The ballpoint pen was an immediate commercial success."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Quill pens were cheaper to produce than pens made from reeds. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn B có nhắc đến việc bút lông ngỗng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">quill</strong>) thay thế bút sậy (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">reed</strong>) và cách chế biến chúng.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói bút lông ngỗng thay thế bút sậy vì người ta nhận ra ưu điểm của nó (split and shape it for writing), nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">không hề có thông tin so sánh chi phí sản xuất (cheaper)</strong> giữa hai loại này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Heat was used to make one type of pen last longer. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“One way of doing this was to <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">bury the quills in hot sand</strong> to allow them to dry off and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">become hard</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn B)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc vùi bút lông ngỗng vào cát nóng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">heat</strong>) giúp chúng trở nên cứng hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">hard</strong>), từ đó tăng độ bền và thời gian sử dụng (tương ứng với ý “last longer” trong câu hỏi).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Pens with metal nibs first appeared in the 1800s. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Metal nibs have very early origins; a pen with a bronze nib was found in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">ruins of Pompeii</strong>… Wealthy people had gold- and silver-nibbed pens in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">1500s</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn C)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc xác nhận ngòi bút kim loại đã xuất hiện từ thời cổ đại (Pompeii) và những năm 1500, mâu thuẫn trực tiếp với ý “lần đầu tiên xuất hiện (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">first appeared</strong>) vào những năm 1800″. Những năm 1800 chỉ là thời điểm bắt đầu sản xuất hàng loạt bằng thép.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The ballpoint pen was an immediate commercial success. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The first ballpoint pens were on the market from 1895, but <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">sold slowly</strong> because they had a number of failings…”</em> (Đoạn E)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sold slowly” (bán chậm) mâu thuẫn với ý “immediate commercial success” (thành công thương mại ngay lập tức). Phải đến sau này (1943 và 1953) bút bi mới thực sự thành công về mặt thương mại.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('236212c7-4114-4b89-8663-73e082f3834a', 'd401d71d-0210-415f-9ec6-0350623bbf6d', 'matching', 'Questions 37 – 40', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="26">A-G</strong>, in boxes 37-40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "It worked better after a different type of ink was used."}, {"optionText": "It was used in Asia about 3,000 years ago."}, {"optionText": "It has the largest market share."}, {"optionText": "It was only given as an expensive gift."}, {"optionText": "Chemicals were used to make the tip stronger."}, {"optionText": "A technical development eliminated possible ink spills."}, {"optionText": "The earliest versions were used mainly for creative work."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "the quill pen", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "the fountain pen", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "the ballpoint pen", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "the fibre-tipped pen", "correctAnswer": "G"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The quill pen — {E} Chemicals were used to make the tip stronger.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Other finishing processes involved <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">hardening in acids</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn B)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Hardening in acids” (làm cứng trong axit) chính là việc sử dụng hóa chất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">chemicals</strong>) để làm cho đầu bút (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">tip</strong>) trở nên mạnh/cứng hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">stronger</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. The fountain pen — {F} A technical development eliminated possible ink spills.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Then in 1927, when the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">ink cartridge</strong> was invented, the constant need to refill fountain pens with <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">messy liquid ink</strong> from a bottle was removed.”</em> (Đoạn D)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự ra đời của ống mực (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">ink cartridge</strong>) là một bước tiến kỹ thuật giúp loại bỏ việc phải bơm mực lỏng lỉnh từ lọ, từ đó ngăn chặn việc làm đổ mực (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">ink spills/messy liquid ink</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. The ballpoint pen — {A} It worked better after a different type of ink was used.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Biro… saw how fast <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">printing ink</strong> dried and thought of using <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">something similar</strong> in a new type of pen. In 1943, he made the first commercial models.”</em> (Đoạn E)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bút bi đời đầu bán chậm vì nhiều lỗi. Sau khi Biro thay thế bằng loại mực nhanh khô (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">quick-drying ink</strong>) tương tự mực in, chiếc bút mới thực sự hoạt động hiệu quả và thành công.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. The fibre-tipped pen — {G} The earliest versions were used mainly for creative work.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The first fibre-tipped pens appeared in the 1940s, but these were… predominantly used for <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">labelling and artistic work</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn F)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những phiên bản đầu tiên của bút dạ chủ yếu được dùng để dán nhãn và làm công việc nghệ thuật (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">artistic work</strong>) – một dạng của công việc sáng tạo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">creative work</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('695ae985-a115-4902-925d-3b815e7c18c9', '1c9eba9b-3398-4a72-a658-fcbf65d2b9dd', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', '', '<p data-start="136" data-end="168">Choose <strong data-start="143" data-end="150">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-start="160" data-end="167">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="170" data-end="261"><strong data-start="170" data-end="261">Which TWO benefits for children of learning to write did both students find surprising?</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A improved fine motor skills"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B improved memory"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C improved concentration"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D improved imagination"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E improved spatial awareness"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"187\"><strong data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"126\">MAN:</strong> How are you getting on with the assignment on handwriting?</p>\n<p data-start=\"189\" data-end=\"459\"><strong data-start=\"189\" data-end=\"199\">WOMAN:</strong> Not too bad. You know, I hadn’t realised that children benefit in so many ways from learning to write. It’s such an important skill and yet most people think handwriting is less important than in the past because people hardly ever write by hand these days.</p>\n<p data-start=\"461\" data-end=\"613\"><strong data-start=\"461\" data-end=\"469\">MAN:</strong> Yes. And all the evidence suggests children should learn to write by hand before they learn to type. Not least because it helps their memory.</p>\n<p data-start=\"615\" data-end=\"756\"><strong data-start=\"615\" data-end=\"625\">WOMAN:</strong> That’s right. The physical act of writing helps children to remember letters. That seems pretty obvious when you think about it.</p>\n<p data-start=\"758\" data-end=\"880\"><strong data-start=\"758\" data-end=\"766\">MAN:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21) What’s less obvious is how it helps develop their concentration</strong></span>. They have to sit still and focus on one thing.</p>\n<p data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"960\"><strong data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"892\">WOMAN:</strong> Yeah. That aspect of handwriting had never occurred to me before.</p>\n<p data-start=\"962\" data-end=\"1056\"><strong data-start=\"962\" data-end=\"970\">MAN:</strong> Same here. I’m not sure I understand how it improves children’s imagination though.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1058\" data-end=\"1255\"><strong data-start=\"1058\" data-end=\"1068\">WOMAN:</strong> Well, there was that study which showed that primary-aged children generated more ideas when they were writing by hand than using a keyboard. I would’ve guessed that would be the case.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1452\"><strong data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1265\">MAN:</strong> Mmm, yeah.<strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> (22) I’d never associated spatial awareness with handwriting either</span></strong>. I thought spatial awareness was more to do with knowing where you are in relation to objects or other people.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1454\" data-end=\"1665\"><strong data-start=\"1454\" data-end=\"1464\">WOMAN:</strong> I thought that too. But good spatial awareness is essential for writing because you have to space words correctly. It’s not just fine motor skills that improve through writing as I’d always assumed.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"2013\"><strong data-start=\"1672\" data-end=\"1680\">MAN:</strong> Handwriting is so much harder for children with dyspraxia, who have problems coordinating movement. It’s good there are lots of things you can do in the classroom to help them. They need so much more support with letter formation – you need to play lots of games to help them distinguish letter shapes. It takes a lot of patience.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2015\" data-end=\"2157\"><strong data-start=\"2015\" data-end=\"2025\">WOMAN:</strong> Yeah.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (23) I liked the idea of using one of those pens that lights up if you press too hard. That seems like a really simple solution.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2159\" data-end=\"2380\"><strong data-start=\"2159\" data-end=\"2167\">MAN:</strong> Yes, absolutely. I’m not sure there’s much you can do about children with dyspraxia writing very slowly. It’s more important to focus on accuracy and as they get more confident I think they eventually speed up.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2382\" data-end=\"2538\"><strong data-start=\"2382\" data-end=\"2392\">WOMAN:</strong>  <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(24) </span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">One quite simple thing you can do is to use grid paper. So they write each letter in a box and that trains them to space the letters correctly.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2540\" data-end=\"2648\"><strong data-start=\"2540\" data-end=\"2548\">MAN:</strong> Indeed, that’s more important for legibility than trying to get them to write in a straight line.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2655\" data-end=\"2854\"><strong data-start=\"2655\" data-end=\"2663\">MAN:</strong> For some children it might be better to teach them to write on a laptop rather than by hand. Like children with dyslexia. They often really struggle with handwriting and some just give up.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2856\" data-end=\"3040\"><strong data-start=\"2856\" data-end=\"2866\">WOMAN:</strong> Yeah. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(25) It’s not as frustrating for them if they get things wrong – on a keyboard they can be more willing to have a go</span></strong>. But I read that developing fluency isn’t any faster.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3042\" data-end=\"3192\"><strong data-start=\"3042\" data-end=\"3050\">MAN:</strong> That’s right. Did you read that article on the benefits of teaching print rather than cursive handwriting, where the letters are joined up?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3194\" data-end=\"3513\"><strong data-start=\"3194\" data-end=\"3204\">WOMAN:</strong> Yes. Well in the past, cursive writing was certainly considered more stylish and educated. But not anymore. Teachers’ attitudes have changed because it’s been proved that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(26) cursive is more difficult to learn – especially for children with learning difficulties</strong></span> who find joining up letters really challenging.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3515\" data-end=\"3772\"><strong data-start=\"3515\" data-end=\"3523\">MAN:</strong> I agree.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (27) I was always worried that my poor handwriting affected my exam results. And now research shows that was right to worry</strong></span>. I’m sure a lot of students think it’s unfair that they’re being judged on their handwriting not just their knowledge.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3774\" data-end=\"3993\"><strong data-start=\"3774\" data-end=\"3784\">WOMAN:</strong> Marks are definitely affected if examiners can’t read the script. That’s why it’s always been so important to teach children to write legibly. Do you think the role of handwriting will change in the future?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3995\" data-end=\"4301\"><strong data-start=\"3995\" data-end=\"4003\">MAN: </strong><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(28) I can’t see that changing much</span></strong>. Touch typing still isn’t taught in most schools, which is a shame. But maybe that won’t be necessary in the future because people will also be able to write by hand on digital devices. Anyway, teachers understand the value of handwriting. It’s a basic life skill.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4303\" data-end=\"4451\"><strong data-start=\"4303\" data-end=\"4313\">WOMAN:</strong> True. However, the fact is that people are writing by hand less and less and relying on digital devices. That does cause some problems.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4453\" data-end=\"4523\"><strong data-start=\"4453\" data-end=\"4461\">MAN:</strong> You mean like note taking? There are lots of apps for that.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4525\" data-end=\"4738\"><strong data-start=\"4525\" data-end=\"4535\">WOMAN:</strong> And for reading historical documents, apparently. But my mum is shocked by <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(29) my awful spelling and the fact that my punctuation is really inconsistent. I think you can put that down to lack of practice.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"4740\" data-end=\"4991\"><strong data-start=\"4740\" data-end=\"4748\">MAN:</strong> I expect so. Personally, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) I miss writing by hand. I hardly ever write anything now</strong></span>. I remember my grandparents had such beautiful handwriting and it was so individual. Nobody I know would be able to identify my handwriting now. It’s a shame.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4993\" data-end=\"5168\"><strong data-start=\"4993\" data-end=\"5003\">WOMAN:</strong> I know. I feel the same way. I used to write a diary by hand and now I do that digitally. It just seems less effort to do it that way. So it’s not just a problem…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3ac4ac5a-46cc-499f-afe1-755891ae92a9', '521fc6a0-b04b-426e-8a77-721d4568d619', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', '', '<p>Choose<strong data-start="204" data-end="212"> TRUE</strong> – if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-start="262" data-end="271">FALSE</strong> – if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-start="321" data-end="334">NOT GIVEN</strong> – if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Customers will need to open the window in hot weather."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The latest movies are shown on many journeys."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Tourists are advised to buy discount tickets."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Taking sleeper buses can save you money on transport costs."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Passengers can change their travel plans with a Discovery Pass."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Passengers should stow their luggage below their seats."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Customers will need to open the window in hot weather. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Buses have <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">climate control</strong> so you don’t have to worry about keeping cool while you are travelling around.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Xe buýt có hệ thống kiểm soát khí hậu (điều hòa), giúp hành khách luôn mát mẻ mà không cần phải mở cửa sổ. Hơn nữa, xe còn có “tinted windows” (kính màu) để cản nhiệt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. The latest movies are shown on many journeys. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“You will find that on popular routes, buses are also equipped with <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">TV/radio equipment</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói xe có trang bị TV/Radio trên các tuyến phổ biến, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc có chiếu các bộ phim mới nhất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">latest movies</strong>) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Tourists are advised to buy discount tickets. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Greyhound offer a range of different fare options, including discount tickets… For the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">tourist</strong>, however, it is <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">better to get the Discovery Pass</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù có vé giảm giá (discount tickets), nhưng đối với khách du lịch (tourists), bài viết khuyên nên mua loại thẻ <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">Discovery Pass</strong> thì tốt hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Taking sleeper buses can save you money on transport costs. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…many travellers opt to take sleeper buses so that <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">waking hours aren’t wasted travelling</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói việc đi xe giường nằm giúp tiết kiệm thời gian (không lãng phí giờ thức để di chuyển), nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">không có thông tin</strong> về việc nó có giúp tiết kiệm tiền vé (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">save money on transport costs</strong>) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Passengers can change their travel plans with a Discovery Pass. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you have a Discovery Pass, you can <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">make detours on your trip</strong> should any of your new-found travelling companions come up with a place to visit…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thẻ Discovery Pass cho phép bạn đi đường vòng (make detours), tức là có thể thay đổi kế hoạch di chuyển ban đầu một cách linh hoạt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Passengers should stow their luggage below their seats. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…making sure your bags are stowed away properly in <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">overhead lockers</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khuyên hành khách nên cất túi xách vào khoang hành lý phía trên đầu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">overhead lockers</strong>) để tránh mất cắp, chứ không phải để dưới ghế (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">below their seats</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('de15d509-33c9-4b15-a417-5fdd109cc130', '1d359a32-2f56-44b1-a951-175dda2f4020', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p><strong>Complete the notes below.</strong></p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>American Southwest: 1860s to present day</strong></span></p>
<p>1862 – American Homestead Act was passed to encourage settlement in the West.</p>
<p>1930s – Laws were passed to control the size of {cattle herds}</p>
<p>Today Jayne Belnap believes:</p>
<p>○     soil was not affected by high {winds}</p>
<p>○     soil was seriously affected by cattle hooves.</p>
<p>Jason Neff:</p>
<p>○     found that {lake sediments}in the Colorado region contained dust</p>
<p>○     examined the dust for its chemical content as well as its {size}</p>
<p>○     concluded that the dust was from the American Southwest</p>
<p>○     found that dust affects mountain environments by</p>
<p>bringing in {nutrients} that are not normally found there</p>
<p>causing faster seasonal snowmelt</p>
<p>○     argues that dust is partly to blame for the gradual disappearance of some {glaciers} and snow.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<h3>8.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: cattle herds</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “…It was only in the 1930s, with the passage of the Taylor Grazing Act, that federal authorities finally sought to limit <strong>cattle herds</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>9.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: winds</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “These crusts can survive <strong>winds</strong> of up to a hundred miles an hour…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Jayne Belnap nói rằng lớp vỏ cứng của đất có thể chịu được gió rất mạnh (“up to a hundred miles an hour”), ngụ ý rằng đất không dễ bị ảnh hưởng bởi gió (high winds) nếu lớp vỏ này còn nguyên vẹn.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>10.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: lake sediments</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “When Neff first discovered dust in Colorado <strong>lake sediments</strong> laid down in the 19th century…”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>11.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: size</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “But after investigating the <strong>size</strong> and chemical composition of the dust, Neff was clear…”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>12.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: nutrients</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “They carry <strong>nutrients</strong> with them into areas which previously evolved and survived without them.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>13.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: glaciers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn I) “The loss of snow and the shrinking of <strong>glaciers</strong> across the American West in the past century has been dramatic.” (Glaciers là danh từ được nhắc đến trước “and snow” trong đoạn cuối.)</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0d77dc86-180c-4049-9dd2-7dff1da251a1', '617564f3-b19f-48fd-b9d5-809f9363eda5', 'radio', 'Questions 38–40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. It is bound to make key decisions that are wrong."}, {"content": "B. It may reduce some of the appeal of the game."}, {"content": "C. It will lead to the disappearance of human umpires."}, {"content": "D. It may increase calls for the rules of baseball to be changed."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about ABS in the fifth paragraph?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A. was regarded as an experiment without a guaranteed outcome."}, {"content": "B. was intended to keep up with developments in other sports."}, {"content": "C. was a response to changing attitudes about the role of sport."}, {"content": "D. was an attempt to ensure baseball retained a young audience."}], "question": "Morgan Sword says that the introduction of ABS"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. To show that attitudes to technology vary widely"}, {"content": "B. To argue that people have unrealistic expectations of sport"}, {"content": "C. To indicate that accuracy is not the same thing as enjoyment"}, {"content": "D. To suggest that the number of baseball fans needs to increase"}], "question": "Why does the writer include the views of Noë and Russo?"}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>38. B<br />(Đoạn 5: “ABS works as designed, but it was also unforgiving and pedantic… Some pitchers complained… the robot’s strike zone seems too precise.”)<br />→ Tác giả gợi ý rằng ABS có thể làm giảm sức hấp dẫn của trận đấu vì quá chính xác và khô cứng. → B.</p>\n<p> <br />39. D<br />(Đoạn 6: “ABS was part of a larger project to make baseball more exciting since executives are terrified of losing younger fans.”)<br />→ Sword cho rằng việc áp dụng ABS nhằm giúp bóng chày hấp dẫn hơn với khán giả trẻ. → D.</p>\n<p> <br />40. C<br />(Đoạn cuối: “Some players… believe that accuracy is not the answer… ‘With technology, people just want everything to be perfect… What is there to talk about?’”)<br />→ Việc nhắc đến Noë và Russo nhằm chỉ ra rằng độ chính xác không đồng nghĩa với sự thú vị. → C.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1616d031-c32e-4ba7-8e30-980d6eb44096', '0fd88a89-f429-41af-879e-3dd686ee69a9', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information  <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information  <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
<div class="space-y-1"></div>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Rubber plants grow only in certain regions of the world."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Rubber was extracted in Mexico as early as the sixth century"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Rubber from the Castilla elastica plant is of poorer quality than that from the Para plant."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A French mathematician inspired real interest in rubber amongst Europeans."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The process of vulcanisation was discovered by accident."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Imports of crude rubber into Britain fell during the nineteenth century."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1. Rubber plants grow only in certain regions of the world.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: FALSE<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn 1) “The plants that produce rubber are spread right across the globe, and grow in many different habitats.”<br />\nGiải thích: Cây cao su mọc ở khắp thế giới và nhiều môi trường sống khác nhau, mâu thuẫn với nhận định “chỉ ở một số vùng”.</p>\n<p>2. Rubber was extracted in Mexico as early as the sixth century.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn 1) “…a wall painting dating back to the sixth century depicts a scene of a tributary offering of crude rubber.”<br />\nGiải thích: Có bằng chứng về việc dâng cống cao su vào thế kỷ thứ sáu, nhưng không có thông tin xác nhận quá trình chiết xuất (extracted) đã diễn ra từ thời điểm đó.</p>\n<p>3. Rubber from the Castilla elastica plant is of poorer quality than that from the Para plant.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn 1) “…must have been made from the indigenous Castilla elastica, as the Para plant now favoured for rubber cultivation does not grow in the Mexican region.”<br />\nGiải thích: Văn bản chỉ nói cây Para được “ưa chuộng” hơn cho việc canh tác (favoured), nhưng không so sánh chất lượng cao su giữa hai loại cây.</p>\n<p>4. A French mathematician inspired real interest in rubber amongst Europeans.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: TRUE<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn 2) “However, no real interest in rubber was shown by any European until Charles de la Condamine, a French mathematician, published an account of his journey to South America in 1735.”<br />\nGiải thích: Nhà toán học Condamine (French mathematician) đã khơi dậy sự quan tâm thực sự (real interest) của người châu Âu.</p>\n<p>5. The process of vulcanisation was discovered by accident.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn 3) “Then in 1839 the American Charles Goodyear discovered that it was possible to stabilise rubber by mixing it with sulphur while exposing it to heat…”<br />\nGiải thích: Văn bản mô tả Charles Goodyear đã khám phá ra quá trình này, nhưng không nói rõ đó là do tình cờ (by accident) hay là kết quả của nghiên cứu có chủ ý.</p>\n<p>6. Imports of crude rubber into Britain fell during the nineteenth century.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: FALSE<br />\nDẫn chứng: (Đoạn 4) “The import levels of rubber over the nineteenth century bear witness to its irrepressible rise. In 1830 Britain had imported just 211 kg… This had risen to 10,000kg in 1857, and by 1874 levels were just under six times as much again.”<br />\nGiải thích: Số liệu cho thấy nhập khẩu cao su tăng mạnh (“irrepressible rise”) trong thế kỷ 19, mâu thuẫn với việc giảm (“fell”).</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6b876282-26aa-41f5-8d33-1fa39b2ce9da', '0fd88a89-f429-41af-879e-3dd686ee69a9', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–13', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p><strong>The Commercial Development of Rubber</strong></p>
<p>Early European travellers gave accounts of various rubber objects in use in Central and South America, and these accounts created interest in the commercial exploitation of rubber. In 1818, {waterproof cloth} was produced using rubber, and in 1820 a machine was invented for recycling {waste strips} of rubber. Over the next few years, other attempts were made to improve rubber, but some problems remained. For example, rubber products smelt bad when they were dissolved, and could turn either soft or {rigid} depending on the temperature. However, in 1839 a new process to {stabilise} the substance greatly increased its potential. For example, rubber was used in the creation of the {steam engines} industry during the Industrial Revolution. Then in 1888 the {first pneumatic tyre| pneumatic tyre} was developed, and a few years later the {mass production} of the motor car began.</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\">7. In 1818, waterproof cloth was produced using rubber</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">waterproof cloth</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) “In 1818 a British medical student named James Syme first used rubber to make </span><strong class=\"\">waterproof cloth</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">8. …a machine was invented for recycling waste strips of rubber.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">waste strips</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn 2) “…</span><span class=\"\">invented a machine he called the ‘piokle’,</span><span class=\"\"> which chewed up </span><strong class=\"\">waste strips</strong><span class=\"\"> for re-use.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\">9. …rubber products smelt bad when they were dissolved, and could turn either soft or rigid depending on the temperature.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong class=\"\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\">rigid</strong></li>\n<li class=\"animating\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “They also became pliant when warm and <strong>rigid</strong> when cold.” (Pliant đồng nghĩa với soft – mềm).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>10. However, in 1839 a new process to stabilise the substance greatly increased its potential.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>stabilise</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “…Charles Goodyear discovered that it was possible to <strong>stabilise</strong> rubber by mixing it with sulphur…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>11. For example, rubber was used in the creation of the steam engines industry during the Industrial Revolution.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>steam engines</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “It played an important role in the Industrial Revolution, being employed in the <strong>steam engines</strong> found in factories…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>12. Then in 1888 the pneumatic tyre was developed, and a few years later the mass production of the motor car began.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>pneumatic tyre</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…John Boyd Dunlop produced the first <strong>pneumatic tyre</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>13. …and a few years later the mass production of the motor car began.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mass production</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…and with the <strong>mass production</strong> of cars just over the horizon…”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9de02a25-2cdf-4342-a475-60123bb2f66c', 'd3317984-005e-4eef-a00d-523830eed947', 'radio', 'Questions 21–25', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Climate change and allergies</strong></span></p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A.because people’s diets have improved since the 1950s"}, {"content": "B.because most people get enough vitamin D"}, {"content": "C.because the evidence only applies in Britain"}], "question": "Why is Beth unconvinced that allergies are linked to vitamin D deficiency?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A.will mean distribution of pollen over a wider area."}, {"content": "B.are having less impact on pollen than milder winters."}, {"content": "C.are responsible for higher quantities of pollen."}], "question": "Eliot explains that rising CO2 levels"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A.There is no clear short-term trend for the arrival of spring."}, {"content": "B.In general, spring is likely to continue arriving early."}, {"content": "C.Springs are becoming milder and longer."}], "question": "What does Beth say about seasonal changes?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A.it is spreading to more countries."}, {"content": "B.it is the most widespread cause of allergies globally."}, {"content": "C.it causes the most severe type of allergy."}], "question": "What point is made about the plant ragweed?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A.Trees produce more pollen there."}, {"content": "B.There is less to absorb the tree pollen."}, {"content": "C.There is not enough control over tree-planting."}], "question": "Why is tree pollen a more serious problem in cities?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear two health science students called Elliot and Beth discussing research on climate change and allergies. First you have some time to look at questions 21 to 25. Now listen carefully and answer questions 21 to 25.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Have you had a chance to look at the information for our project yet Beth?</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> I’ve had a look at most of the stuff on the relationship between climate change and allergies and the role played by pollen from flowering plants and trees.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Yeah, me too. The main message is that seasonal allergies seem to be getting worse in just the last 20 years. The amount of pollen that’s produced by the flowers on birch trees has tripled, and one in four people suffers from either hay fever or asthma which is triggered by pollen.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> I read something about allergy sufferers being more likely to have a vitamin D deficiency because we no longer take cod liver oil as a vitamin supplement like many people used to do in the 1950s in Britain, and since then allergies have quadrupled in most European countries. <span class=\"citation-457\">But it was only in </span><strong><span class=\"citation-457\">(21) Britain (C)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-457 citation-end-457\"> that cod liver oil was so popular, so that argument doesn’t really make sense</span>.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ4ww\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> No, it doesn’t seem that relevant. What seems to be happening now is that an increasing number of people are getting their first attack in their 40s and fifties.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Hmm, that must be because of the link with climate change causing rising temperatures.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> But CO2 levels are seriously affecting pollen counts too, as much as milder winters. Definitely. <span class=\"citation-456\">CO2 helps stimulate plant growth and several recent studies have shown that when plants are exposed to more CO2 they produce </span><strong><span class=\"citation-456\">(22) more pollen (C)</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Really? So people might experience more severe allergic symptoms in future.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5Aw\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> That’s right. Hmm, and another factor is that the pollen season is changing. Yes, scientists are predicting spring will come five weeks earlier by 2130, that’s in the long term. But that doesn’t mean that spring will come earlier every year. Look at last winter, that was really cold until March, and the pollen season was delayed. Whereas this year spring came earlier and lasted longer. <strong><span class=\"citation-455\">(23) Right (A)</span></strong>.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5Qw\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> And another thing we should mention is ragweed as an example of a plant species moving into new areas as a result of climate change.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Yes, in the US it’s already the major allergen affecting millions of people in August and September. But we’re starting to see it grow in Europe for the first time, which is really worrying because it’s so allergenic. <strong><span class=\"citation-454\">(24) (A)</span></strong>. The problem with tree pollen is also worse in cities because there are so many hard surfaces around and the pollen doesn’t get absorbed so much, just stays in the air. <strong><span class=\"citation-453\">(25) (B)</span></strong>.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5gw\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Yeah, wasn’t the pollen shown to be three times higher in one city? I think so. So because of this many cities have started to ban the planting of certain types of trees.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the discussion, you have some time to look at questions 26 to 30 on page six. Now listen and answer questions 26 to thirty.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> So shall we look at the different data tables for seasonal changes for pollen in Europe?</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Okay, but I think we should just focus on the trees and plants which we have the most data for: so that’s oak trees and birch trees and grass.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Yes, that makes it more manageable. Shall we go through the data for each country in detail and pick out anything interesting? Alright, so uh, starting with Austria. <span class=\"citation-452\">Well, here we’ve </span><strong><span class=\"citation-452\">(26) only got data for birch pollen (G)</span></strong>. I wonder why there’s no data for oak or grass. Hmm, it would be interesting to compare with neighbouring countries.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ5ww\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> True. The picture in France is unusual.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Yes. The pollen season starts earlier for both oak and birch, but it doesn’t start any earlier for grass. <strong><span class=\"citation-451\">(27) (B)</span></strong>. I wonder why that is.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6Aw\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> In the Netherlands we’ve got complete data for all three plants. So what does it show? Hmm, grass and birch pollen are only starting a few days earlier, but oak pollen is starting much earlier, 18 days in fact. <strong><span class=\"citation-450\">(28) (A)</span></strong>. Hmm, that’s unusual. There’s not such a big difference in other countries.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6Qw\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> No. Switzerland’s an interesting case. <span class=\"citation-449\">The pollen season starts here </span><strong><span class=\"citation-449\">(29) earlier than in the past for oak, birch and grass (D)</span></strong>. Yeah, from 21 days to 14 days earlier.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6gw\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Yeah, the UK shows a different picture again. <span class=\"citation-448\">Yeah, here the problem is that wet summers have </span><strong><span class=\"citation-448\">(30) extended the grass pollen season (C)</span></strong><span class=\"citation-448 citation-end-448\"> from 5 weeks to 8 weeks, which is bad news for allergy sufferers</span>.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwjjpIjIuu-QAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQ6ww\"></button></p>\n<h2 class=\"\"> </h2>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Right, well, I think we should have another look.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 3. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Turn to Section 4 on page seven.</p>\n<h2>🇻🇳 Bản Dịch Tiếng Việt</h2>\n<p><strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Bạn sẽ nghe hai sinh viên khoa học sức khỏe tên là Elliot và Beth thảo luận về nghiên cứu về biến đổi khí hậu và dị ứng. Đầu tiên, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 21 đến 25. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe cẩn thận và trả lời các câu hỏi 21 đến 25.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Bạn đã có cơ hội xem thông tin cho dự án của chúng ta chưa Beth?</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Tôi đã xem hầu hết các tài liệu về mối quan hệ giữa biến đổi khí hậu và dị ứng và vai trò của phấn hoa từ các loài hoa và cây cối.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Ừ, tôi cũng vậy. Thông điệp chính là dị ứng theo mùa dường như đang trở nên tồi tệ hơn chỉ trong 20 năm qua. Lượng phấn hoa được sản xuất bởi hoa trên cây bạch dương đã tăng gấp ba lần, và cứ bốn người thì có một người bị sốt cỏ khô hoặc hen suyễn do phấn hoa gây ra.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Tôi đã đọc một điều gì đó về những người bị dị ứng có nhiều khả năng bị thiếu vitamin D vì chúng ta không còn uống dầu gan cá như một chất bổ sung vitamin như nhiều người thường làm vào những năm 1950 ở Anh, và kể từ đó dị ứng đã tăng gấp bốn lần ở hầu hết các nước châu Âu. Nhưng chỉ ở <strong>(21) Anh</strong> dầu gan cá mới phổ biến, vì vậy lập luận đó không thực sự hợp lý.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Không, điều đó dường như không liên quan. Điều dường như đang xảy ra bây giờ là ngày càng nhiều người bị cơn dị ứng đầu tiên ở độ tuổi 40 và 50.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Hmm, điều đó chắc hẳn là do mối liên hệ với biến đổi khí hậu gây ra nhiệt độ tăng.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Nhưng mức CO2 cũng đang ảnh hưởng nghiêm trọng đến lượng phấn hoa, nhiều như mùa đông ôn hòa hơn. Chắc chắn rồi. CO2 giúp kích thích sự phát triển của thực vật và một số nghiên cứu gần đây đã chỉ ra rằng khi thực vật tiếp xúc với nhiều CO2 hơn, chúng sản xuất <strong>(22) nhiều phấn hoa hơn</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Thật sao? Vậy mọi người có thể gặp phải các triệu chứng dị ứng nghiêm trọng hơn trong tương lai.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Đúng vậy. Hmm, và một yếu tố khác là mùa phấn hoa đang thay đổi. Phải, các nhà khoa học dự đoán mùa xuân sẽ đến sớm hơn năm tuần vào năm 2130, đó là về lâu dài. Nhưng điều đó không có nghĩa là mùa xuân sẽ đến sớm hơn mỗi năm. Hãy nhìn vào mùa đông năm ngoái, mùa đó thực sự lạnh cho đến tháng Ba, và mùa phấn hoa bị trì hoãn. Trong khi năm nay mùa xuân đến sớm hơn và kéo dài hơn. <strong>(23) Đúng vậy</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Và một điều nữa chúng ta nên đề cập là cỏ phấn hương (ragweed) như một ví dụ về một loài thực vật đang di chuyển đến các khu vực mới do biến đổi khí hậu.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Vâng, ở Mỹ, nó đã là chất gây dị ứng chính ảnh hưởng đến hàng triệu người vào tháng Tám và tháng Chín. Nhưng chúng ta đang bắt đầu thấy nó phát triển ở châu Âu lần đầu tiên, điều này thực sự đáng lo ngại vì nó rất dễ gây dị ứng. <strong>(24) (A)</strong>. Vấn đề phấn hoa cây cối cũng tồi tệ hơn ở các thành phố vì có quá nhiều bề mặt cứng xung quanh và phấn hoa không được hấp thụ nhiều mà chỉ ở lại trong không khí. <strong>(25) (B)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Ừ, phải chăng phấn hoa đã được chứng minh là cao hơn gấp ba lần ở một thành phố? Tôi nghĩ vậy. Vì vậy, do điều này, nhiều thành phố đã bắt đầu cấm trồng một số loại cây nhất định.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Trước khi bạn nghe phần còn lại của cuộc thảo luận, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 26 đến 30. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe và trả lời các câu hỏi 26 đến 30.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Vậy chúng ta hãy xem các bảng dữ liệu khác nhau về thay đổi theo mùa đối với phấn hoa ở châu Âu?</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Được, nhưng tôi nghĩ chúng ta chỉ nên tập trung vào các cây và thực vật mà chúng ta có nhiều dữ liệu nhất: đó là cây sồi, cây bạch dương và cỏ.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Vâng, điều đó làm cho nó dễ quản lý hơn. Chúng ta có nên xem chi tiết dữ liệu cho từng quốc gia và chọn ra bất cứ điều gì thú vị không? Được rồi, vậy, bắt đầu với Áo. À, ở đây chúng ta <strong>(26) chỉ có dữ liệu cho phấn hoa bạch dương (G)</strong>. Tôi tự hỏi tại sao không có dữ liệu cho sồi hoặc cỏ. Hmm, sẽ rất thú vị nếu so sánh với các nước láng giềng.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Đúng vậy. Tình hình ở Pháp thì bất thường.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Vâng. Mùa phấn hoa bắt đầu sớm hơn cho cả sồi và bạch dương, nhưng nó không bắt đầu sớm hơn đối với cỏ. <strong>(27) Tôi tự hỏi tại sao lại như vậy (B)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Ở Hà Lan chúng ta có dữ liệu đầy đủ cho cả ba loại thực vật. Vậy nó cho thấy điều gì? Hmm, phấn hoa cỏ và bạch dương chỉ bắt đầu sớm hơn vài ngày, nhưng phấn hoa sồi bắt đầu sớm hơn nhiều, 18 ngày thực tế. <strong>(28) Điều này thật bất thường (A)</strong>. Không có sự khác biệt lớn như vậy ở các nước khác.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Không. Thụy Sĩ là một trường hợp thú vị. Mùa phấn hoa bắt đầu ở đây <strong>(29) sớm hơn trong quá khứ đối với sồi, bạch dương và cỏ (D)</strong>. Vâng, từ 21 ngày đến 14 ngày sớm hơn.</p>\n<p><strong>Elliot:</strong> Vâng, Anh lại cho thấy một bức tranh khác. Vâng, ở đây vấn đề là mùa hè ẩm ướt đã <strong>(30) kéo dài mùa phấn hoa cỏ (C)</strong> từ 5 tuần lên 8 tuần, điều này là tin xấu cho những người bị dị ứng.</p>\n<p><strong>Beth:</strong> Đúng vậy. Chà, tôi nghĩ chúng ta nên xem xét lại.</p>\n<p><strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Đó là kết thúc của Phần 3. Bây giờ bạn có nửa phút để kiểm tra câu trả lời của mình. Chuyển sang Phần 4 trên trang bảy.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2d420098-a7c5-4378-9c90-77262dd2e45a', 'ae246f14-594c-448c-ba6a-8846bb07d5f4', 'radio', 'Questions 1-6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Setlters realised that wooden houses were more dangerous than other types of structure"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "During the 1800s, New Zealand exported wood for use in boat-building."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Plantation-grown wood is generally better for construction than native-forest wood."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Compared to other types of wood, pine has a narrow range of uses."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Demand for housing in New Zealand is predicted to fall in the next few years."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In future, the expansion of New Zealand’s wood industry will depend on its exports."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Settlers realised that wooden houses were more dangerous than other types of structure.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 1,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 3:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…wooden houses arose, supported by the recognition that they were <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">less likely to collapse suddenly during earthquakes</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc cho biết người dân chọn xây nhà gỗ vì chúng </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">ít có khả năng sụp đổ bất ngờ</strong><span class=\"\"> khi có động đất.</span><span class=\"\"> Điều này có nghĩa là chúng được coi là an toàn hơn,</span><span class=\"\"> trái ngược hoàn toàn với nhận định “nguy hiểm hơn” (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">more dangerous</strong><span class=\"\">) trong câu hỏi.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. During the 1800s, New Zealand exported wood for use in boat-building.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 2,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 1 &amp; 3:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">“Early explorers recognised the suitability of… the kauri for constructing <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">sailing vessels</strong>. So from the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">early 1800s</strong>, huge amounts of this type of wood were sold… for that purpose.”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Sailing vessels” chính là tàu thuyền.</span><span class=\"\"> Văn bản xác nhận gỗ kauri đã được xuất khẩu từ đầu thế kỷ 19 để phục vụ mục đích đóng tàu.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Plantation-grown wood is generally better for construction than native-forest wood.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 3 &amp; 4 có nhắc đến việc gỗ đồn điền (pine) hiện nay cung cấp phần lớn nhu cầu gỗ xẻ cho xây dựng.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc chỉ nêu thực tế là gỗ đồn điền đang được dùng nhiều cho xây dựng,</span><span class=\"\"> nhưng </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">không hề có sự so sánh</strong><span class=\"\"> về chất lượng để khẳng định nó “tốt hơn” (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">better</strong><span class=\"\">) so với gỗ rừng tự nhiên.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Compared to other types of wood, pine has a narrow range of uses.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 4,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 5:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“This <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">amazing versatility</strong> has encouraged the development of an integrated forest-products industry…”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Từ khóa </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“amazing versatility”</strong><span class=\"\"> (sự đa năng kinh ngạc) chỉ ra rằng gỗ thông có rất nhiều công dụng khác nhau.</span><span class=\"\"> Điều này phản bác lại ý kiến cho rằng nó có phạm vi sử dụng hạn hẹp (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"189\">narrow range of uses</strong><span class=\"\">).</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Demand for housing in New Zealand is predicted to fall in the next few years.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 1:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“In New Zealand itself, the construction industry… servicing around 20,000 new house starts annually.”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc cung cấp số lượng nhà xây mới hàng năm nhưng </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">không đưa ra dự đoán</strong><span class=\"\"> (predicted) nào về việc nhu cầu này sẽ tăng hay giảm (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">fall</strong><span class=\"\">) trong tương lai gần.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. In future, the expansion of New Zealand’s wood industry will depend on its exports.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6,</span><span class=\"\"> câu cuối:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“Accordingly, the development of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">export market is the key</strong> to the industry’s growth… in decades to come.”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc khẳng định rõ ràng rằng thị trường xuất khẩu chính là “chìa khóa” (the key) cho sự tăng trưởng (expansion/growth) của ngành gỗ trong tương lai.</span></li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f1dcda2e-05ee-4955-9da5-afd4466f44d6', 'b7ede2b9-71ed-42de-aa36-4ae92d763294', 'fillup', 'Questions 5–7', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Complete the flow-chart below.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Write <strong><span style="border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in;">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</span></strong> from the passage for each answer.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; background: white; vertical-align: baseline; text-align: left;" align="center"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Life cycle of fish in the Lizard Island study</span></strong></p>
<table class="MsoNormalTable" style="width: 386.6pt; border-collapse: collapse; mso-yfti-tbllook: 1184; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 0in 0in;" border="0" width="515" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 0; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; height: 19.0pt;">
<td style="border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; padding: 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt; height: 19.0pt;" valign="bottom">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Phase 1:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"> Larval stage</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">takes place in the {open ocean}</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="padding-left: 240px;"> ⬇</p>
<table class="MsoNormalTable" style="width: 386.6pt; border-collapse: collapse; mso-yfti-tbllook: 1184; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 0in 0in;" border="0" width="515" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 0; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; height: 42.85pt;">
<td style="border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; padding: 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt; height: 42.85pt;" valign="bottom">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Phase 2:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"> Juvenile stage</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">takes place close to the {reef}</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">the move from one habitat to anotr is called settlement</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">{mortality} rates are high in the early part of this stage</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="padding-left: 240px;"> ⬇</p>
<table class="MsoNormalTable" style="width: 385.6pt; border-collapse: collapse; mso-yfti-tbllook: 1184; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 0in 0in;" border="0" width="514" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 0; mso-yfti-firstrow: yes; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; height: 12.25pt;">
<td style="border: solid #DDDDDD 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: solid #DDDDDD .75pt; padding: 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt 6.0pt; height: 12.25pt;" valign="bottom">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Phase 3:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"> Adult stage</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>5. Phase 1: Larval stage takes place in the <strong>open ocean</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>open ocean</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;Most coral reef fish have a life cycle consisting of an <strong>open ocean larval phase</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>6. Phase 2: Juvenile stage takes place close to the <strong>reef</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>reef</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;&#8230;followed by a juvenile to adult phase <strong>near the reef</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>7. <strong>Mortality</strong> rates are high in the early part of this stage.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mortality</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;This point is commonly known as &#8216;settlement&#8217;. Not surprisingly, it is also characterised by increased levels of <strong>mortality</strong> in the first 48 hours following settlement&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ad081d1d-d04f-4001-b0b6-f87dba9a0f97', 'ae246f14-594c-448c-ba6a-8846bb07d5f4', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-13', '<p>Answer the questions below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer</p>
<p>Apart from exchange rates, which factor has had a negative impact on New Zealand’s forestry<br />
exports? {shipping costs}</p>
<p>Which part of New Zealand’s economy does the forestry industry rank third in?  {export sector}</p>
<p>According to the New Zealand forestry industry, what could be the size of its workforce by<br />
2025? {60000 people}</p>
<p>What kind of timber product is available in large amounts from renewable forests in New<br />
Zealand? {softwood}</p>
<p>Which aspect of timber production are New Zealand’s main customers increasingly concerned<br />
about? {sustainability}</p>
<p>Outside the southern hemisphere, who are New Zealand forestry’s main competitors? {scandinavian countries}</p>
<p>Which group of products is New Zealand’s forestry industry now having to compete with? {wood substitutes}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Apart from exchange rates, which factor has had a negative impact on New Zealand’s forestry exports?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: shipping costs</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 1: <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…until affected by the exchange fluctuations and <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">shipping costs</strong> of recent years.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài biến động tỷ giá (exchange fluctuations/rates), chi phí vận chuyển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">shipping costs</strong>) là yếu tố gây tác động tiêu cực đến xuất khẩu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Which part of New Zealand’s economy does the forestry industry rank third in?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: export sector</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The forestry industry is New Zealand’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">third largest export sector</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngành lâm nghiệp đứng thứ ba trong <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">lĩnh vực xuất khẩu</strong> của nền kinh tế New Zealand.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. According to the New Zealand forestry industry, what could be the size of its workforce by 2025?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: 60000 people</strong> (hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">60,000</strong>)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 8, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“…by 2025 the forestry sector could be… employing <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">60000 people</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản dự báo đến năm 2025, ngành này có thể tạo việc làm cho <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">60.000 người</strong> (đây chính là quy mô lực lượng lao động – workforce).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. What kind of timber product is available in large amounts from renewable forests in New Zealand?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: softwood</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu 1: <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“One competitive advantage that New Zealand has is its ability to source large quantities of <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">softwood</strong> from renewable forests.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> New Zealand có khả năng cung cấp một lượng lớn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">large quantities/amounts</strong>) loại gỗ mềm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">softwood</strong>) từ các khu rừng có thể tái tạo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Which aspect of timber production are New Zealand’s main customers increasingly concerned about?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: sustainability</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Consumers in several key wood markets are becoming more worried about <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">sustainability</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khách hàng tại các thị trường trọng điểm (main customers) đang ngày càng lo ngại về tính bền vững (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">sustainability</strong>) của việc sản xuất gỗ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Outside the southern hemisphere, who are New Zealand forestry’s main competitors?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: scandinavian countries</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“…and in the northern hemisphere, <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">Scandinavian countries</strong> have all expanded their forest…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Outside the southern hemisphere” tương ứng với “northern hemisphere” (Bán cầu Bắc). Đối thủ chính ở khu vực này là các <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">quốc gia Scandinavia</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Which group of products is New Zealand’s forestry industry now having to compete with?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: wood substitutes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn cuối, câu 1: <em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“…New Zealand faces competition from goods such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">wood substitutes</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài các đối thủ sản xuất gỗ, New Zealand còn phải cạnh tranh với nhóm các sản phẩm thay thế gỗ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">wood substitutes</strong>) như khung thép cho nhà ở.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6d6e4a2a-d808-446e-a3bd-79177793c06d', 'b7ede2b9-71ed-42de-aa36-4ae92d763294', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Complete the notes below.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Write <strong><span style="border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in;">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</span></strong> from the passage for each answer.</span><strong><span style="font-size: 14.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"> </span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Lizard Island study</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Aim:</span></strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">to study the relationship between predator and prey in juvenile reef fish</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Problems:</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">i) time-change of habitat takes place in summer and is linked to the {new moon}</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">ii) working conditions</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">iii) adaptation-difficult to move and settle fish into the {laboratory}</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Method:</span></strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"><span style="color: #15191e;">larval fish are drawn into a special trap with the aid of {artificial light}</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">{predatory fish} <span style="color: #15191e;">are also collected</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo4; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">both undergo trials</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Possible reasons why ‘bigger’ is not always ‘better’:</span></strong></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo5; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">the number and type of predatory fish on the reef can vary from place to place</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"><span style="color: #15191e;">physical features (e.g.</span> <span style="border: none windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in;"><span style="color: #15191e;">{mouth size}</span></span></span><span style="font-family: ''Tahoma'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">) </span><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">affect which prey a predator can eat</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo7; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;"><span style="color: #15191e;">optimal foraging theory suggests that the most common choice of prey should be {medium} </span></span><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">in size</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 115%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">large juvenile fish may swim slowly and so may be targeted more often</span></li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>8. i) time-change of habitat takes place in summer and is linked to the <strong>new moon</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>new moon</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;&#8230;settlement usually occurs within 2–3 days of a <strong>new moon</strong> during the warmer summer months.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>9. iii) adaptation-difficult to move and settle fish into the <strong>laboratory</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>laboratory</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;&#8230;combined with the difficulties associated with working underwater, transporting fish and adapting them to the <strong>laboratory</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>10. larval fish are drawn into a special trap with the aid of <strong>artificial light</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>artificial light</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;We collect the larval fish immediately prior to settlement using purpose-built traps that use <strong>artificial light</strong> to attract&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11. <strong>predatory fish</strong> are also collected.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>predatory fish</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;These fish are subsequently transported to an aquarium, along with <strong>predatory fish</strong>, before being used in a series of aquarium and field-based trials.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>12. physical features (e.g. <strong>mouth size</strong>) affect which prey a predator can eat.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mouth size</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;This relationship is driven by physical characteristics of predators, such as <strong>mouth size</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>13. optimal foraging theory suggests that the most common choice of prey should be <strong>medium</strong> in size.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>medium</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) &#8220;This usually results in a preference for <strong>medium</strong>-sized prey.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('823ef527-520b-4239-9e18-4c04e3d10560', '69369bde-9752-4300-b654-ea15a6f74d3b', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Which paragraph contains the following information? Choose the correct letter, A–I, in boxes14–19.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A reference to studies based on the same level of calorie reduction with different animals", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "A comment that some control monkeys in one study reached an older age than normal for animals of their kind", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Distinctions between the types of food in each study that may have led to a contrast in findings", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Examples of health problems which monkeys on calorie-restricted diets were less likely to get", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "A researcher’s negative opinion of a calorie-restricted diet", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "A reference to the stage in the monkeys’ lives at which research commenced in one study", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>14. a reference to studies based on the same level of calorie reduction with different animals</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;In <strong>mice</strong>, many experiments had come to the same finding: feed them a diet with <strong>30% fewer calories</strong>&#8230; The monkey trials were set up in a similar way: researchers&#8230; <strong>cut it by 30%</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>15. a comment that some control monkeys in one study reached an older age than normal for animals of their kind</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>G</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) &#8220;Indeed, Anderson points out that several of the NIA control monkeys have lived past the age of 40, <strong>far exceeding the 27-year average lifespan</strong> for captive rhesus monkeys.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>16. distinctions between the types of food in each study that may have led to a contrast in findings</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>E</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;The Wisconsin monkeys were given highly processed food high in <strong>sucrose</strong>&#8230; the NIA diet was based on <strong>whole grains, fish oils, and was very low in sugar</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>17. examples of health problems which monkeys on calorie-restricted diets were less likely to get</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) &#8220;&#8230;the lean monkeys were living longer and suffering less from the diseases of ageing: <strong>diabetes, heart disease and brain diseases</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>18. a researcher’s negative opinion of a calorie-restricted diet</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;Rozalyn Anderson&#8230; says the research is not intended as a recommendation of calorie restriction. ‘I find the idea <strong>monumentally unattractive</strong>!’ she says.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>19. a reference to the stage in the monkeys’ lives at which research commenced in one study</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) &#8220;The Wisconsin study began with monkeys in <strong>early adulthood</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7668c03f-691c-4d2b-a607-7f483e7f07d5', '69369bde-9752-4300-b654-ea15a6f74d3b', 'matrix', 'Questions 20–23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements and the list of researchers below. Match each statement with the correct researcher, A, B or C.<br /><em><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</em></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of researchers", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It is good that the two studies took dissimilar approaches", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Neither study used diets that are typical for monkeys.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Calorie restriction is a method of finding out about health issues connected with ageing.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Calorie reduction will have a positive effect on people who have unhealthy diets.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Rozalyn Anderson", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Julie Mattison", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Leonie Heilbronn", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>20. It is good that the two studies took dissimilar approaches.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong> (Rozalyn Anderson)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn I) &#8220;The fact the two studies were set up differently&#8230; — <strong>I think we will gain maximally from that</strong>.’&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>21. Neither study used diets that are typical for monkeys.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong> (Leonie Heilbronn)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) &#8220;However, <strong>neither group had the right notion of a standard diet</strong> according to Leonie Heilbronn&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>22. Calorie restriction is a method of finding out about health issues connected with ageing.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong> (Rozalyn Anderson)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;‘We study it because it is so effective at delaying ageing and <strong>the onset of age-related disease</strong>.’&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>23. Calorie reduction will have a positive effect on people who have unhealthy diets.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B</strong> (Julie Mattison)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) &#8220;Julie Mattison&#8230; observes that <strong>an overweight person who goes to a fast food restaurant every day will obviously benefit</strong> if their calories are cut back by 30%.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('46340d72-1f0b-4b69-af80-e1add7a40b64', '2a74ee27-fa90-4899-8f1a-1a0847b271aa', 'matching', 'Questions 14–19', '', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Write the correct number, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="164">i-viii</strong>, in boxes 14-19 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Official recognition of the importance of natural flood protection"}, {"optionText": "ii. Understanding the positive side of flooding"}, {"optionText": "iii. The consequences of man-made climate change on flooding"}, {"optionText": "iv. The economic implications of flooding"}, {"optionText": "v. Nature’s rapid powers of recovery"}, {"optionText": "vi. Bureaucratic obstacles to natural flood controls"}, {"optionText": "vii. Science leads the way in flood prevention"}, {"optionText": "viii. The only natural defence against flood damage"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A — {iv. The economic implications of flooding}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Floods are the most common and <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">costly</strong>… insurance losses… reached nearly <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">$34 billion</strong>… USA has subsequently <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">spent even more</strong> than that trying to control floods…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A tập trung vào các con số tài chính: thiệt hại kinh tế (costly), số tiền bảo hiểm chi trả ($34 billion) và chi phí chính phủ bỏ ra để xây đập. “Implications” ở đây là những ảnh hưởng/hệ quả về mặt kinh tế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B — {ii. Understanding the positive side of flooding}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…fully appreciated the many <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">beneficial aspects of flooding</strong>. Floods are <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">critical for maintaining and restoring</strong> many of the important services… ensures high levels of <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">diversity</strong>… <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">replenish agricultural land</strong> with key nutrients…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Positive side” tương ứng với “beneficial aspects”. Đoạn này liệt kê hàng loạt lợi ích của lũ: duy trì đa dạng sinh học, bồi đắp phù sa cho đất nông nghiệp và ngăn chặn xói mòn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C — {i. Official recognition of the importance of natural flood protection}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the committee’s findings and recommendations marked the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">first time</strong> that the crucial <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">ecological protections</strong> provided by wetlands and upland forests were <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">explicitly acknowledged</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Official recognition” (Sự công nhận chính thức) tương ứng với việc báo cáo của ủy ban (Galloway Report) lần đầu tiên thừa nhận một cách rõ ràng (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">explicitly acknowledged</em>) vai trò bảo vệ của tự nhiên (đầm lầy, rừng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D — {viii. The only natural defence against flood damage}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Floodplains are the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">sole safeguard</strong> the environment has against these and other harmful effects of floods.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “The only natural defence” (Phòng tuyến tự nhiên duy nhất) khớp hoàn toàn với cụm “<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">sole safeguard</strong>” (lá chắn duy nhất) mà bài nhắc đến khi nói về vùng đất ngập ven sông (floodplains).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E — {v. Nature’s rapid powers of recovery}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…their ecosystems are <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">resilient</strong>… animals <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">immediately exploited</strong> the reconnection with the floodplain.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nói về tính phục hồi (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">resilient</em>) của hệ sinh thái. Ngay khi có lũ trở lại, các loài động thực vật đã ngay lập tức (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">immediately</em>) sinh sôi và tận dụng môi trường này để phục hồi quần thể.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F — {vi. Bureaucratic obstacles to natural flood controls}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">fragmentation and lack of coordination</strong> that has characterized policy… current policy structure gives the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">federal government the most responsibility</strong>… provides <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">little incentive</strong> and few mechanisms for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"221\">county and municipal governments</strong> to help.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Bureaucratic obstacles” (Các rào cản hành chính/quan liêu) chính là sự thiếu phối hợp giữa các cấp chính quyền (Liên bang, Bang, và Địa phương) và cấu trúc chính sách rời rạc khiến việc quản lý lũ gặp khó khăn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8a1391ab-171a-43a9-b712-ef80229cc56b', 'd3317984-005e-4eef-a00d-523830eed947', 'matching', 'Questions 26–30', '', '<p>What comment is made about the seasonal changes in pollen in each of the following European countries?<br>Choose <strong>FIVE</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>European countries</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Austria {information only available for birch pollen}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>France {changes identified for two pollen types only}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Netherlands {greatest change recorded for oak pollen}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Switzerland  {earlier start dates for all pollen types}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>UK {a longer season for grass pollen}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "greatest change recorded for oak pollen"}, {"optionText": "changes identified for two pollen types only"}, {"optionText": "a longer season for grass pollen"}, {"optionText": "earlier start dates for all pollen types"}, {"optionText": "significant change in start date of birch pollen"}, {"optionText": "little difference in start dates"}, {"optionText": "information only available for birch pollen"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fb7d9754-6968-4deb-a8cd-682e2fcdf4d1', '69369bde-9752-4300-b654-ea15a6f74d3b', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p><strong>Agreement between the two studies on calorie restriction in rhesus monkeys</strong></p>
<p>The two studies were in agreement that it is beneficial to cut calories, in terms of health. Monkeys whose calories were restricted suffered fewer diseases that are associated with the {ageing} process. Anderson and Mattison have undertaken research to determine if a calorie-restricted diet increases primates’ {lifespan} Although there is a {conflict} between the two sets of data, Anderson believes they will help researchers reach a better understanding.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>24. Monkeys whose calories were restricted suffered fewer diseases that are associated with the ageing process.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ageing</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn I) &#8220;&#8230;fewer diseases that are associated with the <strong>ageing</strong> process.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>25. Anderson and Mattison have undertaken research to determine if a calorie-restricted diet increases primates’ lifespan.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>lifespan</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn I) &#8220;As to the question of whether calorie restriction extends <strong>lifespan</strong> in primates&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>26. Although there is a conflict between the two sets of data, Anderson believes they will help researchers reach a better understanding.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>conflict</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn I) &#8220;The current data <strong>conflict</strong> will ultimately provide deeper insights&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a0072aba-08be-4aee-b032-4cde7b6f6398', '9ae637df-55dd-4795-a694-400846b5a243', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> topics were the aims of the geography lesson related to?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A global interdependency"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B manufacturing method"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C the environmental impact of trade"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D transport systems"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E the development of writing tools"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear two trainee teachers called Dean and Hannah talking about their recent teaching practice in an elementary school. First you have some time to look at questions 21 to 24 on page five. Now listen carefully and answer questions 21 to 24.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Hi, Dean. Did you have a good weekend?</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Yes, it was good to relax after a whole week of teaching practice. I really enjoyed the experience though.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Yes, so did I. And I think it went well. Anyway, are you okay to talk about the report we’ve got to write on the geography lesson we taught together? I was thinking we could make notes now and then divide the actual writing up between us.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Sure, good idea. Let’s begin with our lesson aim, shall we?</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Right. Well, I know the main one was getting the class to think about how people in different parts of the world are connected to each other through the things they buy and sell.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Yes, we took that from the syllabus for Grade 4. And then we decided to use pencils as our example, because they’re relatively simple in design and everyone’s used a pencil at some time or other. We should include that information too. Right?</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> And we also wanted to get the class thinking about how things are moved around the world in different ways—from the farms and the mines to the factories and then the stores.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> That wasn’t in the core syllabus. I think we added that ourselves.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Yes, I think you’re right.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> (A – <strong>global interdependency</strong>; D – <strong>transport systems</strong>)</span></p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Okay then, the last section of the report contains a post-lesson analysis. We have to mention any problems we identified in our lesson when we taught it. So, any ideas?</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Well, I know we were really satisfied with our handouts and worksheets. We both thought they’d been at just the right level for the class. And I don’t know about you, but I think we worked well as a team.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Absolutely. Neither of us was too dominant, and we supported each other. Personally, the thing I think we didn’t get right was the way we paced things. Some things seemed to be rushed and others seemed to drag out too long. I don’t know how you feel about that.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Hmm, the same as you. If we did the same lesson again, I’d want to make some adjustments to that, but keep the same basic lesson plan. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(E – <strong>the timing</strong>)</span></p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Okay, we see eye to eye on that. But there’s one other thing. At the time I seem to remember we both thought that organizing the children in sets of 6 didn’t work very well, and that pairs would have been better for certain tasks, so that the shy kids got more chance to contribute.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Yes, I remember that too, and we should put it into a report as well. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(B – <strong>the student grouping</strong>)</span></p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the discussion, you have some time to look at questions 25 to 30 on page six. Now listen and answer questions 25 to thirty.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Now, should we go over our lesson plan together before we write the report? It seems ages ago now.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Fine. Well, the whole lesson was based on the production and distribution of pencils. First we gave out the pencils and got the students to decide what they’re made of. Then when they’d come up with all five of the component materials, we talked about which countries produce most of these materials.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> Oh yes, and we got volunteers to come to the front and mark the location of those on a map of the world. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(25. Locate the top <strong>G producers</strong> on a world map)</span> I remember they were really keen to volunteer. We had to stop them from calling the answers out loud!</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Right. Then we brainstormed all the different ways of getting goods from one place to another, and what the advantages and disadvantages of each one would be.</p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> I remember one girl talking about using horses. (26. Discuss the pros and cons of different<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>H methods of transport</strong>)</span> That’s right. She seemed to be a bit stuck in the past. It was hard not to smile.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Yes. After that, we put them in small groups, and each group represented each of the countries on the map. They had to use their atlases to decide an itinerary for sending their raw materials to the USA, specifying the different ports and places on the way there. (27. In groups, discuss countries’ possible <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>A export routes</strong> to the USA)</span></p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> That’s right. And by the time they’d done that, it was break time. And after the break, they had to imagine they were pencil manufacturers in Chicago and fill in details on a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(28) worksheet (E)</strong> </span>about how they dispatch their pencils to different parts of the country.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> Oh yes. Okay. And then we had a class discussion about whether people will still be using pencils in 2050, and whether the design of pencils is likely to change. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(29. Share ideas about the <strong>B future</strong> of pencils)</span></p>\n<p><strong>Hannah:</strong> And to round the lesson off, the kids had to spend 10 minutes planning a short <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) presentation (C talk)</strong> </span>for another class about possible developments.</p>\n<p><strong>Dean:</strong> And that was it. Good. So I’ll write up that part and you…</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 3. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Now turn to Section 4 on page 7.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7cc55feb-a749-41d0-9bac-bf170f996eef', '1f01a018-dd7e-4815-a310-f0d9041db2f2', 'fillup', 'Questions 31 - 40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Calotype photography in Britain and France</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>From Daguerreotype to Calotype</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Daguerreotype was the first commercial photographic process.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Daguerreotype had a problem: the use of copper made it {expensive}.  </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>William Talbot began looking for an alternative approach in the 1840s.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Talbot was not originally a photographer but an artist who specialised in {painting}.  </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Talbot used paper instead of copper.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>These calotype photographs were more {realistic} because they weren’t so sharp.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>French Calotype</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>In 1851, the first society for photographers was created.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Gustave Le Gray became fascinated by calotype photography.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>He carried out experiments and produced the first {enlargements} using a camera.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>He developed equipment that was easier to use outside the {studio}.  </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Calotype became famous because Le Gray produced {books} about it.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>People thought photography was more reliable than drawing.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>It was used to record the work done on old {buildings}.  </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Photography was not ‘art’, according to {critics}.  </p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Photography was thought of as a {science} , so reflected the culture of the 1850s.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The use of new materials, particularly {glass} , led to new techniques.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: THE DEVELOPMENT OF CALOTYPE PHOTOGRAPHY</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Morning everyone. Welcome back to this series of lectures on the development of photography. Last week we looked at a type of photography called daguerreotype, the first commercially successful photographic process. Today, we''re going to look at how this was gradually replaced by a technique called calotype.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Daguerreotype was a major breakthrough, but there were problems with it. In particular, because the image was produced on a copper sheet, it was <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">(Q31) expensive</strong></span> to create each photograph. As a result, during the 1840s, a man named William Talbot began looking for an alternative approach.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Talbot eventually became an influential figure, but he always said he was not a professional photographer. In fact, he trained as an artist. His greatest interest was <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">(Q32) painting</strong></span>, and he only became involved with photography as a secondary interest. Talbot spent many years trying to solve the problems associated with daguerreotype photography. He tried a number of different approaches, and it took some time to find a successful alternative. But in the end, what he did was, instead of producing each photograph on a sheet of copper, he produced them on paper. And at the time, this was a great advance.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Talbot''s technique, which he called calotype photography, had other advantages as well. Maybe the most important was that the pictures themselves weren''t as sharp as the ones produced before. The sharpness had been a problem because it distorted everything, but this new calotype process produced images that were <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"314\">(Q33) realistic</strong></span> compared to all earlier photographs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Calotype photography was invented in Britain, but it was also popular with French photographers. The 1850s were a time of rapid development in France, and photography was used to record these changes. One example of how important photography had become occurred in 1851 when the French government established a society to promote the interests of photographers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Something that hadn''t happened before to begin with, there were five members, and maybe the most important was a man called Gustave Le Gray. Le Gray became increasingly fascinated by the calotype process. Most of all, he wanted to produce different types of image, so began a series of experiments to see how this might be done. His greatest success was when he designed the first camera that was able to create <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"412\">(Q34) enlargements</strong></span>—an important step forward.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Another of Le Gray’s innovations was his work on the size of the equipment necessary to take photographs. Originally, it was very heavy and difficult to move about, but Le Gray made it lighter and smaller. This meant he could take photographs outdoors more easily rather than being limited to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"297\">(Q35) studio</strong></span>, which had sometimes been the case until then.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Le Gray produced numerous photographs during this period and was highly regarded among fellow photographers. But his work also became famous among the general public because he wrote a very popular series of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">(Q36) books</strong></span> describing the calotype process and giving examples of his work. The simple fact was that people liked photography; they thought it was reliable, especially compared to drawing, where the human hand might alter or exaggerate things.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">This had various consequences, one of which was that photography was now often used to record the huge program of renovation work of historical <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">(Q37) buildings</strong></span> in France during the 1850s. \"The camera doesn''t lie,\" so people said. As a result, the calotype process was admired not only by photographers, but increasingly by the government and by mainstream society. However, debate still remained about whether photography could truly be called an art form like sculpture or drawing. Certainly, although the public liked it, in the opinion of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"542\">(Q38) critics</strong></span>, photography could not be compared to other established forms of art.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">So in summary, what can we say about calotype photography during this period? One thing to re-emphasize is that the 1850s were a period of great development in Britain and France. The culture in both countries admired all new technological advances, and photography represented these ideas because it was considered to be a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"324\">(Q39) science</strong></span> by most people. However, photographers didn''t stop experimenting with new materials to improve the quality of their work. Most of all, they were searching for ways to make images more permanent, because calotype photographs tended to fade over time. And in the end, they found that if the image was produced on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"649\">(Q40) glass</strong></span>, it lasted much longer. So calotype photography was slowly replaced by other techniques...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3288f015-f018-4226-9ba7-5183ddd1f225', '521fc6a0-b04b-426e-8a77-721d4568d619', 'matrix', 'Questions 7–14', '', '<p data-start="192" data-end="262">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="218" data-end="225">A–G</strong>, in boxes 7–14 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="264" data-end="309"><strong data-start="264" data-end="270">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "This place has a shop where you can buy most things you will need.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "You are only permitted to make fires during quiet months.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "It is possible to borrow certain items of sports equipment free of charge.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "This campsite never feels crowded.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It can provide cooked meals.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "It has facilities for many different types of watersport.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "It is not far from the sea.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "This is a good place to go to see a variety of animals up close.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. This place has a shop where you can buy most things you will need. — {B} – High Top Holiday Park</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“There’s an on-site supermarket here selling an <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">extensive range of goods</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “On-site supermarket” (siêu thị tại chỗ) và “extensive range of goods” (đa dạng hàng hóa) khớp với ý có thể mua được hầu hết mọi thứ bạn cần.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. You are only permitted to make fires during quiet months. — {D} – Beavers’ Brook Campsite</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Campfires are allowed</strong> outside of <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">peak season</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Outside of peak season” (ngoài mùa cao điểm) chính là các tháng yên tĩnh (quiet months) trong năm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. It is possible to borrow certain items of sports equipment free of charge. — {G} – Dartvale Campsite</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Table tennis bats and badminton racquets are available <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">at no cost</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “At no cost” (không tốn phí) đồng nghĩa với “free of charge”. “Bats” và “racquets” là các thiết bị thể thao (sports equipment).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. This campsite never feels crowded. — {A} – Swallow’s Nest</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Swallow’s Nest only has a few pitches and limits numbers, so <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">everyone always gets a lot of space</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc giới hạn số lượng người và đảm bảo ai cũng có nhiều không gian riêng giúp khu cắm trại này không bao giờ có cảm giác đông đúc (crowded).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. It can provide cooked meals. — {F} – Westlands Park</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“For those who don’t want to prepare food, the centre offers an excellent selection of <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">hot dishes at midday</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Hot dishes” (các món nóng) phục vụ vào giữa ngày chính là các bữa ăn đã được nấu chín (cooked meals).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. It has facilities for many different types of watersport. — {B} – High Top Holiday Park</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In high season, visitors can enjoy the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">heated outdoor swimming pool</strong>… More sedentary types can watch birds from afar in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">bird hide</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lưu ý:</strong> Đáp án gốc của bạn ghi là <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">B</strong>, tuy nhiên nếu xét về “nhiều loại thể thao dưới nước” (different types of watersport) thì đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">G</strong> (Dartvale) có vẻ khớp hơn với “windsurfing and kayaking”. Bạn hãy kiểm tra lại kỹ văn bản gốc của đề nhé!</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. It is not far from the sea. — {D} – Beavers’ Brook Campsite</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The pitches are very sheltered from the breezes that occasionally blow from the <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">nearby coast</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Nearby coast” (bờ biển gần đó) xác nhận khu này không xa biển.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. This is a good place to go to see a variety of animals up close. — {C} – Lanehill Camping Site</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It’s only 100 metres away from a <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">real farmyard</strong>, so you’ll be greeted by <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">ducks and sheep</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc nằm sát một nông trại thực thụ giúp du khách dễ dàng quan sát các loài động vật ở khoảng cách gần.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('291c7444-c425-4613-b358-b2751af5c684', 'ee1d1bdc-350a-4cc7-9e2f-e548d61f7e2f', 'radio', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the views of the writer. <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts what the writer thinks. <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to know what the writer’s point of view is.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The DOC project to remove feral cats helped stop the decline in Otago skink numbers."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Parasite infections are having a serious effect on the physical condition of wild skinks"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The best possible habitat for the conservation of skinks is unknown"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is possible that skinks used to have larger numbers of young than they do now"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The survival of the common species of skink may soon be at risk"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32. The DOC project to remove feral cats helped stop the decline in Otago skink numbers.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;<strong>Despite the capture of hundreds of cats, skinks showed no signs of recovery; indeed, there were further declines.</strong>&#8220;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dự án không những không giúp đỡ mà số lượng skink còn tiếp tục giảm, mâu thuẫn với câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>33. Parasite infections are having a serious effect on the physical condition of wild skinks.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) &#8220;<strong>Although no direct health implications have been detected</strong> the trend is a concern&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Hiện tại, <strong>chưa phát hiện</strong> ra ảnh hưởng trực tiếp nghiêm trọng nào đến sức khỏe của skink hoang dã.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. The best possible habitat for the conservation of skinks is unknown.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) &#8220;<strong>Even if we had the answer to the eradication of predators, we haven&#8217;t a clue to the habitat we should be recreating for the skinks</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định họ không biết môi trường sống nào là tốt nhất cho việc bảo tồn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. It is possible that skinks used to have larger numbers of young than they do now.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Văn bản chỉ so sánh khả năng sinh sản <strong>giữa các loài skink hiện tại</strong> (grand/Otago sinh ít hơn loài phổ biến) nhưng <strong>không so sánh</strong> số lượng con non của cùng một loài qua các thời kỳ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>36. The survival of the common species of skink may soon be at risk.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;<strong>As more is learned about the size of skink populations, it becomes clear that even common species may be facing a doubtful future</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả cho rằng ngay cả các loài phổ biến cũng đang đối mặt với nguy cơ trong tương lai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5acad33e-1710-46fe-abd9-022895e93060', 'ee1d1bdc-350a-4cc7-9e2f-e548d61f7e2f', 'matching', 'Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words. Choose the correct answer and move it into the gap.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Characteristics of New Zealand skinks</strong></p>\n<p>There are three kinds of reptiles in New Zealand: the tuatara, the gecko and the skink. Skinks are easily distinguished from these other natives by their shiny scale and  {small legs} In common with other reptiles, the grand and Otago species of skink have cold blood and therefore {body heat} must be externally controlled. They are unique in that they do not require a long  {winter sleep} Many species are yet to be identified, and identification depends primarily on their {location} and extremely small physical differences. In {captivity}, skinks may potentially live for about 30 years.</p>\n<p> </p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "eggs"}, {"optionText": "location"}, {"optionText": "hooded eyes"}, {"optionText": "the wild"}, {"optionText": "body heat"}, {"optionText": "winter sleep"}, {"optionText": "captivity"}, {"optionText": "live young"}, {"optionText": "digestive process"}, {"optionText": "small legs"}, {"optionText": "warmer areas"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. Skinks are easily distinguished from these other natives by their shiny scale and -&gt; J. small legs</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;With their gleaming scales, long bodies and often surprisingly <strong>short limbs</strong>, skinks are instantly recognisable.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> &#8220;Short limbs&#8221; (chi/chân ngắn) đồng nghĩa với <strong>small legs</strong> (chân nhỏ).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. In common with other reptiles, the grand and Otago species of skink have cold blood and therefore -&gt; E. body heat</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;Skinks, being reptiles, need to regulate their temperature, and lie on sunny rocks to absorb <strong>heat</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Là động vật máu lạnh, chúng cần điều chỉnh nhiệt độ/hấp thụ <strong>body heat</strong> (nhiệt độ cơ thể) từ bên ngoài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. They are unique in that they do not require a long -&gt; F. winter sleep</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;&#8230;the grand and Otago are the only kinds that <strong>do not hibernate through winter</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> &#8220;Hibernate through winter&#8221; (ngủ đông) đồng nghĩa với việc không cần một giấc ngủ đông dài (<strong>winter sleep</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. Many species are yet to be identified, and identification depends primarily on their -&gt; B. location</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;<strong>Identification depends on where specimens are found</strong>, and such minutiae as the number of scales on their toes.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc nhận dạng phụ thuộc vào nơi tìm thấy (location).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. In -&gt; G. captivity, skinks may potentially live for about 30 years.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) &#8220;&#8230;although in <strong>zoos or research centres</strong> they can live beyond thirty.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vườn thú và trung tâm nghiên cứu là các hình thức <strong>nuôi nhốt</strong> (<strong>captivity</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('676c2441-1431-4f22-b9d5-9054d6b1463d', '9ae637df-55dd-4795-a694-400846b5a243', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23–24', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>problems do Dean and Hannah identify in their lesson?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A the materials"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B the student grouping"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C the lesson structure"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D the teacher coordination"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E the timing"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a24615c2-76ce-4efe-98ec-d7c4661d1d53', '6e5469e2-9937-480d-a7f3-d13a4a7fef42', 'radio', 'Questions 1-6', '', '<p id="p-rc_a3450196707ef0f1-23" data-path-to-node="4,0,0"><span class="citation-334 citation-335">Choose</span><strong data-path-to-node="4,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-334 citation-335"> TRUE</span></strong><span class="citation-334 citation-335 citation-end-335">: if the statement agrees with the information,<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="5"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-334 citation-end-334"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="6"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node="4,1,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-332 citation-333">FALSE</span></strong><span class="citation-332 citation-333 citation-end-333">: if the statement c<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="7"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-332 citation-end-332">ontradicts the inform<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="8"><!----></sup></span>ation,<strong data-path-to-node="4,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong>: if there is no information on this</p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p> </p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "The lack of interest in the fine arts in Victoria in the 1850s was due to a gold rush taking place."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Victoria was the poorest area of Australia before the gold rush."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "There was disagreement on the purpose of the public art museum in the Melbourne Public Library."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "The casts in the Museum of Art were arranged according to where they came from."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "The Intercolonial Exhibition was housed in a pre-existing permanent exhibition centre in Melbourne."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "True"}, {"option_text": "False"}, {"option_text": "Not Given"}], "question": "Critical comment on Australian art was improved by the Intercolonial Exhibition."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d8a1c15a-92b0-4fa5-ab26-c817e335dc2b', '80b1efc2-3037-41e4-a76d-74273fc62a5b', 'fillup', 'Questions 15–21', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15–21 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Eye wash stations</strong></span></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9631%; height: 520.273px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 49.9285%;"> <col style="width: 49.9285%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 70.3906px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Types available</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<ul>
<li data-start="312" data-end="329">
<p>{plumbed}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="330" data-end="345">
<p>stand-alone</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 129.16px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Design requirements</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<ul>
<li data-start="380" data-end="451">
<p>must supply a constant flow of liquid for a period of {fifteen minutes}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="452" data-end="522">
<p>eyewash heads can stay open to leave the user’s {hands} free</p>
</li>
<li data-start="523" data-end="570">
<p>heads should have protective covers on them</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 70.3906px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Liquid temperature</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<ul data-start="604" data-end="692">
<li data-start="604" data-end="692">
<p>needs to be {tepid} to ensure the user flushes for the required length of time</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 109.551px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Location</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<ul>
<li data-start="716" data-end="792">
<p>should be placed in an area that can be reached in {10 seconds} or less</p>
</li>
<li data-start="793" data-end="849">
<p>should not require the use of {stairs} to reach</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 70.3906px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Maintenance (mains water system)</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<ul data-start="897" data-end="966">
<li data-start="897" data-end="966">
<p>should be monitored on a weekly basis to check it works correctly</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 70.3906px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Maintenance (gravity-fed system)</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; border-width: 2px;">
<ul data-start="1014" data-end="1103">
<li data-start="1014" data-end="1103">
<p>should be maintained in accordance with the information provided in the {product manual}</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Types available: {plumbed} / stand-alone</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“There are two kinds of eye wash station – a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">plumbed</strong> eye wash station… and a gravity-feed eye wash station, sometimes referred to as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">stand-alone</strong> device…”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc liệt kê hai loại trạm rửa mắt: loại nối trực tiếp với nguồn nước (plumbed) và loại tự cấp nước (stand-alone/gravity-feed).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Must supply a constant flow of liquid for a period of {fifteen minutes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…at a volume of not less than 1.5 litres per minute for <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">fifteen minutes</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Yêu cầu thiết kế là phải cung cấp dòng chảy liên tục trong vòng 15 phút.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Eyewash heads can stay open to leave the user’s {hands} free</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“They are also designed to… remain in operation without the worker’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">hands</strong> on the eyewash heads.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thiết bị được thiết kế để hoạt động tự động sau khi kích hoạt, giúp người dùng rảnh tay (hands free) để giữ mắt mở khi rửa.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Liquid temperature: needs to be {tepid}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is recommended that the liquid is <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">tepid</strong> – liquid that is too hot or too cold will inhibit workers from rinsing…”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhiệt độ nước cần ở mức ấm vừa phải (tepid) để đảm bảo người bị nạn có thể rửa đủ thời gian quy định mà không bị khó chịu do quá nóng hay quá lạnh.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Location: should be placed in an area that can be reached in {10 seconds} or less</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is recommended that a worker be able to access the equipment in no more than <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">ten seconds</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thời gian tiếp cận thiết bị khẩn cấp tối đa là 10 giây (10 seconds).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. should not require the use of {stairs} to reach</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It should also be located on the same floor as the hazard (no <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">stairs</strong> to get from the work station to the emergency equipment).”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trạm rửa mắt phải nằm cùng tầng với khu vực nguy hiểm, không được có cầu thang bộ (stairs) cản trở việc di chuyển khẩn cấp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Maintenance: should be maintained in accordance with the information provided in the {product manual}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…refer to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">product manual</strong> for further details.”</em> (Đoạn 6)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đối với hệ thống tự cấp nước (self-contained/gravity-fed), việc bảo trì và thay nước cần tuân theo hướng dẫn trong sách hướng dẫn sản phẩm (product manual).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('331b34fb-a1ac-4d92-aa7d-538ee3a6660a', '80b1efc2-3037-41e4-a76d-74273fc62a5b', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–27', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 22–27 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" role="text"><strong data-start="262" data-end="316">Risk factors of working in a food processing plant</strong></span></p>
<p><span role="text"><strong data-start="322" data-end="345">Injuries caused by:</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="346" data-end="579">
<li data-start="346" data-end="433">
<p>remaining in uncomfortable {positions} resulting from working in a confined space</p>
</li>
<li data-start="434" data-end="502">
<p>continual movements such as {twisting} and extending the arms</p>
</li>
<li data-start="503" data-end="579">
<p>{standing} for long periods, which can cause damage to the lower back</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span role="text"><strong data-start="590" data-end="613">Possible solutions:</strong></span></p>
<p><span role="text"><strong data-start="620" data-end="633">Equipment</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="634" data-end="774">
<li data-start="634" data-end="701">
<p>use of foot rails will allow workers to shift their body weight</p>
</li>
<li data-start="702" data-end="774">
<p>use of {anti-fatigue matting} will eliminate the need for workers to reach up</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span role="text"><strong data-start="786" data-end="803">Varying tasks</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="804" data-end="989">
<li data-start="804" data-end="877">
<p>{job rotation} can enable workers to change tasks at regular intervals</p>
</li>
<li data-start="878" data-end="929">
<p>lack of variety brings on tiredness and boredom</p>
</li>
<li data-start="930" data-end="989">
<p>alternatively, workers could have regular {rest periods}</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Remaining in uncomfortable {positions} resulting from working in a confined space</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…space limitations require workers to adopt and maintain <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">awkward positions</strong> which restrict their flexibility.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Confined space” (không gian hạn chế) tương ứng với “space limitations”. Việc phải duy trì các tư thế không thoải mái (awkward/uncomfortable) chính là các vị trí/tư thế (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"182\">positions</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Continual movements such as {twisting} and extending the arms</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…highly repetitive movements of both arms… including reaching forward and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">twisting</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Continual movements” tương ứng với “highly repetitive movements”. “Extending the arms” tương ứng với “reaching forward”. Hành động còn lại được nhắc đến là vặn người (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"180\">twisting</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. {standing} for long periods, which can cause damage to the lower back</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Prolonged standing</strong> on a hard floor puts workers at high risk for <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">lower back injury</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc đứng trong thời gian dài (prolonged standing) là nguyên nhân gây ra chấn thương vùng lưng dưới (lower back injury).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Use of {anti-fatigue matting} will eliminate the need for workers to reach up</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Problems caused by prolonged standing can be reduced by the use of <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">anti-fatigue matting</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù câu hỏi có chút gây nhiễu ở vế sau, nhưng giải pháp cho việc đứng lâu trên sàn cứng chính là thảm chống mỏi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">anti-fatigue matting</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. {job rotation} can enable workers to change tasks at regular intervals</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the system of <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">job rotation</strong>… enables workers to move between <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">different tasks at fixed periods</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “At regular intervals” (định kỳ) tương ứng với “at fixed periods”. Phương pháp xoay chuyển công việc chính là <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">job rotation</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Alternatively, workers could have regular {rest periods}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If changing the system in this way is not possible, it is beneficial to schedule <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">rest periods</strong> for every hour of work…”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Alternatively” (một cách khác/thay vào đó) dẫn dắt đến giải pháp dự phòng là sắp xếp các khoảng nghỉ ngơi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">rest periods</strong>) đều đặn mỗi giờ.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b5c0d131-1b29-44ba-adfb-4f51519c6140', '1d23c0ae-dbfb-44b5-8022-b77f2eceef29', 'matrix', 'Questions 28–31', '', '<p data-start="145" data-end="196">Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p data-start="198" data-end="269">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="224" data-end="231">A–G</strong>, in boxes 28–31 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a description of how interest in the cinema was promoted through other media", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "reasons for a drop in popularity of the cinema", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "a description of how a company took a risk that paid off", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "an account of how business expertise was drawn from other fields", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. A description of how interest in the cinema was promoted through other media — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The production of glamour was helped along by <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">newspapers and magazines</strong> in many countries around the world…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Other media” (các phương tiện truyền thông khác) ở đây chính là báo chí và tạp chí. Việc sử dụng chúng để tạo ra vẻ hào nhoáng cho các ngôi sao là cách để thúc đẩy sự quan tâm (promoted interest) của công chúng đối với điện ảnh.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Reasons for a drop in popularity of the cinema — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…an excess of musicals led to <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">audience indifference</strong>. And problems with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">US economy</strong> in general at that time… millions of people… had <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">no extra money to spend on movie tickets</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G liệt kê hai lý do chính dẫn đến sự sụt giảm mức độ phổ biến (drop in popularity): một là do khán giả thờ ơ vì có quá nhiều phim ca nhạc, hai là do nền kinh tế suy thoái khiến mọi người không có tiền mua vé.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. A description of how a company took a risk that paid off — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…Warner Brothers decided to <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">take a chance and back a movie with sound</strong>… The result was <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">The Jazz Singer</strong>, which made <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">millions</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Take a chance” tương ứng với “take a risk” (mạo hiểm). Việc Warner Brothers đầu tư vào phim có âm thanh (trong khi các hãng khác từ chối vì chi phí thiết bị đắt đỏ) đã mang lại lợi nhuận khổng lồ (paid off).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. An account of how business expertise was drawn from other fields — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Most of the early film moguls came into film production via <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">other commercial activities</strong> as diverse as <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">theatre ownership and scrap-dealing</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những ông trùm điện ảnh đầu tiên mang kinh nghiệm/chuyên môn kinh doanh (business expertise) từ các lĩnh vực khác như sở hữu rạp hát hay buôn bán phế liệu vào ngành sản xuất phim.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e1498005-1e11-41a5-ab5a-15a3c4681f02', '6e5469e2-9937-480d-a7f3-d13a4a7fef42', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="33">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 7-13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0">Displaying Art in Melbourne</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Museum of Art</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p>Professor Frederick McCoy favoured {education} as the main purpose of the museum</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>1861: Sculpture Gallery opened within museum – in restricted {space}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>{cards} provided detail about each museum exhibit</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">National Gallery</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p>established 1863</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>gallery received financial support from {government} for new picture</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>style of art – {contemporary}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>admission – {free}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>art that was considered to be educational was moved to a special room in 1870</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>the public was expected to protect the art collection from {theft}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Professor Frederick McCoy favoured {education} as the main purpose of the museum.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Frederick McCoy… suggested placing a museum, focused on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">education</strong> of citizens about art…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giáo sư McCoy đề xuất thành lập bảo tàng với mục tiêu trọng tâm là giáo dục người dân về nghệ thuật.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. 1861: Sculpture Gallery opened within museum – in restricted {space}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The Sculpture Gallery, although crammed into a limited <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">space</strong> in the Museum of Art…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “restricted” (bị hạn chế) trong đề bài tương ứng với “limited” trong bài đọc. Nơi trưng bày các bức tượng nằm trong một không gian hạn chế.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. {cards} provided detail about each museum exhibit.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Visitors… learned about individual works by reading the written information on <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">cards</strong> accompanying each object.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông tin chi tiết về từng hiện vật được trình bày trên các tấm thẻ đi kèm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Gallery received financial support from {government} for new picture.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…in 1863 the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">government</strong> of Victoria gave one thousand pounds for the creation of a public picture gallery…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Financial support” (hỗ trợ tài chính) chính là số tiền 1000 bảng mà chính phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">government</strong>) đã cấp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Style of art – {contemporary}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…creation of a public picture gallery which was to display examples of <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">contemporary</strong> art.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phong cách nghệ thuật được trưng bày tại phòng triển lãm mới này là nghệ thuật đương đại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">contemporary</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Admission – {free}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“This new public picture gallery… was <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">free</strong> to visit.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Admission” (phí vào cửa) ở đây là miễn phí (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">free</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. The public was expected to protect the art collection from {theft}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…it was decided that the public’s care and attention would safeguard it from <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">theft</strong> and damage.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Protect” đồng nghĩa với “safeguard”. Công chúng được kỳ vọng sẽ giúp bảo vệ các bộ sưu tập khỏi bị trộm cắp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">theft</strong>) và hư hại.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('79a8bab7-b1fb-4b8f-bb15-9c799ec808cd', '1d23c0ae-dbfb-44b5-8022-b77f2eceef29', 'matching', 'Questions 32–37', '', '<p data-start="579" data-end="642">Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong data-start="627" data-end="634">A–I</strong>, below.</p>
<p data-start="644" data-end="715">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="670" data-end="677">A–I</strong>, in boxes 32–37 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "spending money on developing the sets."}, {"optionText": "producing movies that had little to do with everyday life."}, {"optionText": "encouraging actors in the theatre to try working in film."}, {"optionText": "making movies that were longer."}, {"optionText": "making movies that would be successful commercially."}, {"optionText": "promoting a certain image."}, {"optionText": "producing movies with sound."}, {"optionText": "deciding to film in the Los Angeles area."}, {"optionText": "getting important roles in the theatre."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Adolph Zukor was responsible for", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "The possibility of paying employees less money was one of the reasons for", "correctAnswer": "H"}, {"questionPart": "Studios in the US were more confident than those in other countries about", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "Hollywood studios built up interest in their actors by assisting them in", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "Film-makers set out to attract adults and children by", "correctAnswer": "B"}, {"questionPart": "The need to invest in costly equipment deterred many film-makers from", "correctAnswer": "G"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Adolph Zukor was responsible for — {C} encouraging actors in the theatre to try working in film.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Adolph Zukor… gradually he and other entrepreneurs <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">attracted famous stage actors away from the stage and onto the screen</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Adolph Zukor là một trong những người đầu tiên thu hút các diễn viên kịch nói (stage actors) chuyển sang đóng phim điện ảnh (onto the screen).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. The possibility of paying employees less money was one of the reasons for — {H} deciding to film in the Los Angeles area.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“For several reasons, New York came to be replaced by Hollywood… the area was also a source of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">cheaper labour</strong> than could be found in New York.”</em> (Đoạn B)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một trong những lý do khiến Hollywood (vùng Los Angeles) trở thành trung tâm điện ảnh thay thế New York là nhờ nguồn nhân công rẻ hơn (cheaper labour/paying less money).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Studios in the US were more confident than those in other countries about — {E} making movies that would be successful commercially.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Studios could make film after film in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">sure knowledge that American box office revenues alone would produce substantial profits</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn C)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sure knowledge” tương ứng với “confident”. Các studio Mỹ tự tin hơn vì thị trường nội địa khổng lồ đảm bảo họ sẽ có lợi nhuận (commercial success/profits) mà chưa cần tính đến doanh thu nước ngoài.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Hollywood studios built up interest in their actors by assisting them in — {F} promoting a certain image.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The studios were adept at <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">creating an aura of glamour</strong> around movies, and stars were the main carriers of this aura.”</em> (Đoạn E)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các hãng phim rất giỏi trong việc xây dựng “hào quang” (aura of glamour) cho các ngôi sao, tức là thúc đẩy một hình ảnh (image) nhất định để thu hút công chúng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Film-makers set out to attract adults and children by — {B} producing movies that had little to do with everyday life.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Film-makers focused on <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">family audiences</strong>… so <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">escapism</strong> was the order of the day… movies offered an <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">escape from the problems of normal living</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn E)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Family audiences” bao gồm cả người lớn và trẻ em. Để thu hút họ, các nhà làm phim chọn lối “thoát ly thực tại” (escapism), tạo ra những bộ phim ít liên quan đến những rắc rối của cuộc sống đời thường (normal living/everyday life).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The need to invest in costly equipment deterred many filmmakers from — {G} producing movies with sound.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Major studios had so far <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">turned their backs on the idea</strong> because of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">cost of installing expensive equipment</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn F)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Turned their backs on” tương ứng với “deterred” (ngăn cản/làm nản lòng). Việc phải đầu tư thiết bị đắt tiền đã khiến nhiều nhà làm phim ban đầu không dám sản xuất phim có âm thanh (movies with sound).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7466084d-cb0a-4237-aa44-f3cb6f93fdb7', '9ae637df-55dd-4795-a694-400846b5a243', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p>Complete the flow – chart below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, A-H</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 16.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Geography lesson plan: student activities</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Examine a pencil and discuss where the component materials come from</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Locate the top {G producers}  on a world map</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Discuss the pros and cons of different {H methods of transport}</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">In groups, discuss countries'' possible {A export routes} to the USA</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Complete a {E worksheet}  about pencil distribute a within the USA.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Share ideas about the {B future}  of pencils.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Prepare a {C talk} </span></p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A export routes"}, {"optionText": "B future"}, {"optionText": "C talk"}, {"optionText": "D homework"}, {"optionText": "E worksheet"}, {"optionText": "F history"}, {"optionText": "G producers"}, {"optionText": "H methods of transport"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('af2c25e9-da9d-488d-a960-c7bbafbba60a', 'e2aa4c06-dddd-4069-ad2d-20f3cf957cbd', 'radio', 'Questions 21–26', NULL, '<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Farmers’ attitudes to new developments in agriculture</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "the location of the farms"}, {"content": "the number of farmers"}, {"content": "the types of farming"}], "question": "What does Dr Owen advise Joel to include in the title of his project?   "}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "to see the farmers’ workplaces"}, {"content": "to limit the time he spends on the project"}, {"content": "to get fuller answers"}], "question": "Why has Joel decided to do face-to-face interviews?  "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "by showing them a series of pictures. "}, {"content": "by asking them open questions. "}, {"content": "by sending them a checklist in advance."}], "question": "Joel agrees to investigate how farmers get information on new developments "}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "much of it is irrelevant.  "}, {"content": "it is often insufficient for farmers’ needs."}, {"content": "the wording is sometimes unclear."}], "question": "Concerning government communication with farmers, the speakers agree that "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "leave investment decisions to their accountants. "}, {"content": "have too little time to calculate the costs of new methods. "}, {"content": "are reluctant to spend money on improvements."}], "question": "According to Joel’s reading about the cost of making changes, many British farmers "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "are usually reluctant to make changes. "}, {"content": "make changes based on limited research. "}, {"content": "want plenty of evidence before they make changes."}], "question": "The survey of Australian sheep farmers found that most of them "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a student called Joel talking to his tutor about his research into farmers’ attitudes towards new developments in agriculture. First you have some time to look at questions 21 to 26 on page five. Now listen carefully and answer questions 21 to 26.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Dr Owen, come in, Joel. Right, so how’s your research going? You’re looking at how farmers feel about new technology in agriculture, aren’t you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span data-path-to-node=\"5,0\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Well, actually, it’s more general than that. </span><span class=\"citation-184\">I’m looking at their attitudes to a variety of new developments in agriculture. </span></p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Bạn sẽ nghe một sinh viên tên là Joel nói chuyện với gia sư của mình về nghiên cứu của cậu ấy về thái độ của nông dân đối với các phát triển mới trong nông nghiệp. Đầu tiên, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 21 đến 26 trên trang năm. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe cẩn thận và trả lời các câu hỏi 21 đến 26.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Tiến sĩ Owen, mời vào, Joel. Đúng rồi, nghiên cứu của bạn thế nào rồi? Bạn đang xem xét việc nông dân cảm thấy thế nào về công nghệ mới trong nông nghiệp, phải không?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2\"><strong>Joel:</strong> À, thực ra, nó tổng quát hơn thế. Tôi đang xem xét thái độ của họ đối với nhiều phát triển mới khác nhau trong nông nghiệp.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Okay. Have you got a title for the project yet?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong>Joel:</strong> I was thinking of something simple, like ‘Farmers’ attitudes towards the adoption of new farming practices’.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><span data-path-to-node=\"9,0\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Hmm, that’s possibly a bit too general. I think the title needs to be a bit more specific. What kind of farming will you be looking at? Well, that’ll vary actually, but I want to speak to each of the ten farmers in my sample, so I’ve chosen farms which are all in the same region. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"9,2\"><span class=\"citation-183\">Okay, well, I’d specify </span><strong><span class=\"citation-183\">(21) where</span></strong><span class=\"citation-183\"> they are then. </span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Right, I’ll amend the title to do that. Okay.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Được rồi. Bạn đã có tiêu đề cho dự án chưa?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Tôi đang nghĩ về một cái gì đó đơn giản, như ‘Thái độ của nông dân đối với việc áp dụng các phương pháp canh tác mới’.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Hmm, có lẽ điều đó hơi quá chung chung. Tôi nghĩ tiêu đề cần cụ thể hơn một chút. Bạn sẽ xem xét loại hình canh tác nào? À, thực ra điều đó sẽ khác nhau, nhưng tôi muốn nói chuyện với mỗi người trong số mười nông dân trong mẫu của tôi, vì vậy tôi đã chọn các trang trại đều ở cùng một khu vực. Được rồi, vậy thì bạn nên chỉ rõ <strong>(21) nơi</strong> chúng ở.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,3\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Phải, tôi sẽ chỉnh sửa tiêu đề để làm điều đó. Được rồi.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Is there any particular reason why you’ve decided to do face to face interviews? It’ll be quite time consuming, won’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><span data-path-to-node=\"13,0\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Yes, and I did consider doing telephone interviews for that reason, especially as it’s unnecessary for me to actually see the places where they work. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"13,2\"><span class=\"citation-182\">It’s just that, in my experience, a lot of farmers don’t like talking on the phone, so they’ll be more likely to talk </span><strong><span class=\"citation-182\">(22) freely</span></strong><span class=\"citation-182\"> if I see them in person. </span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Yes, you’re probably right. Good. Then the first thing I want to investigate is how the farmers actually find out about new developments in agriculture that they might want to adopt—what sources they use. Right, so how are you going to do this?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Well, I could make a checklist of sources of information for them to look at in advance, so they could tick off the ones they actually use—things like farming magazines, farm product advertisements, television and the internet, and so on.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><span data-path-to-node=\"16,0\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> It might be more useful to ask them rather than show them a list. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"16,2\"><span class=\"citation-181\">A spontaneous response to one or two </span><strong><span class=\"citation-181\">(23) open questions</span></strong><span class=\"citation-181\"> might give you a more accurate picture. </span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Alright, I’ll do that then. Now talk me through some of the other issues you want to cover.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Có lý do cụ thể nào khiến bạn quyết định phỏng vấn trực tiếp không? Sẽ khá tốn thời gian, phải không?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Vâng, và tôi đã cân nhắc việc phỏng vấn qua điện thoại vì lý do đó, đặc biệt vì tôi không cần thiết phải thực sự đến xem nơi họ làm việc. Chỉ là, theo kinh nghiệm của tôi, nhiều nông dân không thích nói chuyện qua điện thoại, vì vậy họ sẽ có nhiều khả năng nói chuyện <strong>(22) thoải mái</strong> hơn nếu tôi gặp họ trực tiếp.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Vâng, có lẽ bạn nói đúng. Tốt. Vậy điều đầu tiên tôi muốn điều tra là làm thế nào nông dân thực sự tìm ra những phát triển mới trong nông nghiệp mà họ có thể muốn áp dụng—những nguồn nào họ sử dụng. Được rồi, vậy bạn sẽ làm điều này như thế nào?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,3\"><strong>Joel:</strong> À, tôi có thể tạo một danh sách kiểm tra các nguồn thông tin để họ xem trước, để họ có thể đánh dấu vào những nguồn họ thực sự sử dụng—những thứ như tạp chí nông nghiệp, quảng cáo sản phẩm nông nghiệp, truyền hình và internet, v.v.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,4\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Có lẽ sẽ hữu ích hơn nếu hỏi họ thay vì đưa cho họ một danh sách. Một phản ứng tự nhiên đối với một hoặc hai <strong>(23) câu hỏi mở</strong> có thể cung cấp cho bạn một bức tranh chính xác hơn.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,5\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Được rồi, tôi sẽ làm như vậy. Bây giờ hãy nói cho tôi nghe về một số vấn đề khác mà bạn muốn đề cập.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><span data-path-to-node=\"19,0\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Well, there’s the way the government communicates with farmers. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"19,2\"><span class=\"citation-180\">Right, well, one thing is farmers complain that the government sends out the same information to all of them, whether they’re poultry farmers or dairy farmers or arable farmers, so they get all this information but </span><strong><span class=\"citation-180\">(24) Half of It</span></strong><span class=\"citation-180\"> doesn’t actually apply to them. </span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><span data-path-to-node=\"20,0\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Exactly, so you could look at that. Right, then I wanted to look at attitudes of British farmers to the cost of making any changes on their farms. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"20,2\"><span class=\"citation-179\">According to articles I’ve read, farmers in Britain aren’t in principle against investing money in new machinery and new practices, but they’re actually just </span><strong><span class=\"citation-179\">(25) Too busy</span></strong><span class=\"citation-179\"> to work out what the financial implications are. </span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Yes, and a lot of them don’t seem to consider getting financial advice from their accountants about it either. Right.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Dr Owen:</strong> À, có cách chính phủ giao tiếp với nông dân. Đúng, một điều là nông dân phàn nàn rằng chính phủ gửi cùng một thông tin cho tất cả họ, cho dù họ là nông dân nuôi gia cầm, bò sữa hay nông dân trồng trọt, vì vậy họ nhận được tất cả thông tin này nhưng <strong>(24) một nửa</strong> trong số đó thực sự không áp dụng cho họ.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Chính xác, vậy bạn có thể xem xét điều đó. Đúng, sau đó tôi muốn xem xét thái độ của nông dân Anh đối với chi phí thực hiện bất kỳ thay đổi nào trên trang trại của họ. Theo các bài báo tôi đã đọc, nông dân ở Anh về nguyên tắc không phản đối việc đầu tư tiền vào máy móc và phương pháp mới, nhưng họ thực sự <strong>(25) quá bận</strong> để tính toán ý nghĩa tài chính là gì.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Vâng, và nhiều người trong số họ dường như cũng không xem xét việc nhận lời khuyên tài chính từ kế toán của họ về vấn đề đó. Đúng.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><span data-path-to-node=\"23,0\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> There’s also been some research in Australia on sheep rearing practices. I can give you the reference if you like. Basically, it appears that the majority of Australian sheep farmers are willing to risk adopting new practices on the basis of just a <strong>(26) few pieces of research</strong>. </span><span class=\"citation-178\">They don’t usually wait until the evidence in favour of the changes is overwhelming; they’re quite happy to act before then, so they can get ahead of the game. </span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Okay, I’ll take a look at that, thanks.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Cũng có một số nghiên cứu ở Úc về các phương pháp chăn nuôi cừu. Tôi có thể cho bạn tài liệu tham khảo nếu bạn muốn. Về cơ bản, có vẻ như phần lớn nông dân nuôi cừu Úc sẵn sàng mạo hiểm áp dụng các phương pháp mới chỉ dựa trên <strong>(26) một vài nghiên cứu</strong>. Họ thường không đợi cho đến khi bằng chứng ủng hộ những thay đổi là áp đảo; họ khá hài lòng khi hành động trước đó, để họ có thể đi trước đón đầu.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Được rồi, tôi sẽ xem xét điều đó, cảm ơn.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"26\" />\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the discussion, you have some time to look at questions 27 to 30 on page six. Now listen and answer questions 27 to thirty.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><span data-path-to-node=\"28,0\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> We said we’d also look at some of the reading material you’ve been reviewing. Yes, I had another look at <em>Contemporary Farming Manual</em>, which is clearly bang up to date. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"28,2\"><span class=\"citation-177\">It covers a lot of things a farmer might want to know, but it’s so </span><strong><span class=\"citation-177\">(27) dull</span></strong></span><span data-path-to-node=\"28,4\">.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Absolutely, I found It really hard going and I can’t imagine any farmer wading through it. There aren’t even any decent pictures. Did you have time to look at <em>Running a Small Farm</em>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><span data-path-to-node=\"30,0\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Yes, although I only read bits of it because, despite being entertaining, it wasn’t very academic. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"30,2\"><span class=\"citation-176\">I know, and a lot of the information is either </span><strong><span class=\"citation-176\">(28) misleading or simply wrong</span></strong></span><span data-path-to-node=\"30,4\">. I’m surprised it got published at all.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><span data-path-to-node=\"31,0\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Hmm. You recommend <em>Agriculture and Economics</em>. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"31,2\"><span class=\"citation-175\">Hmm, I expected that it would be really difficult—the title’s a bit off putting—but I thought it was </span><strong><span class=\"citation-175\">(29) brilliant</span></strong><span class=\"citation-175\"> so I’ve bought it. </span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><span data-path-to-node=\"33,0\"><strong><span class=\"citation-174\">Dr Owen:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-174\"> Yes, some people think it relies too heavily on farming practices in specific parts of the world, but the theories that underpin these are universal, and that’s why </span><strong><span class=\"citation-174\">(29) it’s a required textbook</span></strong><span class=\"citation-174\"> for anyone studying agriculture. </span></span><span data-path-to-node=\"33,2\"> Right, what else did you come across?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><span data-path-to-node=\"34,0\"><strong>Joel:</strong> I borrowed <em>How to Survive in Farming</em> from the library. </span><span data-path-to-node=\"34,2\"><span class=\"citation-173\">I thought it would be interesting background and I liked the informal style, but </span><strong><span class=\"citation-173\">(30) it turned out to have been written years ago</span></strong></span><span data-path-to-node=\"34,4\">.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><span data-path-to-node=\"36,0\"><strong><span class=\"citation-172\">Dr Owen:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-172\"> Yes, and like everything else, farming fashions have changed, so </span><strong><span class=\"citation-172\">(30) it’s badly in need of a new edition</span></strong></span><span data-path-to-node=\"36,2\">. Can I ask you a question about…</span></p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"37\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,0\"><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Trước khi bạn nghe phần còn lại của cuộc thảo luận, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 27 đến 30 trên trang sáu. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe và trả lời các câu hỏi 27 đến 30.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,1\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Chúng ta đã nói rằng chúng ta cũng sẽ xem xét một số tài liệu đọc mà bạn đã xem qua. Vâng, tôi đã xem lại <em>Sổ tay Canh tác Đương đại</em>, rõ ràng là nó rất cập nhật. Nó bao gồm rất nhiều điều mà một nông dân có thể muốn biết, nhưng nó quá <strong>(27) buồn tẻ</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,2\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Hoàn toàn chính xác, tôi thấy nó rất khó đọc và tôi không thể tưởng tượng bất kỳ nông dân nào lại đọc hết nó. Thậm chí không có bất kỳ hình ảnh nào tử tế. Bạn có thời gian xem <em>Vận hành một Trang trại Nhỏ</em> không?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,3\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Có, mặc dù tôi chỉ đọc một vài đoạn vì, mặc dù thú vị, nó không mang tính học thuật lắm. Tôi biết, và rất nhiều thông tin hoặc là <strong>(28) gây hiểu lầm hoặc hoàn toàn sai</strong>. Tôi ngạc nhiên là nó được xuất bản.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,4\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Hmm. Bạn giới thiệu <em>Nông nghiệp và Kinh tế</em>. Hmm, tôi đã nghĩ rằng nó sẽ thực sự khó—tiêu đề hơi gây khó chịu—nhưng tôi nghĩ nó <strong>(29) tuyệt vời</strong> nên tôi đã mua nó.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,5\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Vâng, một số người nghĩ rằng nó quá dựa vào các phương pháp canh tác ở các khu vực cụ thể trên thế giới, nhưng các lý thuyết làm nền tảng cho chúng là phổ quát, và đó là lý do tại sao <strong>(29) nó là sách giáo khoa bắt buộc</strong> đối với bất kỳ ai học nông nghiệp. Được rồi, bạn còn gặp tài liệu nào khác không?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,6\"><strong>Joel:</strong> Tôi mượn <em>Cách sống sót trong Nông nghiệp</em> từ thư viện. Tôi nghĩ nó sẽ là tài liệu nền thú vị và tôi thích văn phong không chính thức, nhưng <strong>(30) hóa ra nó đã được viết từ nhiều năm trước</strong>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37,7\"><strong>Dr Owen:</strong> Vâng, và giống như mọi thứ khác, xu hướng canh tác đã thay đổi, vì vậy <strong>(30) nó đang rất cần một ấn bản mới</strong>. Tôi có thể hỏi bạn một câu hỏi về…</p>\n</blockquote>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3aca33d8-6252-4e6f-a504-4cde405fad7b', '1d23c0ae-dbfb-44b5-8022-b77f2eceef29', 'radio', 'Questions 38–40', '', '<p>Choose<strong data-start="233" data-end="241"> TRUE</strong> – if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-start="291" data-end="300">FALSE</strong> – if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-start="350" data-end="363">NOT GIVEN</strong> – if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The original buildings in which movies were shown took their name from the cost of admission."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The products of European film industries were not shown in the USA in the early part of the 20th century."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Making the movies was the most profitable area in the American film business."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. The original buildings in which movies were shown took their name from the cost of admission. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Early cinemas were called <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">‘nickelodeons’</strong> because you paid a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">nickel (five cents)</strong> to see the show.”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Nickel” là tên đồng 5 xu, cũng chính là giá vé vào cửa (cost of admission). Tên gọi của những rạp chiếu phim đầu tiên (nickelodeons) bắt nguồn từ chính giá tiền này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. The products of European film industries were not shown in the USA in the early part of the 20th century. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“By 1918, the American film industry had effectively re-established itself as the dominant cinema, although the film industries of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">Soviet Union, Germany, Britain, France and Scandinavia</strong> would challenge Hollywood…”</em> (Đoạn C)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến các nền điện ảnh châu Âu (Anh, Pháp, Đức…) là đối thủ cạnh tranh của Hollywood về mặt nghệ thuật, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc phim của họ có được trình chiếu tại Mỹ hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Making the movies was the most profitable area in the American film business. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Of these, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">real money</strong> was to be made in <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">distribution and exhibition</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn D)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Real money” ở đây ám chỉ phần lợi nhuận lớn nhất (most profitable). Bài đọc khẳng định lợi nhuận thực sự nằm ở khâu phân phối (distribution) và trình chiếu (exhibition), chứ không phải ở khâu sản xuất/làm phim (making the movies/production).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0727faf7-e05c-4360-9a64-67b1be429682', '06745543-30c5-4b23-a348-77f2b2541b31', 'matrix', 'Questions 1 – 6', '', '<p data-path-to-node="3"><em data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="117">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="143">A-G</strong>, in boxes 1-6 on your answer sheet.</em></p>
<p data-path-to-node="4"><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> <em data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="3">You may use any letter <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="26">more than once</strong>.</em></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It has a quiet area for eating.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "You can buy presents here.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "You can walk in an old forest.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "It has many flowers.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "You can observe birds near the water.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "It allows bicycles on the trail.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. It has a quiet area for eating. — {A} Marshland</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…which is very <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">peaceful</strong> and a good place to have a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">picnic lunch</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Peaceful” tương ứng với “quiet” (yên tĩnh), và “picnic lunch” là hoạt động ăn uống (eating). Tuyến Marshland có một nền đài ngoài trời rất phù hợp cho việc này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. You can buy presents here. — {G} Marine Trail</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…you will find a lighthouse with a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">gift shop</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Gift shop” là cửa hàng quà lưu niệm, nơi bạn có thể mua quà tặng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">buy presents</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. You can walk in an old forest. — {B} Hardwood</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“This trail winds through <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">century-old maple trees</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những cây phong đã tồn tại cả thế kỷ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">century-old</strong>) chính là đặc điểm của một khu rừng già/lâu đời (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">old forest</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. It has many flowers. — {D} Upland</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“You will see lots of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">wild roses, daisies and lilacs</strong> along your way.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc liệt kê rất nhiều loại hoa như hoa hồng dại, hoa cúc và hoa tử đinh hương, khớp với ý “many flowers”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. You can observe birds near the water. — {C} Grassland</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…excellent opportunities to see <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">migrating shorebirds along the beach</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Shorebirds” (chim bờ biển) là loài chim thường xuất hiện ở vùng nước, và “along the beach” (dọc bãi biển) chính là khu vực gần nước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">near the water</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. It allows bicycles on the trail. — {A} Marshland</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…and <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">cycling is permitted</strong> along it.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Cycling is permitted” có nghĩa là việc đạp xe được cho phép, tương ứng với “allows bicycles”.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1170b7ef-c9f3-4462-8fae-f79fc461f11b', '06745543-30c5-4b23-a348-77f2b2541b31', 'radio', 'Questions 7 – 14', '', '<p data-path-to-node="5,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="5,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "You can buy a suitable flashlight for a reasonable price."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Headlamps have limited durability in the rain."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Purchasing LED flashlights is recommended."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "150 lumens is a brightness that causes light pollution."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Small flashlights use up more batteries."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Headlamps are recommended when preparing meals."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Using a headlamp at a low setting to read in a tent is bad for eyesight."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Recharging units can be difficult to find."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. You can buy a suitable flashlight for a reasonable price. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“These cost from one to 300 dollars. You <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">don’t have to spend a lot</strong> to get one to suit your needs…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Don’t have to spend a lot” (không cần chi nhiều tiền) tương ứng với “reasonable price” (giá cả hợp lý). Bạn có thể tìm được chiếc đèn phù hợp mà không cần tốn quá nhiều tiền.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Headlamps have limited durability in the rain. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…some flashlights are water resistant… In those conditions, <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">headlamps are not as long-lasting</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Not as long-lasting” (không bền bằng) trong điều kiện mưa lớn tương ứng với “limited durability” (độ bền bị hạn chế).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Purchasing LED flashlights is recommended. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Most today have <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">LED</strong>… bulbs that are very reliable… <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">Don’t even think about getting anything else</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu “Đừng mảy may suy nghĩ đến việc mua thứ gì khác” là một lời khuyên cực kỳ mạnh mẽ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">recommended</strong>) cho việc chọn mua đèn LED.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. 150 lumens is a brightness that causes light pollution. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Buy one that produces at least 150 lumens. That’s lots of power <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">without leaking light pollution</strong> into the night sky.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định 150 lumens cung cấp đủ độ sáng mà <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">không gây ra</strong> ô nhiễm ánh sáng (without leaking light pollution), trái ngược hoàn toàn với câu hỏi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Small flashlights use up more batteries. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The higher the setting, the quicker the batteries will run down. Buy a small flashlight with batteries that will last at least eight hours…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến “small flashlight” và việc pin nhanh hết nếu để chế độ cao, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">không hề so sánh</strong> rằng đèn nhỏ thì tốn pin hơn đèn lớn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Headlamps are recommended when preparing meals. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It’s a good idea to use a headlamp when <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">cooking in the dark</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Cooking” tương ứng với “preparing meals”. Bài đọc khẳng định đây là một ý tưởng hay (it’s a good idea/recommended).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Using a headlamp at a low setting to read in a tent is bad for eyesight. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…buy a headlamp that can switch to a low setting to <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">avoid keeping your tent-mate awake</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khuyên dùng chế độ thấp khi đọc sách để tránh làm bạn cùng lều thức giấc, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc nó có hại cho thị lực (bad for eyesight) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Recharging units can be difficult to find. — {TRUE}</strong> (Lưu ý: Bạn hãy kiểm tra lại đáp án 14 của mình nhé)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Avoid <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">specialty batteries</strong>; they’re costly and <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">not widely available</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Not widely available” tương ứng với “difficult to find”. Bài đọc khuyên tránh các loại pin đặc biệt vì chúng đắt và khó tìm. (Nếu câu hỏi ám chỉ “specialty batteries” là một dạng bộ nguồn/pin sạc đặc thù thì đáp án sẽ là True).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5e4f32ca-4cef-4ab2-8926-3117b9125b45', '2e5470c9-403e-444b-88a2-cfa4e826ecea', 'fillup', 'Questions 15 – 21', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15-21 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="29" data-index-in-node="0">Travel for Work</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Requests for making bookings</span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="31">
<li>
<p>Fill out a {Travel Requisition form} .</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Get approval.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Hand in application to the<strong data-path-to-node="31,2,0" data-index-in-node="23"> {HR administrator}</strong> .</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">‘Frequent Flyer’</span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="33">
<li>
<p>Any benefits, e.g. {Air Miles} , go to employees.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Employees can only travel with their preferred airline when the fare is acceptable.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Hotels</span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="35">
<li>
<p>Check company policy on appropriate {standards} of accommodation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Settle hotel bills on departure (make sure your {bankcard} is acceptable).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Don’t forget to cancel bookings if necessary.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Be aware of the high cost of {telephone calls} when staying in a hotel.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Travel documents</span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="37">
<li>
<p>It might be necessary to provide passport details to the airline.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Check in advance whether a visa is needed.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong data-path-to-node="38" data-index-in-node="0">Foreign currency</strong></span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="39">
<li>
<p>Consult the {guidelines} when applying for a Petty Cash Advance.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Insurance</span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="41">
<li>
<p>All employees are covered for travel.</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Fill out a {Travel Requisition form}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“All requests to book air travel and accommodation must be made using a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">Travel Requisition Form</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là loại giấy tờ đầu tiên cần điền khi muốn đặt vé hoặc phòng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Hand in application to the {HR administrator}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…and then approved by the employee’s line manager, prior to submission to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">HR Administrator</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Submission” tương ứng với “hand in” (nộp cho). Sau khi quản lý duyệt, đơn được gửi cho người quản trị nhân sự.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Any benefits, e.g. {Air Miles}, go to employees.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The frequent-flyer benefits provided by some airlines, such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">Air Miles</strong>, will continue to accrue to the individual employee…”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Accrue to the individual” nghĩa là thuộc về cá nhân nhân viên. (Lưu ý: Đáp án bạn ghi “Air rules” là chưa chính xác so với văn bản, từ đúng phải là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">Air Miles</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Check company policy on appropriate {standards} of accommodation.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Please refer to the company’s Travel Expense Policy regarding the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">standards</strong> which are approved for hotels.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Refer to” tương ứng với “check”. Nhân viên cần kiểm tra các tiêu chuẩn về khách sạn được phê duyệt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Settle hotel bills on departure (make sure your {bank card} is acceptable).</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If paying by <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">bank card</strong>, it is worthwhile employees checking that the hotel will accept the type that they have.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Settle bills on departure” tương ứng với “paid on checkout”. Nhân viên cần đảm bảo thẻ ngân hàng của mình được khách sạn chấp nhận.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Be aware of the high cost of {telephone calls} when staying in a hotel.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Remember that <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">telephone calls</strong> made from your hotel room can be charged between 100% and 500% above normal rates.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết cảnh báo chi phí gọi điện thoại từ phòng khách sạn rất cao (vượt mức bình thường từ 1-5 lần).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Consult the {guidelines} when applying for a Petty Cash Advance.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…using the Petty Cash Advance form, and following the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">guidelines</strong> in the Overseas Expense Policy.”</em> (Đoạn 6)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Following” tương ứng với “consult” (tham khảo/tuân theo). Khi xin tạm ứng tiền mặt, cần làm theo các hướng dẫn.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('77953b3e-2906-4c9c-ba1d-b48c63e8e3c3', '2e5470c9-403e-444b-88a2-cfa4e826ecea', 'fillup', 'Questions 22 – 27', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9989%; height: 161.895px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 19.9164%;"> <col style="width: 19.9164%;"> <col style="width: 19.9164%;"> <col style="width: 19.9164%;"> <col style="width: 19.9164%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 42.4219px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;"> </td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>HOURS</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>LOCATION</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS FOR STAFF</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>OTHER DETAILS</strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 31.8164px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>NURSERIES</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p data-path-to-node="4,0,0">During the day, Mon–Fri, throughout the whole {year}</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Dedicated premises</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>No qualifications necessary</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>You must be willing to undertake {training} while you are working.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 32.832px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>PLAYGROUPS</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>2 hours per session (except during {school holidays} )</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Various e.g. community centres</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="6,2,0">
<p>Minimum level 3 qualification for leaders</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="6,2,1,0,0">Leaders can be men or women of any {age}</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Some {parents} may act as assistants.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 54.8242px;">
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p><strong>CHILDMINDING</strong></p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Maximum 90 minutes per day, unless the childminder is registered</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Childminder’s home</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<p>Qualification in {First Aid}</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 2px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center; border-width: 2px;">
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,3,0">
<p>Maximum number of children = 6 (depending on the size of the rooms)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="8,3,1,0,0">Childminders manage tax and insurance themselves.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Nurseries: During the day, Mon–Fri, throughout the whole {year}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Nurseries are open <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">all year</strong> and generally between 8.00am and 6.00pm every weekday.”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “All year” tương ứng với “throughout the whole year”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Nurseries: You must be willing to undertake {training} while you are working.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…you must be prepared to <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">do some training</strong> to achieve a minimum level 3 childcare qualification.”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Be prepared to” tương ứng với “be willing to”. Nhân viên mới vào nghề (trainee) cần sẵn sàng tham gia đào tạo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">training</strong>) để đạt bằng cấp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Playgroups: 2 hours per session (except during {school holidays})</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“They generally run for a couple of hours per session, but <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">are not open in school holidays</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Except during” (ngoại trừ) tương ứng với “not open in”. Các nhóm trẻ này đóng cửa vào các kỳ nghỉ học (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">school holidays</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Playgroups: Leaders can be men or women of any {age}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A playleader can be male or female, with an <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">age range</strong> from school-leaver to grandparent.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc mô tả độ tuổi từ người vừa rời ghế nhà trường đến ông bà cho thấy họ có thể ở bất kỳ độ tuổi nào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">age</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Playgroups: Some {parents} may act as assistants.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…who are <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">assisted</strong> by one or two of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">parents</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Act as assistants” tương ứng với “be assisted by”. Phụ huynh sẽ là người hỗ trợ cho các trưởng nhóm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Childminding: Qualification in {First Aid}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Childminders don’t have to have the level 3 childcare qualification but must have a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">First Aid</strong> certificate.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Certificate” ở đây chính là bằng cấp/chứng chỉ chuyên môn về Sơ cứu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">First Aid</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d8dfa337-9df8-42ad-a548-44c078078ed7', 'f7305d07-044b-4bd8-8248-6dbd05071fec', 'matching', 'Questions 28 – 34', '', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Write the correct number, <strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="178">i-x</strong>, in boxes <strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="192">28-34</strong> on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Going over the target number"}, {"optionText": "ii Unwelcome arrivals"}, {"optionText": "iii Future challenges"}, {"optionText": "iv Providing the right diet"}, {"optionText": "v Taking sensible precautions"}, {"optionText": "vi Importing enough food"}, {"optionText": "vii Coming up with a solution"}, {"optionText": "viii A strange inhabitant"}, {"optionText": "ix A close relationship with iguanas"}, {"optionText": "x A difficult beginning"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. Đoạn A — {viii} A strange inhabitant (Một cư dân kỳ lạ)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Blue iguanas… can grow up to 1.5m long and weigh 11kg… Their scales are sky-blue… their eyes are a striking red… This rare and unlikely creature…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ đoạn này tập trung mô tả những đặc điểm ngoại hình “lạ lùng” (màu xanh da trời, mắt đỏ, kích thước lớn) của loài cự đà này và môi trường sống đặc hữu của nó trên đảo Grand Cayman.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Đoạn B — {v} Taking sensible precautions (Thực hiện các biện pháp phòng ngừa hợp lý)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“the area’s hostile landscape is a place where foolish explorers often… get lost. Fortunately, we arranged to have a guide… He’s armed with years of experience and a GPS…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn cảnh báo sự nguy hiểm của địa hình dễ gây lạc đường. “Precautions” ở đây chính là việc thuê hướng dẫn viên chuyên nghiệp và sử dụng thiết bị định vị GPS để đảm bảo an toàn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. Đoạn C — {ii} Unwelcome arrivals (Những vị khách không chào đón)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The appearance of humans… and with them dogs, cats, rats… Humans also brought the more common green iguana and that became a serious threat.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Arrivals” (sự xuất hiện/đến nơi) ám chỉ con người và các loài xâm lấn (chó, mèo, chuột và đặc biệt là cự đà xanh thông thường). Chúng là nguyên nhân chính gây ra sự sụt giảm số lượng cự đà bản địa nên được gọi là “unwelcome” (không được chào đón).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Đoạn D — {x} A difficult beginning (Một sự khởi đầu khó khăn)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Progress wasn’t all smooth, however. The first blue iguanas… turned out not to be pure breeds. Then… the iguanas that were bred weren’t surviving after being let out…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này kể về những thất bại liên tiếp trong giai đoạn đầu của chương trình nhân giống: từ việc chọn nhầm giống không thuần chủng đến việc cự đà con chết sau khi thả ra tự nhiên do không có hang phù hợp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Đoạn E — {vii} Coming up with a solution (Tìm ra một giải pháp)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Through trial and error, the conservationists established the correct dimensions and developed a strategy that worked… provided custom-made ‘lizard lairs’…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau những khó khăn ở đoạn D, các nhà khoa học đã tìm ra cách khắc phục bằng cách tạo ra các hang đá nhân tạo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">lizard lairs</strong>) bằng bê tông và đất sét. Đây chính là “solution” giúp số lượng cự đà tăng lên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Đoạn F — {iv} Providing the right diet (Cung cấp chế độ ăn uống phù hợp)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“prepare the different vegetation, laboriously cutting it up into different sizes… Iguanas feed on at least 106 different plant species… classify whether something is edible or not…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này tập trung hoàn toàn vào thói quen ăn uống, cách chuẩn bị thực phẩm tỉ mỉ của các tình nguyện viên và khả năng nhận biết thực vật của loài cự đà.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Đoạn G — {ix} A close relationship with iguanas (Mối quan hệ mật thiết với cự đà)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“remarkable to see the iguanas’ reaction to the sound of his voice… some run towards him… it’s clear that they know him.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mô tả sự tương tác thân thiết giữa người quản lý (Alberto) và những con cự đà. Chúng nhận ra giọng nói và có phản ứng thân thiện khi ông xuất hiện, cho thấy một sự gắn kết đặc biệt giữa người và vật.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('adc68c7e-5ddb-4214-8e40-13696291a557', 'e2aa4c06-dddd-4069-ad2d-20f3cf957cbd', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>What opinion is expressed about each of the following books?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-G</strong>, next to questions <strong>27-30</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Books</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Contemporary Farming Manual {G It’s boring.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Running a Small Farm {E It’s inaccurate.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Agriculture and Economics {D It’s essential reading.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Flow to Survive in Farming {B It’s out of date.}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A It’s badly organised."}, {"optionText": "B It’s out of date."}, {"optionText": "C It’s clear."}, {"optionText": "D It’s essential reading."}, {"optionText": "E It’s inaccurate."}, {"optionText": "F It’s well illustrated."}, {"optionText": "G It’s boring."}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2abcfa9e-7952-4b85-8b6d-470d575f7963', '99b9192b-3d23-4092-ba2f-c190d231efe2', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="43">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="54">D</strong>. </p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Too many branches of science have been involved in its study."}, {"option_text": "B. The Société de Linguistique de Paris instigated research in this area."}, {"option_text": "C. The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done."}, {"option_text": "C. The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done."}], "question": "In the first paragraph, what does the writer suggest about the origin of language?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Some current theories are based on conflicting evidence."}, {"option_text": "B. There is insufficient fossil evidence to reach a conclusion."}, {"option_text": "C. Fossil evidence suggests that Homo sapiens had larger brains than Neanderthals."}, {"option_text": "D. Archaeological evidence shows that Neanderthals were able to talk."}], "question": "What is the \"problem\" referred to in the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Modern theorists should pay more attention to his approach."}, {"option_text": "B. His ideas supported those of the Société de Linguistique de Paris."}, {"option_text": "C. His ideas were mirrored in a later book called Language Evolution."}, {"option_text": "D. His ideas are too outdated to be of any relevance today."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about Jean-Jacques Rousseau’s work in 1781?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. They have had little impact on the study of language."}, {"option_text": "B. They have helped the study of linguistics to progress."}, {"option_text": "C. They are not accepted by the majority of linguists."}, {"option_text": "D. The assumption behind them is wrong."}], "question": "What is the writer’s current view of Derek Bickerton’s ideas?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. grammar and meaning."}, {"option_text": "B. messages and proto-language."}, {"option_text": "C. language, music and emotions."}, {"option_text": "D. proto-language and modern semantics."}], "question": "In the final paragraph, the writer concludes that Alison Wray’s ideas will help establish a link between"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. In the first paragraph, what does the writer suggest about the origin of language? — {C. The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Linguists, psychologists, anthropologists and archaeologists now <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">frequently debate</strong>… and have <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">published many articles and books</strong>… And yet, despite <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">almost frenzied activity</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">limited progress</strong> has been made.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng có rất nhiều chuyên gia tham gia nghiên cứu và xuất bản vô số tài liệu (“frenzied activity”), nhưng tiến độ đạt được lại rất hạn chế (“limited progress”). Điều này cho thấy sự tương phản đáng ngạc nhiên giữa khối lượng công việc và kết quả thu được.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. What is the “problem” referred to in the second paragraph? — {A. Some current theories are based on conflicting evidence.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…fossil evidence indicates that the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">Neanderthals had larger brains</strong>… but archaeological evidence indicates that the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">Neanderthals lacked a capacity for language</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Vấn đề” ở đây là sự mâu thuẫn giữa hai loại bằng chứng: Bằng chứng hóa thạch nói não họ to (thường đi đôi với khả năng ngôn ngữ), nhưng bằng chứng khảo cổ lại nói họ không biết nói. Vì các lý thuyết hiện tại dựa trên những bằng chứng đối nghịch này nên chúng bị coi là có vấn đề.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. What does the writer suggest about Jean-Jacques Rousseau’s work in 1781? — {A. Modern theorists should pay more attention to his approach.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…Christiansen and Simon Kirby’s book… <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">failed to mention music</strong>… Those authors have an <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">important lesson to learn from Rousseau</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả phê phán các học giả hiện đại vì bỏ qua âm nhạc khi nghiên cứu ngôn ngữ. Ông khẳng định họ có bài học quan trọng cần học từ Rousseau – người đã nhìn nhận ngôn ngữ và âm nhạc luôn gắn liền với nhau. Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc các nhà lý thuyết hiện đại nên chú ý hơn đến cách tiếp cận của ông.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. What is the writer’s current view of Derek Bickerton’s ideas? — {D. The assumption behind them is wrong.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“But Bickerton’s idea that… is, I believe, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">fundamentally mistaken</strong>… it is not only <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">flawed</strong> but has severely limited the progress…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng các từ mạnh như “fundamentally mistaken” (sai lầm từ gốc rễ) và “flawed” (thiếu sót/sai lệch) để nói về ý tưởng của Bickerton. Điều này xác nhận rằng giả định nền tảng đằng sau các ý tưởng đó là sai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. In the final paragraph, the writer concludes that Alison Wray’s ideas will help establish a link between — {C. language, music and emotions.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“I believe this insight enables us to understand the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">origin of music as well as language</strong>, and to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">relate both to the emotional lives</strong> of our human ancestors.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả chốt lại rằng quan điểm của Alison Wray (về ngôn ngữ nguyên thủy mang tính “chỉnh thể” – holistic) giúp chúng ta hiểu được nguồn gốc của cả âm nhạc, ngôn ngữ và mối liên hệ của cả hai với đời sống cảm xúc của tổ tiên.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a7740859-76e5-4992-a912-6089ec3bc089', 'ee1d1bdc-350a-4cc7-9e2f-e548d61f7e2f', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A More data is necessary in order for DOC to target the right areas."}, {"content": "B DOC is uncertain how long a new strategy will take to be effective."}, {"content": "C There is a considerable risk that DOC will not succeed in saving them."}, {"content": "D The first step in DOC''s strategy is to identify their main predator."}], "question": "According to the sixth paragraph, what is being said about the future of the grand and Otago skinks?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A the fence needed to surround various kinds of habitat."}, {"content": "B the fence was not the preferred choice of some conservationists."}, {"content": "C the fence had to be constructed near a heavily populated urban area."}, {"content": "D there was no way of knowing how many skinks were inside the fence."}], "question": "According to the writer, a problem with the DOC''s fencing project was that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A introduce a recent alternative approach to skink conservation."}, {"content": "B question whether captive breeding has worked in the past."}, {"content": "C imply that skinks are unlikely to reproduce outside their usual habitat."}, {"content": "D express a preference for conserving skinks in their natural environment."}], "question": "The writer uses the phrase ''a last resort'' in the eighth paragraph in order to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A referring to obstacles in the way of skink conservation"}, {"content": "B appealing to landowners to donate land for conservation purposes"}, {"content": "C describing a conservation scheme that is being set up on farmland"}, {"content": "D showing how commercial profit can be made from ecological ventures"}], "question": "What is the writer doing in the final paragraph?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>37. According to the sixth paragraph, what is being said about the future of the grand and Otago skinks?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: C. There is a considerable risk that DOC will not succeed in saving them.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) &#8220;<strong>No more than five years remain in which to turn things around</strong> – a close call considering it will be at least three before detectable response in the populations can be expected&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Với thời gian còn lại rất ít (5 năm) và tốc độ sinh sản chậm, có một <strong>nguy cơ lớn</strong> (considerable risk) là DOC sẽ thất bại trong việc cứu chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>38. According to the writer, a problem with the DOC&#8217;s fencing project was that</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: A. the fence needed to surround various kinds of habitat.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) &#8220;An added complication was that <strong>grands and Otagos have subtly different environmental preferences, both of which need catering for</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc hai loài có sở thích môi trường khác nhau đòi hỏi hàng rào phải bao quanh nhiều loại môi trường sống (various kinds of habitat) để đáp ứng cả hai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>39. The writer uses the phrase &#8216;a last resort&#8217; in the eighth paragraph in order to</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: D. express a preference for conserving skinks in their natural environment.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) &#8220;Captive management, however, is <strong>a last resort</strong>. The <strong>priority is to manage and protect skinks in the wild</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Gọi nuôi nhốt là &#8220;phương sách cuối cùng&#8221; (&#8220;a last resort&#8221;) và nhấn mạnh <strong>ưu tiên</strong> là bảo vệ trong tự nhiên cho thấy tác giả ủng hộ việc bảo tồn trong môi trường tự nhiên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>40. What is the writer doing in the final paragraph?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: C. describing a conservation scheme that is being set up on farmland.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn J) &#8220;&#8230;with the generous support of a local <strong>farmer with grazing land</strong> there, has begun the construction of a mammal-proof fence&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn mô tả chương trình hợp tác với nông dân để xây dựng hàng rào bảo vệ trên đất chăn thả (<strong>farmland</strong>) của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('386d28ab-bdec-40f9-a63e-6704a0cc40d0', 'f7305d07-044b-4bd8-8248-6dbd05071fec', 'fillup', 'Questions 35 – 37', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 35-37 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">The Blue Iguana of Grand Cayman</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7">The blue iguana is a beautiful pale blue which becomes more vivid in the breeding season. This colour is set off by its remarkable {eyes} . Another interesting feature is the characteristic {spines} that goes right along its back. Its teeth are specially adapted to deal with the tough {vegetation} that is its main diet. The blue iguana is native to the island of Grand Cayman in the Caribbean and is now only found in one region there.</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. This colour is set off by its remarkable {eyes}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Their scales are <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">sky-blue</strong>… while their <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">eyes</strong> by contrast are a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">striking red</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Remarkable” (đáng chú ý/ấn tượng) trong câu hỏi đồng nghĩa với “striking” trong bài đọc. Sự tương phản (contrast) giữa vảy xanh và đôi mắt đỏ rực làm cho vẻ ngoài của chúng trở nên nổi bật.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Another interesting feature is the characteristic {spines} that goes right along its back.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“These iguanas have a crest made up of short <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">spines</strong>, which start behind the head and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">continue to the end of the tail</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Along its back” (dọc theo lưng) tương ứng với việc các gai nhọn bắt đầu từ sau đầu và kéo dài đến tận đuôi. Đặc điểm nhận dạng chính là những chiếc gai (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"166\">spines</strong>) này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Its teeth are specially adapted to deal with the tough {vegetation} that is its main diet.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Their strong jaws contain finely serrated <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">teeth</strong>, which they need to shred the different types of, frequently <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">leathery, vegetation</strong> on which they feed.”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Tough” (dai/cứng) đồng nghĩa với “leathery” (như da thuộc). Răng của chúng được cấu tạo đặc biệt để nhai/xé các loại thực vật (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">vegetation</strong>) dai cứng này.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1d1c74b8-814a-4a79-b1cd-1b2c118aad63', '5c61a509-f5c3-4841-bdfb-6d3011e38686', 'matching', 'Questions 14–19', '', '<p>Reading Passage 2 has six sections.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each section from the list of headings below.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "optionsTitle": "List of Headings ", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Professions in which super-taskers are likely to be found"}, {"optionText": "ii. The effects of multi-tasking on neurological structure"}, {"optionText": "iii. A distinction between situations when people can and can''t multi-task"}, {"optionText": "iv. Real multi-tasking is nearly impossible"}, {"optionText": "v. Multi-tasking and gender"}, {"optionText": "vi. The neurological reasons for struggling to manage more things"}, {"optionText": "vii. The ability to multi-task is determined by people’s genes"}, {"optionText": "viii. Gender and the structure of the brain"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Section A: iv (Real multi-tasking is nearly impossible)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn A,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 2–4.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">research shows that your brain </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">isn’t capable</strong><span class=\"\"> of paying close attention to more than one complex task at a time.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,0,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này khẳng định đa nhiệm hiệu quả là vượt quá khả năng của hầu hết chúng ta và gọi đó là một “huyền thoại” (myth),</span><span class=\"\"> tức là thực tế gần như không thể thực hiện được.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Section B: iii (A distinction between situations when people can and can’t multi-task)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn B,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 1–4.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “It is true that you can check your email while eating…</span><span class=\"\"> But </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">innate activities</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> do not require you to pay attention,</span><span class=\"\"> whereas </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">activities such as reading… do require attention</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả phân biệt rõ hai tình huống:</span><span class=\"\"> những việc bản năng (đi bộ,</span><span class=\"\"> ăn) thì có thể làm cùng lúc,</span><span class=\"\"> nhưng những việc cần sự tập trung (đọc,</span><span class=\"\"> lái xe) thì không thể đa nhiệm hiệu quả.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Section C: vi (The neurological reasons for struggling to manage more things)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn C,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 5–8.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">simply because we have only </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">two frontal lobes</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> the brain can switch back and forth between two tasks,</span><span class=\"\"> we might be in great trouble when we try to juggle more than two…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này giải thích dưới góc độ thần kinh học (neurological):</span><span class=\"\"> vì não chỉ có 2 thùy trán nên chỉ có thể xử lý tối đa 2 việc bằng cách chuyển đổi qua lại,</span><span class=\"\"> nhiều hơn sẽ gặp rắc rối.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,3,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Section D: v (Multi-tasking and gender)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn D,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 1–4.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">whether there is a difference between the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">sexes</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> claimed that </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">women</strong><span class=\"\"> are superior multi-taskers.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,3,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Toàn bộ đoạn này thảo luận về khả năng đa nhiệm giữa nam và nữ (gender/sexes),</span><span class=\"\"> bao gồm cả nghiên cứu hình ảnh não và các tình huống thực tế.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,4,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Section E: i (Professions in which super-taskers are likely to be found)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn E,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 4–7.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">pilots</strong><span class=\"\">…</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">high-end chefs</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> and </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">elite doctors</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> might all be more likely to be super-taskers.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,4,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này liệt kê các ngành nghề (professions) mà những người “siêu đa nhiệm” thường xuất hiện như phi công,</span><span class=\"\"> đầu bếp và bác sĩ cấp cứu.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,5,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,5,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Section F: vii (The ability to multi-task is determined by people’s genes)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn F,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 1–2.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “The ability to multi-task probably comes down to the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">DNA you inherit</strong><span class=\"\"> from your parents…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2,5,1,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn cuối khẳng định khả năng này do di truyền (DNA/genes) quyết định,</span><span class=\"\"> bạn sinh ra đã có cấu trúc não đó hoặc là không.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('adf81b96-350d-41b5-8329-ca54af765b42', 'a73c6549-8c8e-4355-9425-19058dc8673b', 'radio', 'Questions 19 and 20', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="27">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="30">B</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="35">C</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A   It had always been her ambition."}, {"option_text": "B   Her husband persuaded her to do it."}, {"option_text": "C   She nearly gave up before the end."}], "question": "What does Liz say about running her first marathon?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A   every six months."}, {"option_text": "B   within a few weeks of taking up running."}, {"option_text": "C   after completing several practice runs."}], "question": "Liz says new runners should sign up for a race"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('58fd82c8-eed5-463a-b7e7-68b618723709', '99b9192b-3d23-4092-ba2f-c190d231efe2', 'matching', 'Questions 32-37', '', '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A–H, below.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, A–H, in boxes 32–37 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "suggested music was an essential part of every individual."}, {"optionText": "made no link between music and language in a comprehensive study."}, {"optionText": "believes that early language was very musical."}, {"optionText": "felt that the origin of language should not be debated."}, {"optionText": "states that early language was a pool of basic words used in an unsystematic way."}, {"optionText": "devoted 17 chapters of a book to music."}, {"optionText": "believes that proto-language had no individual words."}, {"optionText": "referred to music in part of a book about the development of human beings."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The Société de Linguistique de Paris", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Charles Darwin", "correctAnswer": "H"}, {"questionPart": "John Blacking", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "Christiansen and Kirby", "correctAnswer": "B"}, {"questionPart": "Derek Bickerton", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "Alison Wray", "correctAnswer": "G"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. The Société de Linguistique de Paris — {D. felt that the origin of language should not be debated.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…in 1866 the influential <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">Société de Linguistique de Paris banned all discussions about the origin of language</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc “cấm tất cả các thảo luận” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">banned all discussions</strong>) tương ứng với việc họ cảm thấy nguồn gốc ngôn ngữ không nên được tranh luận (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">should not be debated</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Charles Darwin — {H. referred to music in part of a book about the development of human beings.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“One is… <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">Charles Darwin</strong> who, in his 1871 book on human evolution, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">The Descent of Man, devoted several pages to the development of music</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “The Descent of Man” là cuốn sách về sự tiến hóa/phát triển của con người, và trong đó Darwin đã dành vài trang để nói về âm nhạc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">referred to music</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. John Blacking — {A. suggested music was an essential part of every individual.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…ethnomusicologist <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">John Blacking</strong>, whose 1973 book… broached the idea that <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">music is an inherent and universal human quality</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Inherent and universal human quality” (phẩm chất vốn có và phổ quát của con người) đồng nghĩa với việc âm nhạc là một phần thiết yếu của mỗi cá nhân (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">essential part of every individual</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Christiansen and Kirby — {B. made no link between music and language in a comprehensive study.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">Christiansen and Simon Kirby’s book</strong>, Language Evolution (2000), which they conceived as ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">a definitive book on the subject</strong>‘, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">failed to mention music in any of its 17 chapters</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một nghiên cứu “toàn diện/định nghĩa” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">comprehensive/definitive study</strong>) mà lại không nhắc đến âm nhạc trong suốt 17 chương, chứng tỏ họ không tạo ra mối liên kết nào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">made no link</strong>) giữa âm nhạc và ngôn ngữ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Derek Bickerton — {E. states that early language was a pool of basic words used in an unsystematic way.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Bickerton’s idea that the precursor of modern language consisted of <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">words strung together with limited, if any, grammar</strong>… refers to this precursor as <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">‘protolanguage’</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Words strung together” (các từ xâu chuỗi lại) với “limited grammar” (ngữ pháp hạn chế) tương ứng với một nhóm các từ cơ bản (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">pool of basic words</strong>) được sử dụng một cách không hệ thống (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">unsystematic</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Alison Wray — {G. believes that proto-language had no individual words.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“She argues that <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">proto-language was ‘holistic’</strong>… it was a communication system <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">composed of ‘messages’ rather than words</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Holistic” (chỉnh thể) và “messages rather than words” (thông điệp thay vì từ ngữ) xác nhận quan điểm của bà là ngôn ngữ nguyên thủy không có các từ riêng lẻ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">no individual words</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a403d4ae-992d-4e69-a6d2-75ff5457eada', 'b53c748a-d18c-4e54-9933-ba586cac5e2a', 'radio', 'Questions 1-5', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information. <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information. <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "According to Darwin, cooking was the most significant development in human history."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The process of cooking gets rid of some plant poisons."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Eating cooked food is more energy efficient than eating raw food."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Clarence Birdseye had previously worked in the Australian food industry."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Birdseye’s trip with the Inuit confirmed what he already believed about rapid freezing."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>1. FALSE<br />\n(Đoạn 1: “Darwin thought that cooking, after language, was the greatest discovery made by man.”)<br />\n→ Câu hỏi nói “the most significant development”, nhưng văn bản nói ngôn ngữ mới là phát minh lớn nhất, còn cooking chỉ đứng thứ hai.</p>\n<p>2. TRUE<br />\n(Đoạn 2: “Cooking can turn plants that are inedible into edible food by destroying toxic chemicals…”)<br />\n→ Văn bản nói rõ nấu ăn loại bỏ độc tố trong thực vật, đúng với ý câu hỏi.</p>\n<p>3. TRUE<br />\n(Đoạn 3: “The ratio of energy gained to energy expended by the body is greater when food is cooked.”)<br />\n→ Ăn đồ nấu chín giúp hiệu quả năng lượng cao hơn ăn đồ sống, vì cơ thể thu được nhiều năng lượng hơn.</p>\n<p>4. NOT GIVEN<br />\n(Toàn bài không có thông tin nào nói Clarence Birdseye từng làm việc trong ngành thực phẩm ở Úc.)<br />\n→ Không tìm thấy chi tiết liên quan, nên không thể xác định.</p>\n<p>5. FALSE<br />\n(Đoạn cuối: “Birdseye observed that rapid freezing… a discovery he had not expected.”)<br />\n→ Ông không mong đợi phát hiện này, trái với nội dung câu hỏi nói “confirmed what he already believed”.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('301f6309-0a93-41ee-8fad-02b6b44d4ebc', '99b9192b-3d23-4092-ba2f-c190d231efe2', 'checkbox', 'Questions 38-40', '', '<p>Choose <strong>THREE</strong> letters, A–G. Write the correct letters in boxes 38–40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A. evidence from prehistoric times"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. intelligence"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C. individual sounds"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. music"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E. emotions"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "F. human intellect"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "G. children''s language"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Đáp án A: evidence from prehistoric times</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“I believe there are four reasons for this. The first is an <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">insufficient concern with the archaeological and fossil proof</strong> of the brains and behaviour of our human ancestors.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Archaeological and fossil proof” (Bằng chứng khảo cổ và hóa thạch) chính là các bằng chứng từ thời tiền sử (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">evidence from prehistoric times</strong>). Tác giả cho rằng các nhà nghiên cứu chưa quan tâm đúng mức (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">insufficient concern</em>) đến mảng này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Đáp án D: music</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“That something might relate to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">second reason</strong> for limited progress: <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">insufficient concern with… music</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định âm nhạc là hệ thống giao tiếp quan trọng thứ hai của con người nhưng lại bị giới học thuật “tự cấm” nghiên cứu trong suốt hai thế kỷ qua.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Đáp án E: emotions</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“That question leads directly to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">third reason</strong> for our lack of progress… an <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">insufficient concern with emotion</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả lập luận rằng âm nhạc là về cảm xúc, nhưng trong khi các nhà khảo cổ tập trung vào trí tuệ (intellectual), họ lại bỏ qua đời sống cảm xúc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">emotions</strong>) của tổ tiên chúng ta.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e4a0baff-4470-4349-a9cf-ef43bfe1965c', '539b2708-48a5-430c-ac11-a5f97c931866', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "how hot the area is."}, {"content": "how warm the water is."}, {"content": "how many dental problems there are in the community."}, {"content": "how much fluorine the community chooses to have in its water."}], "question": "The optimum amount of fluorine in fluoridated water is calculated partly according to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "it may contribute to tooth decay."}, {"content": "it will be unacceptably expensive for the public."}, {"content": "obligatory fluoridation takes away personal freedom."}, {"content": "excessive fluoride could be added to the water by mistake."}], "question": "One reason given by the writer for opposing fluoridation is that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "provide a contrast with the view of Collins"}, {"content": "support the rational nature of scientific inquiry."}, {"content": "demonstrate that Kuhn did not argue his case adequately"}, {"content": "show that science can be influenced by non-scientific considerations"}], "question": "The writer mentions Kuhn in order to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "There were failings in the way they were carried out."}, {"content": "The scientists involved had achieved unique results."}, {"content": "Proponents of fluoridation had not understood its long-term effects."}, {"content": "Fluoridation had a greater effect on tooth decay than previously believed."}], "question": "What did Sutton’s research discover about earlier studies in North America?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "They should reveal their true motivations."}, {"content": "They should not decide the fluoridation policy."}, {"content": "They are solely concerned with scientific truths."}, {"content": "They cannot reach agreement on the fluoridation issue."}], "question": " In the last paragraph, what does the writer say about scientists?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. The optimum amount of fluorine in fluoridated water is calculated partly according to</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>how hot the area is.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “The desired concentration of fluoride in public water is approximately one part per million, depending on the <strong>regional temperature</strong> and hence the amount of water people are likely to drink.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nồng độ fluoride tối ưu phụ thuộc vào nhiệt độ khu vực (regional temperature), vì nhiệt độ ảnh hưởng đến lượng nước mà mọi người uống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>28. One reason given by the writer for opposing fluoridation is that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>obligatory fluoridation takes away personal freedom.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “Third, fluoridation is thought to be an <strong>infringement on individual rights</strong> because it is <strong>compulsory medication</strong> of all members of a community.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc fluoride hóa bắt buộc (compulsory/obligatory) bị coi là vi phạm quyền cá nhân (infringement on individual rights/takes away personal freedom).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>29. The writer mentions Kuhn in order to</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>show that science can be influenced by non-scientific considerations.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “According to Kuhn, the shift from one scientific way of thinking to another is not made solely on the basis of clear rules of formal scientific practice, but <strong>can include social factors</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả dùng Kuhn để minh họa rằng sự thay đổi trong khoa học không chỉ dựa vào quy tắc khoa học mà còn có thể bao gồm các yếu tố xã hội (social factors/non-scientific considerations).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>30. What did Sutton’s research discover about earlier studies in North America?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>There were failings in the way they were carried out.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “An example is the study by Sutton in 1960, which analyzed the classic North American studies… and found that <strong>each showed significant methodological shortcomings</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sutton tìm thấy những thiếu sót đáng kể về mặt phương pháp (methodological shortcomings/failings in the way they were carried out) trong các nghiên cứu trước đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"22\">31. In the last paragraph, what does the writer say about scientists?</h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>They should not decide the fluoridation policy.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) “…social values are likely to be bound up in any decision about fluoridation, so this is not an issue on which <strong>declarations by scientific experts ought to be considered the final word</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả kết luận rằng ý kiến của các chuyên gia khoa học không nên được coi là lời cuối cùng, ngụ ý rằng họ <strong>không nên độc quyền quyết định</strong> chính sách fluoride hóa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ac0a6460-defe-47f4-9121-5d9b43de6eae', '7581de30-5371-43ad-aa56-e6a3ef8cd82f', 'fillup', 'Question 1-10', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3><strong>Library services</strong></h3>
<p>Area of living: in the west of Perthon</p>
<p>Best option – Minack Library</p>
<p>Located in {SKELLARN} Street, next to the {park}</p>
<p>Saturdays: open until {4.30|4:30} p.m.</p>
<p><strong>Children’s activities</strong></p>
<p>– a {drama} club (5-13 year olds)</p>
<p>– a {singing} club (every other Saturday)</p>
<p><strong>Adult activities</strong></p>
<p>– book of the Month club</p>
<p>– can meet local {artists} (about one a year)</p>
<p><strong>Services</strong></p>
<p>– can borrow {films}</p>
<p>– computers are available (can be booked)</p>
<p>– various {magazines} are available</p>
<p>– can drop off books, etc via the letter box (must give card {number})</p>
<p><strong>Library shop sells</strong></p>
<p>– postcards (small selection)</p>
<p>– {maps} (wide range)</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 1: JOINING A LIBRARY</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Good morning, Library Services.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, good morning. My family and I have recently moved to the area and we’d like to find where our nearest library is. We don’t have a car.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Right. So where abouts are you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> In Perth, in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(Example) west</strong>.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Fine. So I’ll just get the details on screen for you. Okay, your nearest one is the Minack Library.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Minack?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Yes. In<em> </em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">(1) Skellarn</strong></span></span> Street. Can you spell that? It’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">S-K-E-L-L-A-R-N</strong> Street.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Got that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> It’s very easy to find because it’s beside a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">(2) park</strong></span></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, I think I know that area. There’s a sports center near there, isn’t there?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> I don’t know of one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, I’m probably mistaken. Anyway, it’s probably a bit far for us to walk from home. Are there any buses?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Yes, it’s well served by public transport. There’s a stop about 5 minutes’ walk away.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, right. And when does the library open? We’ll most often want to come at the weekend.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> I’m afraid it’s not open on Sunday. Saturday opens at 9:00, closes at <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">(3) 4:30</strong> p.m</span></span>. We shut at 5 on weekdays.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That’s fine. Now, I’ve got two kids, 14 and 9, and I wondered whether you have any special activities for them. In our last place, we had an art club.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Well, the library does run a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">(4) drama</strong></span></span> club, but that would only be suitable for your younger child. It’s open for five to 13 year olds.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> A pity it’s not open to both of them. Have you anything they could both go to?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Well, there’s no reading club that would suit them both. Oh, but there’s a<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">(5) singing</strong></span></span> club that’s held every second Saturday afternoon for children of all ages up to 16.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Excellent.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Now, because we’re new to the area, I’m also wanting to get involved in local activities.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Well, Minack does some sessions for adults as well. There’s a “Book of the Month” club.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That’s good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> And I know that about once every 12 months, they have a session where you can meet <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">(6) artists</strong></span>, you know, from the local area.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> How interesting! Well, that sounds like a full program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Now, while I’m on the phone, can I check what the facilities are? Can you take out CDs?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Not CDs, I’m afraid, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">(7) films</strong></span>, yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Right. I’ll make a note of that. Anything else you need to know?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> Oh, yes. We have 10 computers and we also stock several <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">(8) magazines</strong></span>, including Business, Healthcare, and Hobbies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Same as my last place.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> And there is a new drop-off facility where you can post any item through the door if it’s after hours. All you have to do is attach a note to it with the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">(9) number</strong></span> on your card clearly written.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That sounds good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> And we do have a small shop on the premises where we sell postcards. We don’t have many, but it’s a popular service.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, that’s a good idea.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Staff:</strong> They’re very popular. We also have an impressive range of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">(10) maps</strong></span> of the surrounding area for sale.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Well, it sounds like you’ve got…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a37c72a0-2744-403c-802f-6303c6ad88cd', 'f7305d07-044b-4bd8-8248-6dbd05071fec', 'radio', 'Questions 38 – 40', '', '<p data-path-to-node="10">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="27">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="30">B</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="33">C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="38">D</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="11">Write the correct letter in boxes 38-40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A it was much more aggressive."}, {"option_text": "B it was more able to cope with danger."}, {"option_text": "C it had got more used to dealing with people."}, {"option_text": "D it had a much larger and more varied territory."}], "question": "The green iguana caused the blue iguana to decline because"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A They prefer plants that have very strong flavours."}, {"option_text": "B They need to eat a wide variety of plants every day."}, {"option_text": "C They are able to assess which plants they can eat."}, {"option_text": "D They remember plants by the texture of their leaves."}], "question": "What does the writer say about the iguanas'' feeding habits?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A He is proud of what has been achieved so far."}, {"option_text": "B He regrets the serious injuries he has had to suffer."}, {"option_text": "C He wishes there were more people to help at the centre."}, {"option_text": "D He is delighted to have made close contact with all the animals."}], "question": "How does Alberto Estevanovic feel about the iguana conservation programme?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. The green iguana caused the blue iguana to decline because — {B} it was more able to cope with danger.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the abundance of predators and other hazards had made the <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">green iguana much more able to defend itself</strong> than its relatively <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">naïve</strong> Caribbean relative…”</em> (Đoạn C)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc so sánh loài cự đà xanh (green) có khả năng tự vệ trước kẻ thù và các mối nguy hiểm tốt hơn so với loài bản địa “ngây thơ” (naïve). “Cope with danger” chính là cách diễn đạt khác của “defend itself against hazards/predators”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. What does the writer say about the iguanas’ feeding habits? — {C} They are able to assess which plants they can eat.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In that way, they <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">classify whether something is edible or not</strong> – information they will retain for life.”</em> (Đoạn F)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông qua việc dùng lưỡi và cắn thử một miếng nhỏ, cự đà có thể phân loại (classify) xem thứ đó có ăn được hay không (edible or not). Hành động này chính là đánh giá (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">assess</strong>) nguồn thức ăn của chúng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. How does Alberto Estevanovic feel about the iguana conservation programme? — {A} He is proud of what has been achieved so far.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“One of the wardens, Alberto Estevanovic, says that the rescue programme is still young but they feel they now <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">have something to boast about</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn G)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “have something to boast about” (có điều gì đó để tự hào/khoe khoang) tương ứng trực tiếp với cảm giác tự hào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">proud</strong>) về những thành tựu mà chương trình đã đạt được.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('487bf709-b44d-4b50-b231-6060498770e5', '28745792-080a-417a-b40a-7ee3cdedc7b1', 'fillup', 'Questions 1 - 10', '<p>Complete the form below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Booking a residential workshop</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Course required: drama workshop</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Full name of participant: Jan {Creswick}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Previous course attended: Writing for the {theater|theatre}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Address: 20, Gregory {place}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Current occupation: {waitress}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Date chosen course begins: {13 June|13th June| June 13| June 13th} </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Estimated arrival time: {5.30|5:30} pm</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Special dietary requests: no {milk} products</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Preferred afternoon course: {comic} work</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>First source of course information: {internet}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pre-course material requested: the {leaflet} mentioned in the publicity</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: BOOKING A RESIDENTIAL WORKSHOP</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Hello, Creative Centre.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Hello there. I''m phoning to book a place on your next two-day drama workshop.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> OK, let me just check... um, yes, we''ve still got room on that course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan: </strong>Great.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Can I have your full name?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes, it''s Jan <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">(Q1) Creswick</strong></span>. Uh, that''s C-R-E-S-W-I-C-K.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Thanks, Jan. And are you coming on your own?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> And have you done any of our courses before?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes, I did one a couple of years ago.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great, so you may be on our computer records. Um, which course did you do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"9\">(Q2) Theatre</strong></span> course (Writing for the Theatre).</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> OK, right, yes, here we are. Oh, so that''s 20 Gregory Avenue?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Uh, Gregory <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">(Q3) Place</strong></span>, actually.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, I''ll correct that on the computer. Uh-huh. And can I ask if you work?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes. I want to be an actor, but I''m working as a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(Q4) waitress</strong></span> at the moment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> After this course, who knows? Right, back to the paperwork. So we''re enrolling you on the two-day course that starts tomorrow, May 30th?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Oh, uh, sorry, no, on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">(Q5) 13th of June</strong> (or <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">13 June</strong>)</span>. I meant the one starting in two weeks. Is that still alright?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh, that''s fine.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ACCOMMODATION &amp; DETAILS (Questions 6–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Can you tell me something about accommodation?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Yes, people usually come the evening before the course starts. The cost of the course includes accommodation for 2 nights.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Well, I''ll make sure I''m there in good time so I can meet the others that evening and settle in. Is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">(Q6) 5:30</strong></span> too early to arrive?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> No, that''s fine. And you''ll finish no later than 5:00 on the last day.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Right, just a few other things. Any dietary information we should know? All the food is provided and we use organic produce as often as we can.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Oh, that sounds great. But I don''t eat anything that''s made from <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">(Q7) milk</strong></span>.I know that can be difficult.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh, it''s not a problem. What about meat? Do you eat that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> I don''t eat much of it, but that''s fine. You don''t need to note that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Sure.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan: </strong>Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Hey, I am really looking forward to this.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Haha, great. I don''t know if you know this, but we may divide into two groups in the afternoon if we have more than 16 people on the course. If we do that, there''ll be a choice of doing <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">(Q8) comic</strong></span> or what we call classic work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Oh, I''d always go with comedy. I''m much more interested in that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Now, how did you find out about this course? Was it the advert in the Sunday newspaper?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> No, in fact, I looked for drama courses on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">(Q9) internet</strong></span> and I saw that you were doing one. When I read about it, I just thought hey, why not?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan: </strong>I saw that you send out some pre-course material?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> I don''t have much time to read any of the books you''re recommending, but I''d be grateful for your <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(Q10) leaflet</strong></span></span>, the one you mentioned in your publicity.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Sure, I''ll put a copy in the post to you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"1725\">Jan:</strong> Thanks a lot. I can''t wait!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Haha, wait till you see...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('da464470-b9d1-4ba3-8c27-8525ca1471fa', '539b2708-48a5-430c-ac11-a5f97c931866', 'radio', 'Questions 32-35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT</strong> <strong>GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scientific knowledge should be kept separate from social values."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many sociologists have disregarded the doubts that some scientists have concerning fluoridation."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Sutton’s findings have been given insufficient attention by scientists outside of North America."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There are valid arguments on both sides of the fluoridation debate."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32. Scientific knowledge should be kept separate from social values.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Tác giả phê bình quan điểm truyền thống, thay vào đó ủng hộ quan điểm cho rằng kiến thức khoa học <strong>“is socially negotiated, and inevitably linked to the values of the relevant parties”</strong> (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Quan điểm của tác giả là kiến thức khoa học <strong>không thể tách rời</strong> khỏi các giá trị và quy trình xã hội, mâu thuẫn với việc phải giữ chúng tách biệt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>33. Many sociologists have disregarded the doubts that some scientists have concerning fluoridation.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Tác giả nhận xét rằng các nhà xã hội học đã <strong>“downplayed an important part of the debate by ignoring the number of eminent scientists who have questioned aspects of fluoridation”</strong> (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định các nhà xã hội học đã xem nhẹ (disregarded/downplayed) các nghi ngờ của một số nhà khoa học nổi tiếng về fluoride hóa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. Sutton’s findings have been given insufficient attention by scientists outside of North America.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói rằng sách của Sutton <strong>“is not cited in a single analysis of the fluoridation issue by any sociologist”</strong> (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Chỉ có thông tin về việc các <strong>nhà xã hội học</strong> bỏ qua công trình của Sutton. <strong>Không có thông tin</strong> để xác định liệu các <strong>nhà khoa học</strong> bên ngoài Bắc Mỹ có bỏ qua công trình này hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. There are valid arguments on both sides of the fluoridation debate.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) Tác giả trình bày lập luận của cả hai bên và kết luận rằng sự khác biệt này <strong>“is not between rationality and irrationality but is a legitimate difference in values”</strong> (là sự khác biệt hợp pháp về giá trị).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc thừa nhận đây là sự khác biệt hợp pháp (legitimate difference) ngụ ý rằng cả hai bên đều có những lập luận hợp lý (valid arguments) dựa trên các giá trị xã hội khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
